5371  CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&ParamIn).withElementType(
5372  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(RHSVD->getType())->getPointerTo()),
5373  C.getPointerType(RHSVD->getType())->castAs<PointerType>()));
5374  PrivateScope.Privatize();
5375  // Emit the combiner body:
5376  // %2 = <ReductionOp>(<type> *%lhs, <type> *%rhs)
5377  // store <type> %2, <type>* %lhs
5378  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().emitSingleReductionCombiner(
5379  CGF, ReductionOp, PrivateRef, cast<DeclRefExpr>(LHS),
5380  cast<DeclRefExpr>(RHS));
5381  CGF.FinishFunction();
5382  return Fn;
5383 }
5384 
5385 /// Emits reduction finalizer function:
5386 /// \code
5387 /// void @.red_fini(void* %arg) {
5388 /// %0 = bitcast void* %arg to <type>*
5389 /// <destroy>(<type>* %0)
5390 /// ret void
5391 /// }
5392 /// \endcode
5393 static llvm::Value *emitReduceFiniFunction(CodeGenModule &CGM,
5394  SourceLocation Loc,
5395  ReductionCodeGen &RCG, unsigned N) {
5396  if (!RCG.needCleanups(N))
5397  return nullptr;
5398  ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
5399  FunctionArgList Args;
5400  ImplicitParamDecl Param(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr, C.VoidPtrTy,
5401  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
5402  Args.emplace_back(&Param);
5403  const auto &FnInfo =
5404  CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(C.VoidTy, Args);
5405  llvm::FunctionType *FnTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
5406  std::string Name = CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getName({"red_fini", ""});
5407  auto *Fn = llvm::Function::Create(FnTy, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
5408  Name, &CGM.getModule());
5409  CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, FnInfo);
5410  Fn->setDoesNotRecurse();
5411  CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
5412  CGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), C.VoidTy, Fn, FnInfo, Args, Loc, Loc);
5413  Address PrivateAddr = CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(
5414  CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&Param), C.VoidPtrTy.castAs<PointerType>());
5415  llvm::Value *Size = nullptr;
5416  // If the size of the reduction item is non-constant, load it from global
5417  // threadprivate variable.
5418  if (RCG.getSizes(N).second) {
5419  Address SizeAddr = CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfArtificialThreadPrivate(
5420  CGF, CGM.getContext().getSizeType(),
5421  generateUniqueName(CGM, "reduction_size", RCG.getRefExpr(N)));
5422  Size = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(SizeAddr, /*Volatile=*/false,
5423  CGM.getContext().getSizeType(), Loc);
5424  }
5425  RCG.emitAggregateType(CGF, N, Size);
5426  // Emit the finalizer body:
5427  // <destroy>(<type>* %0)
5428  RCG.emitCleanups(CGF, N, PrivateAddr);
5429  CGF.FinishFunction(Loc);
5430  return Fn;
5431 }
5432 
5433 llvm::Value *CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTaskReductionInit(
5434  CodeGenFunction &CGF, SourceLocation Loc, ArrayRef<const Expr *> LHSExprs,
5435  ArrayRef<const Expr *> RHSExprs, const OMPTaskDataTy &Data) {
5436  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint() || Data.ReductionVars.empty())
5437  return nullptr;
5438 
5439  // Build typedef struct:
5440  // kmp_taskred_input {
5441  // void *reduce_shar; // shared reduction item
5442  // void *reduce_orig; // original reduction item used for initialization
5443  // size_t reduce_size; // size of data item
5444  // void *reduce_init; // data initialization routine
5445  // void *reduce_fini; // data finalization routine
5446  // void *reduce_comb; // data combiner routine
5447  // kmp_task_red_flags_t flags; // flags for additional info from compiler
5448  // } kmp_taskred_input_t;
5449  ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
5450  RecordDecl *RD = C.buildImplicitRecord("kmp_taskred_input_t");
5451  RD->startDefinition();
5452  const FieldDecl *SharedFD = addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, C.VoidPtrTy);
5453  const FieldDecl *OrigFD = addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, C.VoidPtrTy);
5454  const FieldDecl *SizeFD = addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, C.getSizeType());
5455  const FieldDecl *InitFD = addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, C.VoidPtrTy);
5456  const FieldDecl *FiniFD = addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, C.VoidPtrTy);
5457  const FieldDecl *CombFD = addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, C.VoidPtrTy);
5458  const FieldDecl *FlagsFD = addFieldToRecordDecl(
5459  C, RD, C.getIntTypeForBitwidth(/*DestWidth=*/32, /*Signed=*/false));
5460  RD->completeDefinition();
5461  QualType RDType = C.getRecordType(RD);
5462  unsigned Size = Data.ReductionVars.size();
5463  llvm::APInt ArraySize(/*numBits=*/64, Size);
5464  QualType ArrayRDType =
5465  C.getConstantArrayType(RDType, ArraySize, nullptr,
5466  ArraySizeModifier::Normal, /*IndexTypeQuals=*/0);
5467  // kmp_task_red_input_t .rd_input.[Size];
5468  RawAddress TaskRedInput = CGF.CreateMemTemp(ArrayRDType, ".rd_input.");
5469  ReductionCodeGen RCG(Data.ReductionVars, Data.ReductionOrigs,
5470  Data.ReductionCopies, Data.ReductionOps);
5471  for (unsigned Cnt = 0; Cnt < Size; ++Cnt) {
5472  // kmp_task_red_input_t &ElemLVal = .rd_input.[Cnt];
5473  llvm::Value *Idxs[] = {llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.SizeTy, /*V=*/0),
5474  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.SizeTy, Cnt)};
5475  llvm::Value *GEP = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
5476  TaskRedInput.getElementType(), TaskRedInput.getPointer(), Idxs,
5477  /*SignedIndices=*/false, /*IsSubtraction=*/false, Loc,
5478  ".rd_input.gep.");
5479  LValue ElemLVal = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignRawAddrLValue(GEP, RDType);
5480  // ElemLVal.reduce_shar = &Shareds[Cnt];
5481  LValue SharedLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(ElemLVal, SharedFD);
5482  RCG.emitSharedOrigLValue(CGF, Cnt);
5483  llvm::Value *Shared = RCG.getSharedLValue(Cnt).getPointer(CGF);
5484  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Shared, SharedLVal);
5485  // ElemLVal.reduce_orig = &Origs[Cnt];
5486  LValue OrigLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(ElemLVal, OrigFD);
5487  llvm::Value *Orig = RCG.getOrigLValue(Cnt).getPointer(CGF);
5488  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Orig, OrigLVal);
5489 
5490  RCG.emitAggregateType(CGF, Cnt);
5491  llvm::Value *SizeValInChars;
5492  llvm::Value *SizeVal;
5493  std::tie(SizeValInChars, SizeVal) = RCG.getSizes(Cnt);
5494  // We use delayed creation/initialization for VLAs and array sections. It is
5495  // required because runtime does not provide the way to pass the sizes of
5496  // VLAs/array sections to initializer/combiner/finalizer functions. Instead
5497  // threadprivate global variables are used to store these values and use
5498  // them in the functions.
5499  bool DelayedCreation = !!SizeVal;
5500  SizeValInChars = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(SizeValInChars, CGM.SizeTy,
5501  /*isSigned=*/false);
5502  LValue SizeLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(ElemLVal, SizeFD);
5503  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(SizeValInChars, SizeLVal);
5504  // ElemLVal.reduce_init = init;
5505  LValue InitLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(ElemLVal, InitFD);
5506  llvm::Value *InitAddr = emitReduceInitFunction(CGM, Loc, RCG, Cnt);
5507  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(InitAddr, InitLVal);
5508  // ElemLVal.reduce_fini = fini;
5509  LValue FiniLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(ElemLVal, FiniFD);
5510  llvm::Value *Fini = emitReduceFiniFunction(CGM, Loc, RCG, Cnt);
5511  llvm::Value *FiniAddr =
5512  Fini ? Fini : llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGM.VoidPtrTy);
5513  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(FiniAddr, FiniLVal);
5514  // ElemLVal.reduce_comb = comb;
5515  LValue CombLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(ElemLVal, CombFD);
5516  llvm::Value *CombAddr = emitReduceCombFunction(
5517  CGM, Loc, RCG, Cnt, Data.ReductionOps[Cnt], LHSExprs[Cnt],
5518  RHSExprs[Cnt], Data.ReductionCopies[Cnt]);
5519 
5520  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(CombAddr, CombLVal);
5521  // ElemLVal.flags = 0;
5522  LValue FlagsLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(ElemLVal, FlagsFD);
5523  if (DelayedCreation) {
5524  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(
5525  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.Int32Ty, /*V=*/1, /*isSigned=*/true),
5526  FlagsLVal);
5527  } else
5528  CGF.EmitNullInitialization(FlagsLVal.getAddress(CGF),
5529  FlagsLVal.getType());
5530  }
5531  if (Data.IsReductionWithTaskMod) {
5532  // Build call void *__kmpc_taskred_modifier_init(ident_t *loc, int gtid, int
5533  // is_ws, int num, void *data);
5534  llvm::Value *IdentTLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc);
5535  llvm::Value *GTid = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(getThreadID(CGF, Loc),
5536  CGM.IntTy, /*isSigned=*/true);
5537  llvm::Value *Args[] = {
5538  IdentTLoc, GTid,
5539  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Data.IsWorksharingReduction ? 1 : 0,
5540  /*isSigned=*/true),
5541  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Size, /*isSigned=*/true),
5542  CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
5543  TaskRedInput.getPointer(), CGM.VoidPtrTy)};
5544  return CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
5545  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
5546  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_taskred_modifier_init),
5547  Args);
5548  }
5549  // Build call void *__kmpc_taskred_init(int gtid, int num_data, void *data);
5550  llvm::Value *Args[] = {
5551  CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(getThreadID(CGF, Loc), CGM.IntTy,
5552  /*isSigned=*/true),
5553  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy, Size, /*isSigned=*/true),
5554  CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(TaskRedInput.getPointer(),
5555  CGM.VoidPtrTy)};
5556  return CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
5557  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_taskred_init),
5558  Args);
5559 }
5560 
5561 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTaskReductionFini(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5562  SourceLocation Loc,
5563  bool IsWorksharingReduction) {
5564  // Build call void *__kmpc_taskred_modifier_init(ident_t *loc, int gtid, int
5565  // is_ws, int num, void *data);
5566  llvm::Value *IdentTLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc);
5567  llvm::Value *GTid = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(getThreadID(CGF, Loc),
5568  CGM.IntTy, /*isSigned=*/true);
5569  llvm::Value *Args[] = {IdentTLoc, GTid,
5570  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGM.IntTy,
5571  IsWorksharingReduction ? 1 : 0,
5572  /*isSigned=*/true)};
5573  (void)CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
5574  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
5575  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_task_reduction_modifier_fini),
5576  Args);
5577 }

5579 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTaskReductionFixups(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5580  SourceLocation Loc,
5581  ReductionCodeGen &RCG,
5582  unsigned N) {
5583  auto Sizes = RCG.getSizes(N);
5584  // Emit threadprivate global variable if the type is non-constant
5585  // (Sizes.second = nullptr).
5586  if (Sizes.second) {
5587  llvm::Value *SizeVal = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(Sizes.second, CGM.SizeTy,
5588  /*isSigned=*/false);
5589  Address SizeAddr = getAddrOfArtificialThreadPrivate(
5590  CGF, CGM.getContext().getSizeType(),
5591  generateUniqueName(CGM, "reduction_size", RCG.getRefExpr(N)));
5592  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(SizeVal, SizeAddr, /*IsVolatile=*/false);
5593  }
5594 }

5596 Address CGOpenMPRuntime::getTaskReductionItem(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5597  SourceLocation Loc,
5598  llvm::Value *ReductionsPtr,
5599  LValue SharedLVal) {
5600  // Build call void *__kmpc_task_reduction_get_th_data(int gtid, void *tg, void
5601  // *d);
5602  llvm::Value *Args[] = {CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(getThreadID(CGF, Loc),
5603  CGM.IntTy,
5604  /*isSigned=*/true),
5605  ReductionsPtr,
5606  CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
5607  SharedLVal.getPointer(CGF), CGM.VoidPtrTy)};
5608  return Address(
5609  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
5610  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
5611  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_task_reduction_get_th_data),
5612  Args),
5613  CGF.Int8Ty, SharedLVal.getAlignment());
5614 }
5615 
5616 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTaskwaitCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF, SourceLocation Loc,
5617  const OMPTaskDataTy &Data) {
5618  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
5619  return;
5620 
5621  if (CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIRBuilder && Data.Dependences.empty()) {
5622  // TODO: Need to support taskwait with dependences in the OpenMPIRBuilder.
5623  OMPBuilder.createTaskwait(CGF.Builder);
5624  } else {
5625  llvm::Value *ThreadID = getThreadID(CGF, Loc);
5626  llvm::Value *UpLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc);
5627  auto &M = CGM.getModule();
5628  Address DependenciesArray = Address::invalid();
5629  llvm::Value *NumOfElements;
5630  std::tie(NumOfElements, DependenciesArray) =
5631  emitDependClause(CGF, Data.Dependences, Loc);
5632  if (!Data.Dependences.empty()) {
5633  llvm::Value *DepWaitTaskArgs[7];
5634  DepWaitTaskArgs[0] = UpLoc;
5635  DepWaitTaskArgs[1] = ThreadID;
5636  DepWaitTaskArgs[2] = NumOfElements;
5637  DepWaitTaskArgs[3] = DependenciesArray.emitRawPointer(CGF);
5638  DepWaitTaskArgs[4] = CGF.Builder.getInt32(0);
5639  DepWaitTaskArgs[5] = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGF.VoidPtrTy);
5640  DepWaitTaskArgs[6] =
5641  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, Data.HasNowaitClause);
5642 
5643  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope LocalScope(CGF);
5644 
5645  // Build void __kmpc_omp_taskwait_deps_51(ident_t *, kmp_int32 gtid,
5646  // kmp_int32 ndeps, kmp_depend_info_t *dep_list, kmp_int32
5647  // ndeps_noalias, kmp_depend_info_t *noalias_dep_list,
5648  // kmp_int32 has_no_wait); if dependence info is specified.
5649  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
5650  M, OMPRTL___kmpc_omp_taskwait_deps_51),
5651  DepWaitTaskArgs);
5652 
5653  } else {
5654 
5655  // Build call kmp_int32 __kmpc_omp_taskwait(ident_t *loc, kmp_int32
5656  // global_tid);
5657  llvm::Value *Args[] = {UpLoc, ThreadID};
5658  // Ignore return result until untied tasks are supported.
5659  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
5660  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(M, OMPRTL___kmpc_omp_taskwait),
5661  Args);
5662  }
5663  }
5664 
5665  if (auto *Region = dyn_cast_or_null<CGOpenMPRegionInfo>(CGF.CapturedStmtInfo))
5666  Region->emitUntiedSwitch(CGF);
5667 }
5668 
5669 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitInlinedDirective(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5670  OpenMPDirectiveKind InnerKind,
5671  const RegionCodeGenTy &CodeGen,
5672  bool HasCancel) {
5673  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
5674  return;
5675  InlinedOpenMPRegionRAII Region(CGF, CodeGen, InnerKind, HasCancel,
5676  InnerKind != OMPD_critical &&
5677  InnerKind != OMPD_master &&
5678  InnerKind != OMPD_masked);
5679  CGF.CapturedStmtInfo->EmitBody(CGF, /*S=*/nullptr);
5680 }
5681 
5682 namespace {
5683 enum RTCancelKind {
5684  CancelNoreq = 0,
5685  CancelParallel = 1,
5686  CancelLoop = 2,
5687  CancelSections = 3,
5688  CancelTaskgroup = 4
5689 };
5690 } // anonymous namespace
5691 
5692 static RTCancelKind getCancellationKind(OpenMPDirectiveKind CancelRegion) {
5693  RTCancelKind CancelKind = CancelNoreq;
5694  if (CancelRegion == OMPD_parallel)
5695  CancelKind = CancelParallel;
5696  else if (CancelRegion == OMPD_for)
5697  CancelKind = CancelLoop;
5698  else if (CancelRegion == OMPD_sections)
5699  CancelKind = CancelSections;
5700  else {
5701  assert(CancelRegion == OMPD_taskgroup);
5702  CancelKind = CancelTaskgroup;
5703  }
5704  return CancelKind;
5705 }
5706 
5707 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitCancellationPointCall(
5708  CodeGenFunction &CGF, SourceLocation Loc,
5709  OpenMPDirectiveKind CancelRegion) {
5710  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
5711  return;
5712  // Build call kmp_int32 __kmpc_cancellationpoint(ident_t *loc, kmp_int32
5713  // global_tid, kmp_int32 cncl_kind);
5714  if (auto *OMPRegionInfo =
5715  dyn_cast_or_null<CGOpenMPRegionInfo>(CGF.CapturedStmtInfo)) {
5716  // For 'cancellation point taskgroup', the task region info may not have a
5717  // cancel. This may instead happen in another adjacent task.
5718  if (CancelRegion == OMPD_taskgroup || OMPRegionInfo->hasCancel()) {
5719  llvm::Value *Args[] = {
5720  emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc), getThreadID(CGF, Loc),
5721  CGF.Builder.getInt32(getCancellationKind(CancelRegion))};
5722  // Ignore return result until untied tasks are supported.
5723  llvm::Value *Result = CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
5724  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
5725  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_cancellationpoint),
5726  Args);
5727  // if (__kmpc_cancellationpoint()) {
5728  // call i32 @__kmpc_cancel_barrier( // for parallel cancellation only
5729  // exit from construct;
5730  // }
5731  llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".cancel.exit");
5732  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".cancel.continue");
5733  llvm::Value *Cmp = CGF.Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Result);
5734  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Cmp, ExitBB, ContBB);
5735  CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB);
5736  if (CancelRegion == OMPD_parallel)
5737  emitBarrierCall(CGF, Loc, OMPD_unknown, /*EmitChecks=*/false);
5738  // exit from construct;
5739  CodeGenFunction::JumpDest CancelDest =
5740  CGF.getOMPCancelDestination(OMPRegionInfo->getDirectiveKind());
5741  CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(CancelDest);
5742  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
5743  }
5744  }
5745 }
5746 
5747 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitCancelCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF, SourceLocation Loc,
5748  const Expr *IfCond,
5749  OpenMPDirectiveKind CancelRegion) {
5750  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
5751  return;
5752  // Build call kmp_int32 __kmpc_cancel(ident_t *loc, kmp_int32 global_tid,
5753  // kmp_int32 cncl_kind);
5754  auto &M = CGM.getModule();
5755  if (auto *OMPRegionInfo =
5756  dyn_cast_or_null<CGOpenMPRegionInfo>(CGF.CapturedStmtInfo)) {
5757  auto &&ThenGen = [this, &M, Loc, CancelRegion,
5758  OMPRegionInfo](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &) {
5759  CGOpenMPRuntime &RT = CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime();
5760  llvm::Value *Args[] = {
5761  RT.emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc), RT.getThreadID(CGF, Loc),
5762  CGF.Builder.getInt32(getCancellationKind(CancelRegion))};
5763  // Ignore return result until untied tasks are supported.
5764  llvm::Value *Result = CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
5765  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(M, OMPRTL___kmpc_cancel), Args);
5766  // if (__kmpc_cancel()) {
5767  // call i32 @__kmpc_cancel_barrier( // for parallel cancellation only
5768  // exit from construct;
5769  // }
5770  llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".cancel.exit");
5771  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB = CGF.createBasicBlock(".cancel.continue");
5772  llvm::Value *Cmp = CGF.Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Result);
5773  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Cmp, ExitBB, ContBB);
5774  CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB);
5775  if (CancelRegion == OMPD_parallel)
5776  RT.emitBarrierCall(CGF, Loc, OMPD_unknown, /*EmitChecks=*/false);
5777  // exit from construct;
5778  CodeGenFunction::JumpDest CancelDest =
5779  CGF.getOMPCancelDestination(OMPRegionInfo->getDirectiveKind());
5780  CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(CancelDest);
5781  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
5782  };
5783  if (IfCond) {
5784  emitIfClause(CGF, IfCond, ThenGen,
5785  [](CodeGenFunction &, PrePostActionTy &) {});
5786  } else {
5787  RegionCodeGenTy ThenRCG(ThenGen);
5788  ThenRCG(CGF);
5789  }
5790  }
5791 }
5792 
5793 namespace {
5794 /// Cleanup action for uses_allocators support.
5795 class OMPUsesAllocatorsActionTy final : public PrePostActionTy {
5796  ArrayRef<std::pair<const Expr *, const Expr *>> Allocators;
5797 
5798 public:
5799  OMPUsesAllocatorsActionTy(
5800  ArrayRef<std::pair<const Expr *, const Expr *>> Allocators)
5801  : Allocators(Allocators) {}
5802  void Enter(CodeGenFunction &CGF) override {
5803  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
5804  return;
5805  for (const auto &AllocatorData : Allocators) {
5806  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().emitUsesAllocatorsInit(
5807  CGF, AllocatorData.first, AllocatorData.second);
5808  }
5809  }
5810  void Exit(CodeGenFunction &CGF) override {
5811  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
5812  return;
5813  for (const auto &AllocatorData : Allocators) {
5814  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().emitUsesAllocatorsFini(CGF,
5815  AllocatorData.first);
5816  }
5817  }
5818 };
5819 } // namespace
5820 
5821 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetOutlinedFunction(
5822  const OMPExecutableDirective &D, StringRef ParentName,
5823  llvm::Function *&OutlinedFn, llvm::Constant *&OutlinedFnID,
5824  bool IsOffloadEntry, const RegionCodeGenTy &CodeGen) {
5825  assert(!ParentName.empty() && "Invalid target entry parent name!");
5826  HasEmittedTargetRegion = true;
5827  SmallVector<std::pair<const Expr *, const Expr *>, 4> Allocators;
5828  for (const auto *C : D.getClausesOfKind<OMPUsesAllocatorsClause>()) {
5829  for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumberOfAllocators(); I < E; ++I) {
5830  const OMPUsesAllocatorsClause::Data D = C->getAllocatorData(I);
5831  if (!D.AllocatorTraits)
5832  continue;
5833  Allocators.emplace_back(D.Allocator, D.AllocatorTraits);
5834  }
5835  }
5836  OMPUsesAllocatorsActionTy UsesAllocatorAction(Allocators);
5837  CodeGen.setAction(UsesAllocatorAction);
5838  emitTargetOutlinedFunctionHelper(D, ParentName, OutlinedFn, OutlinedFnID,
5839  IsOffloadEntry, CodeGen);
5840 }
5841 
5842 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitUsesAllocatorsInit(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5843  const Expr *Allocator,
5844  const Expr *AllocatorTraits) {
5845  llvm::Value *ThreadId = getThreadID(CGF, Allocator->getExprLoc());
5846  ThreadId = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(ThreadId, CGF.IntTy, /*isSigned=*/true);
5847  // Use default memspace handle.
5848  llvm::Value *MemSpaceHandle = llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGF.VoidPtrTy);
5849  llvm::Value *NumTraits = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5850  CGF.IntTy, cast<ConstantArrayType>(
5851  AllocatorTraits->getType()->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe())
5852  ->getSize()
5853  .getLimitedValue());
5854  LValue AllocatorTraitsLVal = CGF.EmitLValue(AllocatorTraits);
5855  Address Addr = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
5856  AllocatorTraitsLVal.getAddress(CGF), CGF.VoidPtrPtrTy, CGF.VoidPtrTy);
5857  AllocatorTraitsLVal = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy,
5858  AllocatorTraitsLVal.getBaseInfo(),
5859  AllocatorTraitsLVal.getTBAAInfo());
5860  llvm::Value *Traits = Addr.emitRawPointer(CGF);
5861 
5862  llvm::Value *AllocatorVal =
5863  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
5864  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_init_allocator),
5865  {ThreadId, MemSpaceHandle, NumTraits, Traits});
5866  // Store to allocator.
5867  CGF.EmitAutoVarAlloca(*cast<VarDecl>(
5868  cast<DeclRefExpr>(Allocator->IgnoreParenImpCasts())->getDecl()));
5869  LValue AllocatorLVal = CGF.EmitLValue(Allocator->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
5870  AllocatorVal =
5871  CGF.EmitScalarConversion(AllocatorVal, CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy,
5872  Allocator->getType(), Allocator->getExprLoc());
5873  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(AllocatorVal, AllocatorLVal);
5874 }
5875 
5876 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitUsesAllocatorsFini(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5877  const Expr *Allocator) {
5878  llvm::Value *ThreadId = getThreadID(CGF, Allocator->getExprLoc());
5879  ThreadId = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(ThreadId, CGF.IntTy, /*isSigned=*/true);
5880  LValue AllocatorLVal = CGF.EmitLValue(Allocator->IgnoreParenImpCasts());
5881  llvm::Value *AllocatorVal =
5882  CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(AllocatorLVal, Allocator->getExprLoc());
5883  AllocatorVal = CGF.EmitScalarConversion(AllocatorVal, Allocator->getType(),
5884  CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy,
5885  Allocator->getExprLoc());
5886  (void)CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
5887  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(CGM.getModule(),
5888  OMPRTL___kmpc_destroy_allocator),
5889  {ThreadId, AllocatorVal});
5890 }
5891 
5892 void CGOpenMPRuntime::computeMinAndMaxThreadsAndTeams(
5893  const OMPExecutableDirective &D, CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5894  int32_t &MinThreadsVal, int32_t &MaxThreadsVal, int32_t &MinTeamsVal,
5895  int32_t &MaxTeamsVal) {
5896 
5897  getNumTeamsExprForTargetDirective(CGF, D, MinTeamsVal, MaxTeamsVal);
5898  getNumThreadsExprForTargetDirective(CGF, D, MaxThreadsVal,
5899  /*UpperBoundOnly=*/true);
5900 
5901  for (auto *C : D.getClausesOfKind<OMPXAttributeClause>()) {
5902  for (auto *A : C->getAttrs()) {
5903  int32_t AttrMinThreadsVal = 1, AttrMaxThreadsVal = -1;
5904  int32_t AttrMinBlocksVal = 1, AttrMaxBlocksVal = -1;
5905  if (auto *Attr = dyn_cast<CUDALaunchBoundsAttr>(A))
5906  CGM.handleCUDALaunchBoundsAttr(nullptr, Attr, &AttrMaxThreadsVal,
5907  &AttrMinBlocksVal, &AttrMaxBlocksVal);
5908  else if (auto *Attr = dyn_cast<AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr>(A))
5909  CGM.handleAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(
5910  nullptr, Attr, /*ReqdWGS=*/nullptr, &AttrMinThreadsVal,
5911  &AttrMaxThreadsVal);
5912  else
5913  continue;
5914 
5915  MinThreadsVal = std::max(MinThreadsVal, AttrMinThreadsVal);
5916  if (AttrMaxThreadsVal > 0)
5917  MaxThreadsVal = MaxThreadsVal > 0
5918  ? std::min(MaxThreadsVal, AttrMaxThreadsVal)
5919  : AttrMaxThreadsVal;
5920  MinTeamsVal = std::max(MinTeamsVal, AttrMinBlocksVal);
5921  if (AttrMaxBlocksVal > 0)
5922  MaxTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal > 0 ? std::min(MaxTeamsVal, AttrMaxBlocksVal)
5923  : AttrMaxBlocksVal;
5924  }
5925  }
5926 }
5927 
5928 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetOutlinedFunctionHelper(
5929  const OMPExecutableDirective &D, StringRef ParentName,
5930  llvm::Function *&OutlinedFn, llvm::Constant *&OutlinedFnID,
5931  bool IsOffloadEntry, const RegionCodeGenTy &CodeGen) {
5932 
5933  llvm::TargetRegionEntryInfo EntryInfo =
5934  getEntryInfoFromPresumedLoc(CGM, OMPBuilder, D.getBeginLoc(), ParentName);
5935 
5936  CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM, true);
5937  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::FunctionGenCallback &&GenerateOutlinedFunction =
5938  [&CGF, &D, &CodeGen](StringRef EntryFnName) {
5939  const CapturedStmt &CS = *D.getCapturedStmt(OMPD_target);
5940 
5941  CGOpenMPTargetRegionInfo CGInfo(CS, CodeGen, EntryFnName);
5942  CodeGenFunction::CGCapturedStmtRAII CapInfoRAII(CGF, &CGInfo);
5943  return CGF.GenerateOpenMPCapturedStmtFunction(CS, D.getBeginLoc());
5944  };
5945 
5946  OMPBuilder.emitTargetRegionFunction(EntryInfo, GenerateOutlinedFunction,
5947  IsOffloadEntry, OutlinedFn, OutlinedFnID);
5948 
5949  if (!OutlinedFn)
5950  return;
5951 
5952  CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().setTargetAttributes(nullptr, OutlinedFn, CGM);
5953 
5954  for (auto *C : D.getClausesOfKind<OMPXAttributeClause>()) {
5955  for (auto *A : C->getAttrs()) {
5956  if (auto *Attr = dyn_cast<AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr>(A))
5957  CGM.handleAMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(OutlinedFn, Attr);
5958  }
5959  }
5960 }
5961 
5962 /// Checks if the expression is constant or does not have non-trivial function
5963 /// calls.
5964 static bool isTrivial(ASTContext &Ctx, const Expr * E) {
5965  // We can skip constant expressions.
5966  // We can skip expressions with trivial calls or simple expressions.
5967  return (E->isEvaluatable(Ctx, Expr::SE_AllowUndefinedBehavior) ||
5968  !E->hasNonTrivialCall(Ctx)) &&
5969  !E->HasSideEffects(Ctx, /*IncludePossibleEffects=*/true);
5970 }
5971 
5972 const Stmt *CGOpenMPRuntime::getSingleCompoundChild(ASTContext &Ctx,
5973  const Stmt *Body) {
5974  const Stmt *Child = Body->IgnoreContainers();
5975  while (const auto *C = dyn_cast_or_null<CompoundStmt>(Child)) {
5976  Child = nullptr;
5977  for (const Stmt *S : C->body()) {
5978  if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<Expr>(S)) {
5979  if (isTrivial(Ctx, E))
5980  continue;
5981  }
5982  // Some of the statements can be ignored.
5983  if (isa<AsmStmt>(S) || isa<NullStmt>(S) || isa<OMPFlushDirective>(S) ||
5984  isa<OMPBarrierDirective>(S) || isa<OMPTaskyieldDirective>(S))
5985  continue;
5986  // Analyze declarations.
5987  if (const auto *DS = dyn_cast<DeclStmt>(S)) {
5988  if (llvm::all_of(DS->decls(), [](const Decl *D) {
5989  if (isa<EmptyDecl>(D) || isa<DeclContext>(D) ||
5990  isa<TypeDecl>(D) || isa<PragmaCommentDecl>(D) ||
5991  isa<PragmaDetectMismatchDecl>(D) || isa<UsingDecl>(D) ||
5992  isa<UsingDirectiveDecl>(D) ||
5993  isa<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(D) ||
5994  isa<OMPThreadPrivateDecl>(D) || isa<OMPAllocateDecl>(D))
5995  return true;
5996  const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D);
5997  if (!VD)
5998  return false;
5999  return VD->hasGlobalStorage() || !VD->isUsed();
6000  }))
6001  continue;
6002  }
6003  // Found multiple children - cannot get the one child only.
6004  if (Child)
6005  return nullptr;
6006  Child = S;
6007  }
6008  if (Child)
6009  Child = Child->IgnoreContainers();
6010  }
6011  return Child;
6012 }
6013 
6014 const Expr *CGOpenMPRuntime::getNumTeamsExprForTargetDirective(
6015  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D, int32_t &MinTeamsVal,
6016  int32_t &MaxTeamsVal) {
6017 
6018  OpenMPDirectiveKind DirectiveKind = D.getDirectiveKind();
6019  assert(isOpenMPTargetExecutionDirective(DirectiveKind) &&
6020  "Expected target-based executable directive.");
6021  switch (DirectiveKind) {
6022  case OMPD_target: {
6023  const auto *CS = D.getInnermostCapturedStmt();
6024  const auto *Body =
6025  CS->getCapturedStmt()->IgnoreContainers(/*IgnoreCaptured=*/true);
6026  const Stmt *ChildStmt =
6027  CGOpenMPRuntime::getSingleCompoundChild(CGF.getContext(), Body);
6028  if (const auto *NestedDir =
6029  dyn_cast_or_null<OMPExecutableDirective>(ChildStmt)) {
6030  if (isOpenMPTeamsDirective(NestedDir->getDirectiveKind())) {
6031  if (NestedDir->hasClausesOfKind<OMPNumTeamsClause>()) {
6032  const Expr *NumTeams =
6033  NestedDir->getSingleClause<OMPNumTeamsClause>()->getNumTeams();
6034  if (NumTeams->isIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext()))
6035  if (auto Constant =
6036  NumTeams->getIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext()))
6037  MinTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal = Constant->getExtValue();
6038  return NumTeams;
6039  }
6040  MinTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal = 0;
6041  return nullptr;
6042  }
6043  if (isOpenMPParallelDirective(NestedDir->getDirectiveKind()) ||
6044  isOpenMPSimdDirective(NestedDir->getDirectiveKind())) {
6045  MinTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal = 1;
6046  return nullptr;
6047  }
6048  MinTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal = 1;
6049  return nullptr;
6050  }
6051  // A value of -1 is used to check if we need to emit no teams region
6052  MinTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal = -1;
6053  return nullptr;
6054  }
6055  case OMPD_target_teams_loop:
6056  case OMPD_target_teams:
6057  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute:
6058  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_simd:
6059  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
6060  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd: {
6061  if (D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPNumTeamsClause>()) {
6062  const Expr *NumTeams =
6063  D.getSingleClause<OMPNumTeamsClause>()->getNumTeams();
6064  if (NumTeams->isIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext()))
6065  if (auto Constant = NumTeams->getIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext()))
6066  MinTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal = Constant->getExtValue();
6067  return NumTeams;
6068  }
6069  MinTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal = 0;
6070  return nullptr;
6071  }
6072  case OMPD_target_parallel:
6073  case OMPD_target_parallel_for:
6074  case OMPD_target_parallel_for_simd:
6075  case OMPD_target_parallel_loop:
6076  case OMPD_target_simd:
6077  MinTeamsVal = MaxTeamsVal = 1;
6078  return nullptr;
6079  case OMPD_parallel:
6080  case OMPD_for:
6081  case OMPD_parallel_for:
6082  case OMPD_parallel_loop:
6083  case OMPD_parallel_master:
6084  case OMPD_parallel_sections:
6085  case OMPD_for_simd:
6086  case OMPD_parallel_for_simd:
6087  case OMPD_cancel:
6088  case OMPD_cancellation_point:
6089  case OMPD_ordered:
6090  case OMPD_threadprivate:
6091  case OMPD_allocate:
6092  case OMPD_task:
6093  case OMPD_simd:
6094  case OMPD_tile:
6095  case OMPD_unroll:
6096  case OMPD_sections:
6097  case OMPD_section:
6098  case OMPD_single:
6099  case OMPD_master:
6100  case OMPD_critical:
6101  case OMPD_taskyield:
6102  case OMPD_barrier:
6103  case OMPD_taskwait:
6104  case OMPD_taskgroup:
6105  case OMPD_atomic:
6106  case OMPD_flush:
6107  case OMPD_depobj:
6108  case OMPD_scan:
6109  case OMPD_teams:
6110  case OMPD_target_data:
6111  case OMPD_target_exit_data:
6112  case OMPD_target_enter_data:
6113  case OMPD_distribute:
6114  case OMPD_distribute_simd:
6115  case OMPD_distribute_parallel_for:
6116  case OMPD_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
6117  case OMPD_teams_distribute:
6118  case OMPD_teams_distribute_simd:
6119  case OMPD_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
6120  case OMPD_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
6121  case OMPD_target_update:
6122  case OMPD_declare_simd:
6123  case OMPD_declare_variant:
6124  case OMPD_begin_declare_variant:
6125  case OMPD_end_declare_variant:
6126  case OMPD_declare_target:
6127  case OMPD_end_declare_target:
6128  case OMPD_declare_reduction:
6129  case OMPD_declare_mapper:
6130  case OMPD_taskloop:
6131  case OMPD_taskloop_simd:
6132  case OMPD_master_taskloop:
6133  case OMPD_master_taskloop_simd:
6134  case OMPD_parallel_master_taskloop:
6135  case OMPD_parallel_master_taskloop_simd:
6136  case OMPD_requires:
6137  case OMPD_metadirective:
6138  case OMPD_unknown:
6139  break;
6140  default:
6141  break;
6142  }
6143  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected directive kind.");
6144 }
6145 
6146 llvm::Value *CGOpenMPRuntime::emitNumTeamsForTargetDirective(
6147  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D) {
6148  assert(!CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice &&
6149  "Clauses associated with the teams directive expected to be emitted "
6150  "only for the host!");
6151  CGBuilderTy &Bld = CGF.Builder;
6152  int32_t MinNT = -1, MaxNT = -1;
6153  const Expr *NumTeams =
6154  getNumTeamsExprForTargetDirective(CGF, D, MinNT, MaxNT);
6155  if (NumTeams != nullptr) {
6156  OpenMPDirectiveKind DirectiveKind = D.getDirectiveKind();
6157 
6158  switch (DirectiveKind) {
6159  case OMPD_target: {
6160  const auto *CS = D.getInnermostCapturedStmt();
6161  CGOpenMPInnerExprInfo CGInfo(CGF, *CS);
6162  CodeGenFunction::CGCapturedStmtRAII CapInfoRAII(CGF, &CGInfo);
6163  llvm::Value *NumTeamsVal = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(NumTeams,
6164  /*IgnoreResultAssign*/ true);
6165  return Bld.CreateIntCast(NumTeamsVal, CGF.Int32Ty,
6166  /*isSigned=*/true);
6167  }
6168  case OMPD_target_teams:
6169  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute:
6170  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_simd:
6171  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
6172  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd: {
6173  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope NumTeamsScope(CGF);
6174  llvm::Value *NumTeamsVal = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(NumTeams,
6175  /*IgnoreResultAssign*/ true);
6176  return Bld.CreateIntCast(NumTeamsVal, CGF.Int32Ty,
6177  /*isSigned=*/true);
6178  }
6179  default:
6180  break;
6181  }
6182  }
6183 
6184  assert(MinNT == MaxNT && "Num threads ranges require handling here.");
6185  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, MinNT);
6186 }
6187 
6188 /// Check for a num threads constant value (stored in \p DefaultVal), or
6189 /// expression (stored in \p E). If the value is conditional (via an if-clause),
6190 /// store the condition in \p CondVal. If \p E, and \p CondVal respectively, are
6191 /// nullptr, no expression evaluation is perfomed.
6192 static void getNumThreads(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CapturedStmt *CS,
6193  const Expr **E, int32_t &UpperBound,
6194  bool UpperBoundOnly, llvm::Value **CondVal) {
6195  const Stmt *Child = CGOpenMPRuntime::getSingleCompoundChild(
6196  CGF.getContext(), CS->getCapturedStmt());
6197  const auto *Dir = dyn_cast_or_null<OMPExecutableDirective>(Child);
6198  if (!Dir)
6199  return;
6200 
6201  if (isOpenMPParallelDirective(Dir->getDirectiveKind())) {
6202  // Handle if clause. If if clause present, the number of threads is
6203  // calculated as <cond> ? (<numthreads> ? <numthreads> : 0 ) : 1.
6204  if (CondVal && Dir->hasClausesOfKind<OMPIfClause>()) {
6205  CGOpenMPInnerExprInfo CGInfo(CGF, *CS);
6206  CodeGenFunction::CGCapturedStmtRAII CapInfoRAII(CGF, &CGInfo);
6207  const OMPIfClause *IfClause = nullptr;
6208  for (const auto *C : Dir->getClausesOfKind<OMPIfClause>()) {
6209  if (C->getNameModifier() == OMPD_unknown ||
6210  C->getNameModifier() == OMPD_parallel) {
6211  IfClause = C;
6212  break;
6213  }
6214  }
6215  if (IfClause) {
6216  const Expr *CondExpr = IfClause->getCondition();
6217  bool Result;
6218  if (CondExpr->EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(Result, CGF.getContext())) {
6219  if (!Result) {
6220  UpperBound = 1;
6221  return;
6222  }
6223  } else {
6224  CodeGenFunction::LexicalScope Scope(CGF, CondExpr->getSourceRange());
6225  if (const auto *PreInit =
6226  cast_or_null<DeclStmt>(IfClause->getPreInitStmt())) {
6227  for (const auto *I : PreInit->decls()) {
6228  if (!I->hasAttr<OMPCaptureNoInitAttr>()) {
6229  CGF.EmitVarDecl(cast<VarDecl>(*I));
6230  } else {
6231  CodeGenFunction::AutoVarEmission Emission =
6232  CGF.EmitAutoVarAlloca(cast<VarDecl>(*I));
6233  CGF.EmitAutoVarCleanups(Emission);
6234  }
6235  }
6236  *CondVal = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(CondExpr);
6237  }
6238  }
6239  }
6240  }
6241  // Check the value of num_threads clause iff if clause was not specified
6242  // or is not evaluated to false.
6243  if (Dir->hasClausesOfKind<OMPNumThreadsClause>()) {
6244  CGOpenMPInnerExprInfo CGInfo(CGF, *CS);
6245  CodeGenFunction::CGCapturedStmtRAII CapInfoRAII(CGF, &CGInfo);
6246  const auto *NumThreadsClause =
6247  Dir->getSingleClause<OMPNumThreadsClause>();
6248  const Expr *NTExpr = NumThreadsClause->getNumThreads();
6249  if (NTExpr->isIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext()))
6250  if (auto Constant = NTExpr->getIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext()))
6251  UpperBound =
6252  UpperBound
6253  ? Constant->getZExtValue()
6254  : std::min(UpperBound,
6255  static_cast<int32_t>(Constant->getZExtValue()));
6256  // If we haven't found a upper bound, remember we saw a thread limiting
6257  // clause.
6258  if (UpperBound == -1)
6259  UpperBound = 0;
6260  if (!E)
6261  return;
6262  CodeGenFunction::LexicalScope Scope(CGF, NTExpr->getSourceRange());
6263  if (const auto *PreInit =
6264  cast_or_null<DeclStmt>(NumThreadsClause->getPreInitStmt())) {
6265  for (const auto *I : PreInit->decls()) {
6266  if (!I->hasAttr<OMPCaptureNoInitAttr>()) {
6267  CGF.EmitVarDecl(cast<VarDecl>(*I));
6268  } else {
6269  CodeGenFunction::AutoVarEmission Emission =
6270  CGF.EmitAutoVarAlloca(cast<VarDecl>(*I));
6271  CGF.EmitAutoVarCleanups(Emission);
6272  }
6273  }
6274  }
6275  *E = NTExpr;
6276  }
6277  return;
6278  }
6279  if (isOpenMPSimdDirective(Dir->getDirectiveKind()))
6280  UpperBound = 1;
6281 }
6282 
6283 const Expr *CGOpenMPRuntime::getNumThreadsExprForTargetDirective(
6284  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D, int32_t &UpperBound,
6285  bool UpperBoundOnly, llvm::Value **CondVal, const Expr **ThreadLimitExpr) {
6286  assert((!CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice || UpperBoundOnly) &&
6287  "Clauses associated with the teams directive expected to be emitted "
6288  "only for the host!");
6289  OpenMPDirectiveKind DirectiveKind = D.getDirectiveKind();
6290  assert(isOpenMPTargetExecutionDirective(DirectiveKind) &&
6291  "Expected target-based executable directive.");
6292 
6293  const Expr *NT = nullptr;
6294  const Expr **NTPtr = UpperBoundOnly ? nullptr : &NT;
6295 
6296  auto CheckForConstExpr = [&](const Expr *E, const Expr **EPtr) {
6297  if (E->isIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext())) {
6298  if (auto Constant = E->getIntegerConstantExpr(CGF.getContext()))
6299  UpperBound = UpperBound ? Constant->getZExtValue()
6300  : std::min(UpperBound,
6301  int32_t(Constant->getZExtValue()));
6302  }
6303  // If we haven't found a upper bound, remember we saw a thread limiting
6304  // clause.
6305  if (UpperBound == -1)
6306  UpperBound = 0;
6307  if (EPtr)
6308  *EPtr = E;
6309  };
6310 
6311  auto ReturnSequential = [&]() {
6312  UpperBound = 1;
6313  return NT;
6314  };
6315 
6316  switch (DirectiveKind) {
6317  case OMPD_target: {
6318  const CapturedStmt *CS = D.getInnermostCapturedStmt();
6319  getNumThreads(CGF, CS, NTPtr, UpperBound, UpperBoundOnly, CondVal);
6320  const Stmt *Child = CGOpenMPRuntime::getSingleCompoundChild(
6321  CGF.getContext(), CS->getCapturedStmt());
6322  // TODO: The standard is not clear how to resolve two thread limit clauses,
6323  // let's pick the teams one if it's present, otherwise the target one.
6324  const auto *ThreadLimitClause = D.getSingleClause<OMPThreadLimitClause>();
6325  if (const auto *Dir = dyn_cast_or_null<OMPExecutableDirective>(Child)) {
6326  if (const auto *TLC = Dir->getSingleClause<OMPThreadLimitClause>()) {
6327  ThreadLimitClause = TLC;
6328  if (ThreadLimitExpr) {
6329  CGOpenMPInnerExprInfo CGInfo(CGF, *CS);
6330  CodeGenFunction::CGCapturedStmtRAII CapInfoRAII(CGF, &CGInfo);
6331  CodeGenFunction::LexicalScope Scope(
6332  CGF, ThreadLimitClause->getThreadLimit()->getSourceRange());
6333  if (const auto *PreInit =
6334  cast_or_null<DeclStmt>(ThreadLimitClause->getPreInitStmt())) {
6335  for (const auto *I : PreInit->decls()) {
6336  if (!I->hasAttr<OMPCaptureNoInitAttr>()) {
6337  CGF.EmitVarDecl(cast<VarDecl>(*I));
6338  } else {
6339  CodeGenFunction::AutoVarEmission Emission =
6340  CGF.EmitAutoVarAlloca(cast<VarDecl>(*I));
6341  CGF.EmitAutoVarCleanups(Emission);
6342  }
6343  }
6344  }
6345  }
6346  }
6347  }
6348  if (ThreadLimitClause)
6349  CheckForConstExpr(ThreadLimitClause->getThreadLimit(), ThreadLimitExpr);
6350  if (const auto *Dir = dyn_cast_or_null<OMPExecutableDirective>(Child)) {
6351  if (isOpenMPTeamsDirective(Dir->getDirectiveKind()) &&
6352  !isOpenMPDistributeDirective(Dir->getDirectiveKind())) {
6353  CS = Dir->getInnermostCapturedStmt();
6354  const Stmt *Child = CGOpenMPRuntime::getSingleCompoundChild(
6355  CGF.getContext(), CS->getCapturedStmt());
6356  Dir = dyn_cast_or_null<OMPExecutableDirective>(Child);
6357  }
6358  if (Dir && isOpenMPParallelDirective(Dir->getDirectiveKind())) {
6359  CS = Dir->getInnermostCapturedStmt();
6360  getNumThreads(CGF, CS, NTPtr, UpperBound, UpperBoundOnly, CondVal);
6361  } else if (Dir && isOpenMPSimdDirective(Dir->getDirectiveKind()))
6362  return ReturnSequential();
6363  }
6364  return NT;
6365  }
6366  case OMPD_target_teams: {
6367  if (D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPThreadLimitClause>()) {
6368  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope ThreadLimitScope(CGF);
6369  const auto *ThreadLimitClause = D.getSingleClause<OMPThreadLimitClause>();
6370  CheckForConstExpr(ThreadLimitClause->getThreadLimit(), ThreadLimitExpr);
6371  }
6372  const CapturedStmt *CS = D.getInnermostCapturedStmt();
6373  getNumThreads(CGF, CS, NTPtr, UpperBound, UpperBoundOnly, CondVal);
6374  const Stmt *Child = CGOpenMPRuntime::getSingleCompoundChild(
6375  CGF.getContext(), CS->getCapturedStmt());
6376  if (const auto *Dir = dyn_cast_or_null<OMPExecutableDirective>(Child)) {
6377  if (Dir->getDirectiveKind() == OMPD_distribute) {
6378  CS = Dir->getInnermostCapturedStmt();
6379  getNumThreads(CGF, CS, NTPtr, UpperBound, UpperBoundOnly, CondVal);
6380  }
6381  }
6382  return NT;
6383  }
6384  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute:
6385  if (D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPThreadLimitClause>()) {
6386  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope ThreadLimitScope(CGF);
6387  const auto *ThreadLimitClause = D.getSingleClause<OMPThreadLimitClause>();
6388  CheckForConstExpr(ThreadLimitClause->getThreadLimit(), ThreadLimitExpr);
6389  }
6390  getNumThreads(CGF, D.getInnermostCapturedStmt(), NTPtr, UpperBound,
6391  UpperBoundOnly, CondVal);
6392  return NT;
6393  case OMPD_target_teams_loop:
6394  case OMPD_target_parallel_loop:
6395  case OMPD_target_parallel:
6396  case OMPD_target_parallel_for:
6397  case OMPD_target_parallel_for_simd:
6398  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
6399  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd: {
6400  if (CondVal && D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPIfClause>()) {
6401  const OMPIfClause *IfClause = nullptr;
6402  for (const auto *C : D.getClausesOfKind<OMPIfClause>()) {
6403  if (C->getNameModifier() == OMPD_unknown ||
6404  C->getNameModifier() == OMPD_parallel) {
6405  IfClause = C;
6406  break;
6407  }
6408  }
6409  if (IfClause) {
6410  const Expr *Cond = IfClause->getCondition();
6411  bool Result;
6412  if (Cond->EvaluateAsBooleanCondition(Result, CGF.getContext())) {
6413  if (!Result)
6414  return ReturnSequential();
6415  } else {
6416  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope Scope(CGF);
6417  *CondVal = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(Cond);
6418  }
6419  }
6420  }
6421  if (D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPThreadLimitClause>()) {
6422  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope ThreadLimitScope(CGF);
6423  const auto *ThreadLimitClause = D.getSingleClause<OMPThreadLimitClause>();
6424  CheckForConstExpr(ThreadLimitClause->getThreadLimit(), ThreadLimitExpr);
6425  }
6426  if (D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPNumThreadsClause>()) {
6427  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope NumThreadsScope(CGF);
6428  const auto *NumThreadsClause = D.getSingleClause<OMPNumThreadsClause>();
6429  CheckForConstExpr(NumThreadsClause->getNumThreads(), nullptr);
6430  return NumThreadsClause->getNumThreads();
6431  }
6432  return NT;
6433  }
6434  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_simd:
6435  case OMPD_target_simd:
6436  return ReturnSequential();
6437  default:
6438  break;
6439  }
6440  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported directive kind.");
6441 }
6442 
6443 llvm::Value *CGOpenMPRuntime::emitNumThreadsForTargetDirective(
6444  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D) {
6445  llvm::Value *NumThreadsVal = nullptr;
6446  llvm::Value *CondVal = nullptr;
6447  llvm::Value *ThreadLimitVal = nullptr;
6448  const Expr *ThreadLimitExpr = nullptr;
6449  int32_t UpperBound = -1;
6450 
6451  const Expr *NT = getNumThreadsExprForTargetDirective(
6452  CGF, D, UpperBound, /* UpperBoundOnly */ false, &CondVal,
6453  &ThreadLimitExpr);
6454 
6455  // Thread limit expressions are used below, emit them.
6456  if (ThreadLimitExpr) {
6457  ThreadLimitVal =
6458  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(ThreadLimitExpr, /*IgnoreResultAssign=*/true);
6459  ThreadLimitVal = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(ThreadLimitVal, CGF.Int32Ty,
6460  /*isSigned=*/false);
6461  }
6462 
6463  // Generate the num teams expression.
6464  if (UpperBound == 1) {
6465  NumThreadsVal = CGF.Builder.getInt32(UpperBound);
6466  } else if (NT) {
6467  NumThreadsVal = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(NT, /*IgnoreResultAssign=*/true);
6468  NumThreadsVal = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(NumThreadsVal, CGF.Int32Ty,
6469  /*isSigned=*/false);
6470  } else if (ThreadLimitVal) {
6471  // If we do not have a num threads value but a thread limit, replace the
6472  // former with the latter. We know handled the thread limit expression.
6473  NumThreadsVal = ThreadLimitVal;
6474  ThreadLimitVal = nullptr;
6475  } else {
6476  // Default to "0" which means runtime choice.
6477  assert(!ThreadLimitVal && "Default not applicable with thread limit value");
6478  NumThreadsVal = CGF.Builder.getInt32(0);
6479  }
6480 
6481  // Handle if clause. If if clause present, the number of threads is
6482  // calculated as <cond> ? (<numthreads> ? <numthreads> : 0 ) : 1.
6483  if (CondVal) {
6484  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope Scope(CGF);
6485  NumThreadsVal = CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(CondVal, NumThreadsVal,
6486  CGF.Builder.getInt32(1));
6487  }
6488 
6489  // If the thread limit and num teams expression were present, take the
6490  // minimum.
6491  if (ThreadLimitVal) {
6492  NumThreadsVal = CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(
6493  CGF.Builder.CreateICmpULT(ThreadLimitVal, NumThreadsVal),
6494  ThreadLimitVal, NumThreadsVal);
6495  }
6496 
6497  return NumThreadsVal;
6498 }

6503 // Utility to handle information from clauses associated with a given
6504 // construct that use mappable expressions (e.g. 'map' clause, 'to' clause).

6509  /// Get the offset of the OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF field.
6510  static unsigned getFlagMemberOffset() {
6511  unsigned Offset = 0;
6512  for (uint64_t Remain =
6513  static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
6514  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF);
6515  !(Remain & 1); Remain = Remain >> 1)
6516  Offset++;
6517  return Offset;
6518  }

6653  llvm::Value *getExprTypeSize(const Expr *E) const {
6654  QualType ExprTy = E->getType().getCanonicalType();
6655 
6656  // Calculate the size for array shaping expression.
6657  if (const auto *OAE = dyn_cast<OMPArrayShapingExpr>(E)) {
6658  llvm::Value *Size =
6659  CGF.getTypeSize(OAE->getBase()->getType()->getPointeeType());
6660  for (const Expr *SE : OAE->getDimensions()) {
6661  llvm::Value *Sz = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(SE);
6662  Sz = CGF.EmitScalarConversion(Sz, SE->getType(),
6663  CGF.getContext().getSizeType(),
6664  SE->getExprLoc());
6665  Size = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(Size, Sz);
6666  }
6667  return Size;
6668  }
6669 
6670  // Reference types are ignored for mapping purposes.
6671  if (const auto *RefTy = ExprTy->getAs<ReferenceType>())
6672  ExprTy = RefTy->getPointeeType().getCanonicalType();
6673 
6674  // Given that an array section is considered a built-in type, we need to
6675  // do the calculation based on the length of the section instead of relying
6676  // on CGF.getTypeSize(E->getType()).
6677  if (const auto *OAE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(E)) {
6678  QualType BaseTy = OMPArraySectionExpr::getBaseOriginalType(
6679  OAE->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts())
6680  .getCanonicalType();
6681 
6682  // If there is no length associated with the expression and lower bound is
6683  // not specified too, that means we are using the whole length of the
6684  // base.
6685  if (!OAE->getLength() && OAE->getColonLocFirst().isValid() &&
6686  !OAE->getLowerBound())
6687  return CGF.getTypeSize(BaseTy);
6688 
6689  llvm::Value *ElemSize;
6690  if (const auto *PTy = BaseTy->getAs<PointerType>()) {
6691  ElemSize = CGF.getTypeSize(PTy->getPointeeType().getCanonicalType());
6692  } else {
6693  const auto *ATy = cast<ArrayType>(BaseTy.getTypePtr());
6694  assert(ATy && "Expecting array type if not a pointer type.");
6695  ElemSize = CGF.getTypeSize(ATy->getElementType().getCanonicalType());
6696  }
6697 
6698  // If we don't have a length at this point, that is because we have an
6699  // array section with a single element.
6700  if (!OAE->getLength() && OAE->getColonLocFirst().isInvalid())
6701  return ElemSize;
6702 
6703  if (const Expr *LenExpr = OAE->getLength()) {
6704  llvm::Value *LengthVal = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(LenExpr);
6705  LengthVal = CGF.EmitScalarConversion(LengthVal, LenExpr->getType(),
6706  CGF.getContext().getSizeType(),
6707  LenExpr->getExprLoc());
6708  return CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(LengthVal, ElemSize);
6709  }
6710  assert(!OAE->getLength() && OAE->getColonLocFirst().isValid() &&
6711  OAE->getLowerBound() && "expected array_section[lb:].");
6712  // Size = sizetype - lb * elemtype;
6713  llvm::Value *LengthVal = CGF.getTypeSize(BaseTy);
6714  llvm::Value *LBVal = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(OAE->getLowerBound());
6715  LBVal = CGF.EmitScalarConversion(LBVal, OAE->getLowerBound()->getType(),
6716  CGF.getContext().getSizeType(),
6717  OAE->getLowerBound()->getExprLoc());
6718  LBVal = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(LBVal, ElemSize);
6719  llvm::Value *Cmp = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpUGT(LengthVal, LBVal);
6720  llvm::Value *TrueVal = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWSub(LengthVal, LBVal);
6721  LengthVal = CGF.Builder.CreateSelect(
6722  Cmp, TrueVal, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, 0));
6723  return LengthVal;
6724  }
6725  return CGF.getTypeSize(ExprTy);
6726  }
6727 
6728  /// Return the corresponding bits for a given map clause modifier. Add
6729  /// a flag marking the map as a pointer if requested. Add a flag marking the
6730  /// map as the first one of a series of maps that relate to the same map
6731  /// expression.
6732  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags getMapTypeBits(
6733  OpenMPMapClauseKind MapType, ArrayRef<OpenMPMapModifierKind> MapModifiers,
6734  ArrayRef<OpenMPMotionModifierKind> MotionModifiers, bool IsImplicit,
6735  bool AddPtrFlag, bool AddIsTargetParamFlag, bool IsNonContiguous) const {
6736  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags Bits =
6737  IsImplicit ? OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_IMPLICIT
6738  : OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_NONE;
6739  switch (MapType) {
6740  case OMPC_MAP_alloc:
6741  case OMPC_MAP_release:
6742  // alloc and release is the default behavior in the runtime library, i.e.
6743  // if we don't pass any bits alloc/release that is what the runtime is
6744  // going to do. Therefore, we don't need to signal anything for these two
6745  // type modifiers.
6746  break;
6747  case OMPC_MAP_to:
6748  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO;
6749  break;
6750  case OMPC_MAP_from:
6751  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM;
6752  break;
6753  case OMPC_MAP_tofrom:
6754  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO |
6755  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM;
6756  break;
6757  case OMPC_MAP_delete:
6758  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_DELETE;
6759  break;
6760  case OMPC_MAP_unknown:
6761  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected map type!");
6762  }
6763  if (AddPtrFlag)
6764  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PTR_AND_OBJ;
6765  if (AddIsTargetParamFlag)
6766  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TARGET_PARAM;
6767  if (llvm::is_contained(MapModifiers, OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_always))
6768  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_ALWAYS;
6769  if (llvm::is_contained(MapModifiers, OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_close))
6770  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_CLOSE;
6771  if (llvm::is_contained(MapModifiers, OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_present) ||
6772  llvm::is_contained(MotionModifiers, OMPC_MOTION_MODIFIER_present))
6773  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PRESENT;
6774  if (llvm::is_contained(MapModifiers, OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_ompx_hold))
6775  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_OMPX_HOLD;
6776  if (IsNonContiguous)
6777  Bits |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_NON_CONTIG;
6778  return Bits;
6779  }
6780 
6781  /// Return true if the provided expression is a final array section. A
6782  /// final array section, is one whose length can't be proved to be one.
6783  bool isFinalArraySectionExpression(const Expr *E) const {
6784  const auto *OASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(E);
6785 
6786  // It is not an array section and therefore not a unity-size one.
6787  if (!OASE)
6788  return false;
6789 
6790  // An array section with no colon always refer to a single element.
6791  if (OASE->getColonLocFirst().isInvalid())
6792  return false;
6793 
6794  const Expr *Length = OASE->getLength();
6795 
6796  // If we don't have a length we have to check if the array has size 1
6797  // for this dimension. Also, we should always expect a length if the
6798  // base type is pointer.
6799  if (!Length) {
6800  QualType BaseQTy = OMPArraySectionExpr::getBaseOriginalType(
6801  OASE->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts())
6802  .getCanonicalType();
6803  if (const auto *ATy = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(BaseQTy.getTypePtr()))
6804  return ATy->getSExtSize() != 1;
6805  // If we don't have a constant dimension length, we have to consider
6806  // the current section as having any size, so it is not necessarily
6807  // unitary. If it happen to be unity size, that's user fault.
6808  return true;
6809  }
6810 
6811  // Check if the length evaluates to 1.
6812  Expr::EvalResult Result;
6813  if (!Length->EvaluateAsInt(Result, CGF.getContext()))
6814  return true; // Can have more that size 1.
6815 
6816  llvm::APSInt ConstLength = Result.Val.getInt();
6817  return ConstLength.getSExtValue() != 1;
6818  }
6819 
6820  /// Generate the base pointers, section pointers, sizes, map type bits, and
6821  /// user-defined mappers (all included in \a CombinedInfo) for the provided
6822  /// map type, map or motion modifiers, and expression components.
6823  /// \a IsFirstComponent should be set to true if the provided set of
6824  /// components is the first associated with a capture.
6825  void generateInfoForComponentList(
6826  OpenMPMapClauseKind MapType, ArrayRef<OpenMPMapModifierKind> MapModifiers,
6827  ArrayRef<OpenMPMotionModifierKind> MotionModifiers,
6828  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef Components,
6829  MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo,
6830  MapCombinedInfoTy &StructBaseCombinedInfo,
6831  StructRangeInfoTy &PartialStruct, bool IsFirstComponentList,
6832  bool IsImplicit, bool GenerateAllInfoForClauses,
6833  const ValueDecl *Mapper = nullptr, bool ForDeviceAddr = false,
6834  const ValueDecl *BaseDecl = nullptr, const Expr *MapExpr = nullptr,
6835  ArrayRef<OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef>
6836  OverlappedElements = std::nullopt) const {
6837  // The following summarizes what has to be generated for each map and the
6838  // types below. The generated information is expressed in this order:
6839  // base pointer, section pointer, size, flags
6840  // (to add to the ones that come from the map type and modifier).
6841  //
6842  // double d;
6843  // int i[100];
6844  // float *p;
6845  // int **a = &i;
6846  //
6847  // struct S1 {
6848  // int i;
6849  // float f[50];
6850  // }
6851  // struct S2 {
6852  // int i;
6853  // float f[50];
6854  // S1 s;
6855  // double *p;
6856  // struct S2 *ps;
6857  // int &ref;
6858  // }
6859  // S2 s;
6860  // S2 *ps;
6861  //
6862  // map(d)
6863  // &d, &d, sizeof(double), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6864  //
6865  // map(i)
6866  // &i, &i, 100*sizeof(int), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6867  //
6868  // map(i[1:23])
6869  // &i(=&i[0]), &i[1], 23*sizeof(int), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6870  //
6871  // map(p)
6872  // &p, &p, sizeof(float*), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6873  //
6874  // map(p[1:24])
6875  // &p, &p[1], 24*sizeof(float), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM | PTR_AND_OBJ
6876  // in unified shared memory mode or for local pointers
6877  // p, &p[1], 24*sizeof(float), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6878  //
6879  // map((*a)[0:3])
6880  // &(*a), &(*a), sizeof(pointer), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6881  // &(*a), &(*a)[0], 3*sizeof(int), PTR_AND_OBJ | TO | FROM
6882  //
6883  // map(**a)
6884  // &(*a), &(*a), sizeof(pointer), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6885  // &(*a), &(**a), sizeof(int), PTR_AND_OBJ | TO | FROM
6886  //
6887  // map(s)
6888  // &s, &s, sizeof(S2), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6889  //
6890  // map(s.i)
6891  // &s, &(s.i), sizeof(int), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6892  //
6893  // map(s.s.f)
6894  // &s, &(s.s.f[0]), 50*sizeof(float), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6895  //
6896  // map(s.p)
6897  // &s, &(s.p), sizeof(double*), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6898  //
6899  // map(to: s.p[:22])
6900  // &s, &(s.p), sizeof(double*), TARGET_PARAM (*)
6901  // &s, &(s.p), sizeof(double*), MEMBER_OF(1) (**)
6902  // &(s.p), &(s.p[0]), 22*sizeof(double),
6903  // MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ | TO (***)
6904  // (*) alloc space for struct members, only this is a target parameter
6905  // (**) map the pointer (nothing to be mapped in this example) (the compiler
6906  // optimizes this entry out, same in the examples below)
6907  // (***) map the pointee (map: to)
6908  //
6909  // map(to: s.ref)
6910  // &s, &(s.ref), sizeof(int*), TARGET_PARAM (*)
6911  // &s, &(s.ref), sizeof(int), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ | TO (***)
6912  // (*) alloc space for struct members, only this is a target parameter
6913  // (**) map the pointer (nothing to be mapped in this example) (the compiler
6914  // optimizes this entry out, same in the examples below)
6915  // (***) map the pointee (map: to)
6916  //
6917  // map(s.ps)
6918  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6919  //
6920  // map(from: s.ps->s.i)
6921  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6922  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6923  // &(s.ps), &(s.ps->s.i), sizeof(int), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ | FROM
6924  //
6925  // map(to: s.ps->ps)
6926  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6927  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6928  // &(s.ps), &(s.ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ | TO
6929  //
6930  // map(s.ps->ps->ps)
6931  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6932  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6933  // &(s.ps), &(s.ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ
6934  // &(s.ps->ps), &(s.ps->ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), PTR_AND_OBJ | TO | FROM
6935  //
6936  // map(to: s.ps->ps->s.f[:22])
6937  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6938  // &s, &(s.ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6939  // &(s.ps), &(s.ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ
6940  // &(s.ps->ps), &(s.ps->ps->s.f[0]), 22*sizeof(float), PTR_AND_OBJ | TO
6941  //
6942  // map(ps)
6943  // &ps, &ps, sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6944  //
6945  // map(ps->i)
6946  // ps, &(ps->i), sizeof(int), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6947  //
6948  // map(ps->s.f)
6949  // ps, &(ps->s.f[0]), 50*sizeof(float), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6950  //
6951  // map(from: ps->p)
6952  // ps, &(ps->p), sizeof(double*), TARGET_PARAM | FROM
6953  //
6954  // map(to: ps->p[:22])
6955  // ps, &(ps->p), sizeof(double*), TARGET_PARAM
6956  // ps, &(ps->p), sizeof(double*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6957  // &(ps->p), &(ps->p[0]), 22*sizeof(double), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ | TO
6958  //
6959  // map(ps->ps)
6960  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM | TO | FROM
6961  //
6962  // map(from: ps->ps->s.i)
6963  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6964  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6965  // &(ps->ps), &(ps->ps->s.i), sizeof(int), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ | FROM
6966  //
6967  // map(from: ps->ps->ps)
6968  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6969  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6970  // &(ps->ps), &(ps->ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ | FROM
6971  //
6972  // map(ps->ps->ps->ps)
6973  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6974  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6975  // &(ps->ps), &(ps->ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ
6976  // &(ps->ps->ps), &(ps->ps->ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), PTR_AND_OBJ | TO | FROM
6977  //
6978  // map(to: ps->ps->ps->s.f[:22])
6979  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6980  // ps, &(ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6981  // &(ps->ps), &(ps->ps->ps), sizeof(S2*), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ
6982  // &(ps->ps->ps), &(ps->ps->ps->s.f[0]), 22*sizeof(float), PTR_AND_OBJ | TO
6983  //
6984  // map(to: s.f[:22]) map(from: s.p[:33])
6985  // &s, &(s.f[0]), 50*sizeof(float) + sizeof(struct S1) +
6986  // sizeof(double*) (**), TARGET_PARAM
6987  // &s, &(s.f[0]), 22*sizeof(float), MEMBER_OF(1) | TO
6988  // &s, &(s.p), sizeof(double*), MEMBER_OF(1)
6989  // &(s.p), &(s.p[0]), 33*sizeof(double), MEMBER_OF(1) | PTR_AND_OBJ | FROM
6990  // (*) allocate contiguous space needed to fit all mapped members even if
6991  // we allocate space for members not mapped (in this example,
6992  // s.f[22..49] and s.s are not mapped, yet we must allocate space for
6993  // them as well because they fall between &s.f[0] and &s.p)
6994  //
6995  // map(from: s.f[:22]) map(to: ps->p[:33])
6996  // &s, &(s.f[0]), 22*sizeof(float), TARGET_PARAM | FROM
6997  // ps, &(ps->p), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
6998  // ps, &(ps->p), sizeof(double*), MEMBER_OF(2) (*)
6999  // &(ps->p), &(ps->p[0]), 33*sizeof(double), MEMBER_OF(2) | PTR_AND_OBJ | TO
7000  // (*) the struct this entry pertains to is the 2nd element in the list of
7001  // arguments, hence MEMBER_OF(2)
7002  //
7003  // map(from: s.f[:22], s.s) map(to: ps->p[:33])
7004  // &s, &(s.f[0]), 50*sizeof(float) + sizeof(struct S1), TARGET_PARAM
7005  // &s, &(s.f[0]), 22*sizeof(float), MEMBER_OF(1) | FROM
7006  // &s, &(s.s), sizeof(struct S1), MEMBER_OF(1) | FROM
7007  // ps, &(ps->p), sizeof(S2*), TARGET_PARAM
7008  // ps, &(ps->p), sizeof(double*), MEMBER_OF(4) (*)
7009  // &(ps->p), &(ps->p[0]), 33*sizeof(double), MEMBER_OF(4) | PTR_AND_OBJ | TO
7010  // (*) the struct this entry pertains to is the 4th element in the list
7011  // of arguments, hence MEMBER_OF(4)
7012 
7013  // Track if the map information being generated is the first for a capture.
7014  bool IsCaptureFirstInfo = IsFirstComponentList;
7015  // When the variable is on a declare target link or in a to clause with
7016  // unified memory, a reference is needed to hold the host/device address
7017  // of the variable.
7018  bool RequiresReference = false;
7019 
7020  // Scan the components from the base to the complete expression.
7021  auto CI = Components.rbegin();
7022  auto CE = Components.rend();
7023  auto I = CI;
7024 
7025  // Track if the map information being generated is the first for a list of
7026  // components.
7027  bool IsExpressionFirstInfo = true;
7028  bool FirstPointerInComplexData = false;
7029  Address BP = Address::invalid();
7030  const Expr *AssocExpr = I->getAssociatedExpression();
7031  const auto *AE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(AssocExpr);
7032  const auto *OASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(AssocExpr);
7033  const auto *OAShE = dyn_cast<OMPArrayShapingExpr>(AssocExpr);
7034 
7035  if (isa<MemberExpr>(AssocExpr)) {
7036  // The base is the 'this' pointer. The content of the pointer is going
7037  // to be the base of the field being mapped.
7038  BP = CGF.LoadCXXThisAddress();
7039  } else if ((AE && isa<CXXThisExpr>(AE->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) ||
7040  (OASE &&
7041  isa<CXXThisExpr>(OASE->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))) {
7042  BP = CGF.EmitOMPSharedLValue(AssocExpr).getAddress(CGF);
7043  } else if (OAShE &&
7044  isa<CXXThisExpr>(OAShE->getBase()->IgnoreParenCasts())) {
7045  BP = Address(
7046  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(OAShE->getBase()),
7047  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(OAShE->getBase()->getType()->getPointeeType()),
7048  CGF.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(OAShE->getBase()->getType()));
7049  } else {
7050  // The base is the reference to the variable.
7051  // BP = &Var.
7052  BP = CGF.EmitOMPSharedLValue(AssocExpr).getAddress(CGF);
7053  if (const auto *VD =
7054  dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(I->getAssociatedDeclaration())) {
7055  if (std::optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MapTypeTy> Res =
7056  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD)) {
7057  if ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link) ||
7058  ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To ||
7059  *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Enter) &&
7060  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory())) {
7061  RequiresReference = true;
7062  BP = CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfDeclareTargetVar(VD);
7063  }
7064  }
7065  }
7066 
7067  // If the variable is a pointer and is being dereferenced (i.e. is not
7068  // the last component), the base has to be the pointer itself, not its
7069  // reference. References are ignored for mapping purposes.
7070  QualType Ty =
7071  I->getAssociatedDeclaration()->getType().getNonReferenceType();
7072  if (Ty->isAnyPointerType() && std::next(I) != CE) {
7073  // No need to generate individual map information for the pointer, it
7074  // can be associated with the combined storage if shared memory mode is
7075  // active or the base declaration is not global variable.
7076  const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(I->getAssociatedDeclaration());
7077  if (CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory() ||
7078  !VD || VD->hasLocalStorage())
7079  BP = CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(BP, Ty->castAs<PointerType>());
7080  else
7081  FirstPointerInComplexData = true;
7082  ++I;
7083  }
7084  }
7085 
7086  // Track whether a component of the list should be marked as MEMBER_OF some
7087  // combined entry (for partial structs). Only the first PTR_AND_OBJ entry
7088  // in a component list should be marked as MEMBER_OF, all subsequent entries
7089  // do not belong to the base struct. E.g.
7090  // struct S2 s;
7091  // s.ps->ps->ps->f[:]
7092  // (1) (2) (3) (4)
7093  // ps(1) is a member pointer, ps(2) is a pointee of ps(1), so it is a
7094  // PTR_AND_OBJ entry; the PTR is ps(1), so MEMBER_OF the base struct. ps(3)
7095  // is the pointee of ps(2) which is not member of struct s, so it should not
7096  // be marked as such (it is still PTR_AND_OBJ).
7097  // The variable is initialized to false so that PTR_AND_OBJ entries which
7098  // are not struct members are not considered (e.g. array of pointers to
7099  // data).
7100  bool ShouldBeMemberOf = false;
7101 
7102  // Variable keeping track of whether or not we have encountered a component
7103  // in the component list which is a member expression. Useful when we have a
7104  // pointer or a final array section, in which case it is the previous
7105  // component in the list which tells us whether we have a member expression.
7106  // E.g. X.f[:]
7107  // While processing the final array section "[:]" it is "f" which tells us
7108  // whether we are dealing with a member of a declared struct.
7109  const MemberExpr *EncounteredME = nullptr;
7110 
7111  // Track for the total number of dimension. Start from one for the dummy
7112  // dimension.
7113  uint64_t DimSize = 1;
7114 
7115  bool IsNonContiguous = CombinedInfo.NonContigInfo.IsNonContiguous;
7116  bool IsPrevMemberReference = false;
7117 
7118  // We need to check if we will be encountering any MEs. If we do not
7119  // encounter any ME expression it means we will be mapping the whole struct.
7120  // In that case we need to skip adding an entry for the struct to the
7121  // CombinedInfo list and instead add an entry to the StructBaseCombinedInfo
7122  // list only when generating all info for clauses.
7123  bool IsMappingWholeStruct = true;
7124  if (!GenerateAllInfoForClauses) {
7125  IsMappingWholeStruct = false;
7126  } else {
7127  for (auto TempI = I; TempI != CE; ++TempI) {
7128  const MemberExpr *PossibleME =
7129  dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(TempI->getAssociatedExpression());
7130  if (PossibleME) {
7131  IsMappingWholeStruct = false;
7132  break;
7133  }
7134  }
7135  }
7136 
7137  for (; I != CE; ++I) {
7138  // If the current component is member of a struct (parent struct) mark it.
7139  if (!EncounteredME) {
7140  EncounteredME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(I->getAssociatedExpression());
7141  // If we encounter a PTR_AND_OBJ entry from now on it should be marked
7142  // as MEMBER_OF the parent struct.
7143  if (EncounteredME) {
7144  ShouldBeMemberOf = true;
7145  // Do not emit as complex pointer if this is actually not array-like
7146  // expression.
7147  if (FirstPointerInComplexData) {
7148  QualType Ty = std::prev(I)
7149  ->getAssociatedDeclaration()
7150  ->getType()
7151  .getNonReferenceType();
7152  BP = CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(BP, Ty->castAs<PointerType>());
7153  FirstPointerInComplexData = false;
7154  }
7155  }
7156  }
7157 
7158  auto Next = std::next(I);
7159 
7160  // We need to generate the addresses and sizes if this is the last
7161  // component, if the component is a pointer or if it is an array section
7162  // whose length can't be proved to be one. If this is a pointer, it
7163  // becomes the base address for the following components.
7164 
7165  // A final array section, is one whose length can't be proved to be one.
7166  // If the map item is non-contiguous then we don't treat any array section
7167  // as final array section.
7168  bool IsFinalArraySection =
7169  !IsNonContiguous &&
7170  isFinalArraySectionExpression(I->getAssociatedExpression());
7171 
7172  // If we have a declaration for the mapping use that, otherwise use
7173  // the base declaration of the map clause.
7174  const ValueDecl *MapDecl = (I->getAssociatedDeclaration())
7175  ? I->getAssociatedDeclaration()
7176  : BaseDecl;
7177  MapExpr = (I->getAssociatedExpression()) ? I->getAssociatedExpression()
7178  : MapExpr;
7179 
7180  // Get information on whether the element is a pointer. Have to do a
7181  // special treatment for array sections given that they are built-in
7182  // types.
7183  const auto *OASE =
7184  dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(I->getAssociatedExpression());
7185  const auto *OAShE =
7186  dyn_cast<OMPArrayShapingExpr>(I->getAssociatedExpression());
7187  const auto *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(I->getAssociatedExpression());
7188  const auto *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(I->getAssociatedExpression());
7189  bool IsPointer =
7190  OAShE ||
7191  (OASE && OMPArraySectionExpr::getBaseOriginalType(OASE)
7192  .getCanonicalType()
7193  ->isAnyPointerType()) ||
7194  I->getAssociatedExpression()->getType()->isAnyPointerType();
7195  bool IsMemberReference = isa<MemberExpr>(I->getAssociatedExpression()) &&
7196  MapDecl &&
7197  MapDecl->getType()->isLValueReferenceType();
7198  bool IsNonDerefPointer = IsPointer &&
7199  !(UO && UO->getOpcode() != UO_Deref) && !BO &&
7200  !IsNonContiguous;
7201 
7202  if (OASE)
7203  ++DimSize;
7204 
7205  if (Next == CE || IsMemberReference || IsNonDerefPointer ||
7206  IsFinalArraySection) {
7207  // If this is not the last component, we expect the pointer to be
7208  // associated with an array expression or member expression.
7209  assert((Next == CE ||
7210  isa<MemberExpr>(Next->getAssociatedExpression()) ||
7211  isa<ArraySubscriptExpr>(Next->getAssociatedExpression()) ||
7212  isa<OMPArraySectionExpr>(Next->getAssociatedExpression()) ||
7213  isa<OMPArrayShapingExpr>(Next->getAssociatedExpression()) ||
7214  isa<UnaryOperator>(Next->getAssociatedExpression()) ||
7215  isa<BinaryOperator>(Next->getAssociatedExpression())) &&
7216  "Unexpected expression");
7217 
7218  Address LB = Address::invalid();
7219  Address LowestElem = Address::invalid();
7220  auto &&EmitMemberExprBase = [](CodeGenFunction &CGF,
7221  const MemberExpr *E) {
7222  const Expr *BaseExpr = E->getBase();
7223  // If this is s.x, emit s as an lvalue. If it is s->x, emit s as a
7224  // scalar.
7225  LValue BaseLV;
7226  if (E->isArrow()) {
7227  LValueBaseInfo BaseInfo;
7228  TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo;
7229  Address Addr =
7230  CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(BaseExpr, &BaseInfo, &TBAAInfo);
7231  QualType PtrTy = BaseExpr->getType()->getPointeeType();
7232  BaseLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, PtrTy, BaseInfo, TBAAInfo);
7233  } else {
7234  BaseLV = CGF.EmitOMPSharedLValue(BaseExpr);
7235  }
7236  return BaseLV;
7237  };
7238  if (OAShE) {
7239  LowestElem = LB =
7240  Address(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(OAShE->getBase()),
7241  CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(
7242  OAShE->getBase()->getType()->getPointeeType()),
7243  CGF.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(
7244  OAShE->getBase()->getType()));
7245  } else if (IsMemberReference) {
7246  const auto *ME = cast<MemberExpr>(I->getAssociatedExpression());
7247  LValue BaseLVal = EmitMemberExprBase(CGF, ME);
7248  LowestElem = CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(
7249  BaseLVal, cast<FieldDecl>(MapDecl))
7250  .getAddress(CGF);
7251  LB = CGF.EmitLoadOfReferenceLValue(LowestElem, MapDecl->getType())
7252  .getAddress(CGF);
7253  } else {
7254  LowestElem = LB =
7255  CGF.EmitOMPSharedLValue(I->getAssociatedExpression())
7256  .getAddress(CGF);
7257  }
7258 
7259  // If this component is a pointer inside the base struct then we don't
7260  // need to create any entry for it - it will be combined with the object
7261  // it is pointing to into a single PTR_AND_OBJ entry.
7262  bool IsMemberPointerOrAddr =
7263  EncounteredME &&
7264  (((IsPointer || ForDeviceAddr) &&
7265  I->getAssociatedExpression() == EncounteredME) ||
7266  (IsPrevMemberReference && !IsPointer) ||
7267  (IsMemberReference && Next != CE &&
7268  !Next->getAssociatedExpression()->getType()->isPointerType()));
7269  if (!OverlappedElements.empty() && Next == CE) {
7270  // Handle base element with the info for overlapped elements.
7271  assert(!PartialStruct.Base.isValid() && "The base element is set.");
7272  assert(!IsPointer &&
7273  "Unexpected base element with the pointer type.");
7274  // Mark the whole struct as the struct that requires allocation on the
7275  // device.
7276  PartialStruct.LowestElem = {0, LowestElem};
7277  CharUnits TypeSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(
7278  I->getAssociatedExpression()->getType());
7279  Address HB = CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP(
7280  CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
7281  LowestElem, CGF.VoidPtrTy, CGF.Int8Ty),
7282  TypeSize.getQuantity() - 1);
7283  PartialStruct.HighestElem = {
7284  std::numeric_limits<decltype(
7285  PartialStruct.HighestElem.first)>::max(),
7286  HB};
7287  PartialStruct.Base = BP;
7288  PartialStruct.LB = LB;
7289  assert(
7290  PartialStruct.PreliminaryMapData.BasePointers.empty() &&
7291  "Overlapped elements must be used only once for the variable.");
7292  std::swap(PartialStruct.PreliminaryMapData, CombinedInfo);
7293  // Emit data for non-overlapped data.
7294  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags Flags =
7295  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF |
7296  getMapTypeBits(MapType, MapModifiers, MotionModifiers, IsImplicit,
7297  /*AddPtrFlag=*/false,
7298  /*AddIsTargetParamFlag=*/false, IsNonContiguous);
7299  llvm::Value *Size = nullptr;
7300  // Do bitcopy of all non-overlapped structure elements.
7301  for (OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef
7302  Component : OverlappedElements) {
7303  Address ComponentLB = Address::invalid();
7304  for (const OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableComponent &MC :
7305  Component) {
7306  if (const ValueDecl *VD = MC.getAssociatedDeclaration()) {
7307  const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(VD);
7308  if (FD && FD->getType()->isLValueReferenceType()) {
7309  const auto *ME =
7310  cast<MemberExpr>(MC.getAssociatedExpression());
7311  LValue BaseLVal = EmitMemberExprBase(CGF, ME);
7312  ComponentLB =
7313  CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(BaseLVal, FD)
7314  .getAddress(CGF);
7315  } else {
7316  ComponentLB =
7317  CGF.EmitOMPSharedLValue(MC.getAssociatedExpression())
7318  .getAddress(CGF);
7319  }
7320  llvm::Value *ComponentLBPtr = ComponentLB.emitRawPointer(CGF);
7321  llvm::Value *LBPtr = LB.emitRawPointer(CGF);
7322  Size = CGF.Builder.CreatePtrDiff(CGF.Int8Ty, ComponentLBPtr,
7323  LBPtr);
7324  break;
7325  }
7326  }
7327  assert(Size && "Failed to determine structure size");
7328  CombinedInfo.Exprs.emplace_back(MapDecl, MapExpr);
7329  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(BP.emitRawPointer(CGF));
7330  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
7331  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
7332  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(LB.emitRawPointer(CGF));
7333  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
7334  Size, CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
7335  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(Flags);
7336  CombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
7337  CombinedInfo.NonContigInfo.Dims.push_back(IsNonContiguous ? DimSize
7338  : 1);
7339  LB = CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP(ComponentLB, 1);
7340  }
7341  CombinedInfo.Exprs.emplace_back(MapDecl, MapExpr);
7342  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(BP.emitRawPointer(CGF));
7343  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
7344  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
7345  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(LB.emitRawPointer(CGF));
7346  llvm::Value *LBPtr = LB.emitRawPointer(CGF);
7347  Size = CGF.Builder.CreatePtrDiff(
7348  CGF.Int8Ty, CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP(HB, 1).emitRawPointer(CGF),
7349  LBPtr);
7350  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(
7351  CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(Size, CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
7352  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(Flags);
7353  CombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
7354  CombinedInfo.NonContigInfo.Dims.push_back(IsNonContiguous ? DimSize
7355  : 1);
7356  break;
7357  }
7358  llvm::Value *Size = getExprTypeSize(I->getAssociatedExpression());
7359  // Skip adding an entry in the CurInfo of this combined entry if the
7360  // whole struct is currently being mapped. The struct needs to be added
7361  // in the first position before any data internal to the struct is being
7362  // mapped.
7363  if (!IsMemberPointerOrAddr ||
7364  (Next == CE && MapType != OMPC_MAP_unknown)) {
7365  if (!IsMappingWholeStruct) {
7366  CombinedInfo.Exprs.emplace_back(MapDecl, MapExpr);
7367  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(BP.emitRawPointer(CGF));
7368  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
7369  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
7370  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(LB.emitRawPointer(CGF));
7371  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
7372  Size, CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
7373  CombinedInfo.NonContigInfo.Dims.push_back(IsNonContiguous ? DimSize
7374  : 1);
7375  } else {
7376  StructBaseCombinedInfo.Exprs.emplace_back(MapDecl, MapExpr);
7377  StructBaseCombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(
7378  BP.emitRawPointer(CGF));
7379  StructBaseCombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
7380  StructBaseCombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
7381  StructBaseCombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(LB.emitRawPointer(CGF));
7382  StructBaseCombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
7383  Size, CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
7384  StructBaseCombinedInfo.NonContigInfo.Dims.push_back(
7385  IsNonContiguous ? DimSize : 1);
7386  }
7387 
7388  // If Mapper is valid, the last component inherits the mapper.
7389  bool HasMapper = Mapper && Next == CE;
7390  if (!IsMappingWholeStruct)
