7391  CombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(HasMapper ? Mapper : nullptr);
7392  else
7393  StructBaseCombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(HasMapper ? Mapper
7394  : nullptr);
7395 
7396  // We need to add a pointer flag for each map that comes from the
7397  // same expression except for the first one. We also need to signal
7398  // this map is the first one that relates with the current capture
7399  // (there is a set of entries for each capture).
7400  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags Flags = getMapTypeBits(
7401  MapType, MapModifiers, MotionModifiers, IsImplicit,
7402  !IsExpressionFirstInfo || RequiresReference ||
7403  FirstPointerInComplexData || IsMemberReference,
7404  IsCaptureFirstInfo && !RequiresReference, IsNonContiguous);
7405 
7406  if (!IsExpressionFirstInfo || IsMemberReference) {
7407  // If we have a PTR_AND_OBJ pair where the OBJ is a pointer as well,
7408  // then we reset the TO/FROM/ALWAYS/DELETE/CLOSE flags.
7409  if (IsPointer || (IsMemberReference && Next != CE))
7410  Flags &= ~(OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO |
7411  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM |
7412  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_ALWAYS |
7413  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_DELETE |
7414  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_CLOSE);
7415 
7416  if (ShouldBeMemberOf) {
7417  // Set placeholder value MEMBER_OF=FFFF to indicate that the flag
7418  // should be later updated with the correct value of MEMBER_OF.
7419  Flags |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF;
7420  // From now on, all subsequent PTR_AND_OBJ entries should not be
7421  // marked as MEMBER_OF.
7422  ShouldBeMemberOf = false;
7423  }
7424  }
7425 
7426  if (!IsMappingWholeStruct)
7427  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(Flags);
7428  else
7429  StructBaseCombinedInfo.Types.push_back(Flags);
7430  }
7431 
7432  // If we have encountered a member expression so far, keep track of the
7433  // mapped member. If the parent is "*this", then the value declaration
7434  // is nullptr.
7435  if (EncounteredME) {
7436  const auto *FD = cast<FieldDecl>(EncounteredME->getMemberDecl());
7437  unsigned FieldIndex = FD->getFieldIndex();
7438 
7439  // Update info about the lowest and highest elements for this struct
7440  if (!PartialStruct.Base.isValid()) {
7441  PartialStruct.LowestElem = {FieldIndex, LowestElem};
7442  if (IsFinalArraySection) {
7443  Address HB =
7444  CGF.EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(OASE, /*IsLowerBound=*/false)
7445  .getAddress(CGF);
7446  PartialStruct.HighestElem = {FieldIndex, HB};
7447  } else {
7448  PartialStruct.HighestElem = {FieldIndex, LowestElem};
7449  }
7450  PartialStruct.Base = BP;
7451  PartialStruct.LB = BP;
7452  } else if (FieldIndex < PartialStruct.LowestElem.first) {
7453  PartialStruct.LowestElem = {FieldIndex, LowestElem};
7454  } else if (FieldIndex > PartialStruct.HighestElem.first) {
7455  if (IsFinalArraySection) {
7456  Address HB =
7457  CGF.EmitOMPArraySectionExpr(OASE, /*IsLowerBound=*/false)
7458  .getAddress(CGF);
7459  PartialStruct.HighestElem = {FieldIndex, HB};
7460  } else {
7461  PartialStruct.HighestElem = {FieldIndex, LowestElem};
7462  }
7463  }
7464  }
7465 
7466  // Need to emit combined struct for array sections.
7467  if (IsFinalArraySection || IsNonContiguous)
7468  PartialStruct.IsArraySection = true;
7469 
7470  // If we have a final array section, we are done with this expression.
7471  if (IsFinalArraySection)
7472  break;
7473 
7474  // The pointer becomes the base for the next element.
7475  if (Next != CE)
7476  BP = IsMemberReference ? LowestElem : LB;
7477 
7478  IsExpressionFirstInfo = false;
7479  IsCaptureFirstInfo = false;
7480  FirstPointerInComplexData = false;
7481  IsPrevMemberReference = IsMemberReference;
7482  } else if (FirstPointerInComplexData) {
7483  QualType Ty = Components.rbegin()
7484  ->getAssociatedDeclaration()
7485  ->getType()
7486  .getNonReferenceType();
7487  BP = CGF.EmitLoadOfPointer(BP, Ty->castAs<PointerType>());
7488  FirstPointerInComplexData = false;
7489  }
7490  }
7491  // If ran into the whole component - allocate the space for the whole
7492  // record.
7493  if (!EncounteredME)
7494  PartialStruct.HasCompleteRecord = true;
7495 
7496  if (!IsNonContiguous)
7497  return;
7498 
7499  const ASTContext &Context = CGF.getContext();
7500 
7501  // For supporting stride in array section, we need to initialize the first
7502  // dimension size as 1, first offset as 0, and first count as 1
7503  MapValuesArrayTy CurOffsets = {llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.CGM.Int64Ty, 0)};
7504  MapValuesArrayTy CurCounts = {llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.CGM.Int64Ty, 1)};
7505  MapValuesArrayTy CurStrides;
7506  MapValuesArrayTy DimSizes{llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.CGM.Int64Ty, 1)};
7507  uint64_t ElementTypeSize;
7508 
7509  // Collect Size information for each dimension and get the element size as
7510  // the first Stride. For example, for `int arr[10][10]`, the DimSizes
7511  // should be [10, 10] and the first stride is 4 btyes.
7512  for (const OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableComponent &Component :
7513  Components) {
7514  const Expr *AssocExpr = Component.getAssociatedExpression();
7515  const auto *OASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(AssocExpr);
7516 
7517  if (!OASE)
7518  continue;
7519 
7520  QualType Ty = OMPArraySectionExpr::getBaseOriginalType(OASE->getBase());
7521  auto *CAT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(Ty);
7522  auto *VAT = Context.getAsVariableArrayType(Ty);
7523 
7524  // We need all the dimension size except for the last dimension.
7525  assert((VAT || CAT || &Component == &*Components.begin()) &&
7526  "Should be either ConstantArray or VariableArray if not the "
7527  "first Component");
7528 
7529  // Get element size if CurStrides is empty.
7530  if (CurStrides.empty()) {
7531  const Type *ElementType = nullptr;
7532  if (CAT)
7533  ElementType = CAT->getElementType().getTypePtr();
7534  else if (VAT)
7535  ElementType = VAT->getElementType().getTypePtr();
7536  else
7537  assert(&Component == &*Components.begin() &&
7538  "Only expect pointer (non CAT or VAT) when this is the "
7539  "first Component");
7540  // If ElementType is null, then it means the base is a pointer
7541  // (neither CAT nor VAT) and we'll attempt to get ElementType again
7542  // for next iteration.
7543  if (ElementType) {
7544  // For the case that having pointer as base, we need to remove one
7545  // level of indirection.
7546  if (&Component != &*Components.begin())
7547  ElementType = ElementType->getPointeeOrArrayElementType();
7548  ElementTypeSize =
7549  Context.getTypeSizeInChars(ElementType).getQuantity();
7550  CurStrides.push_back(
7551  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, ElementTypeSize));
7552  }
7553  }
7554  // Get dimension value except for the last dimension since we don't need
7555  // it.
7556  if (DimSizes.size() < Components.size() - 1) {
7557  if (CAT)
7558  DimSizes.push_back(
7559  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, CAT->getZExtSize()));
7560  else if (VAT)
7561  DimSizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
7562  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(VAT->getSizeExpr()), CGF.Int64Ty,
7563  /*IsSigned=*/false));
7564  }
7565  }
7566 
7567  // Skip the dummy dimension since we have already have its information.
7568  auto *DI = DimSizes.begin() + 1;
7569  // Product of dimension.
7570  llvm::Value *DimProd =
7571  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.CGM.Int64Ty, ElementTypeSize);
7572 
7573  // Collect info for non-contiguous. Notice that offset, count, and stride
7574  // are only meaningful for array-section, so we insert a null for anything
7575  // other than array-section.
7576  // Also, the size of offset, count, and stride are not the same as
7577  // pointers, base_pointers, sizes, or dims. Instead, the size of offset,
7578  // count, and stride are the same as the number of non-contiguous
7579  // declaration in target update to/from clause.
7580  for (const OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableComponent &Component :
7581  Components) {
7582  const Expr *AssocExpr = Component.getAssociatedExpression();
7583 
7584  if (const auto *AE = dyn_cast<ArraySubscriptExpr>(AssocExpr)) {
7585  llvm::Value *Offset = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
7586  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(AE->getIdx()), CGF.Int64Ty,
7587  /*isSigned=*/false);
7588  CurOffsets.push_back(Offset);
7589  CurCounts.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, /*V=*/1));
7590  CurStrides.push_back(CurStrides.back());
7591  continue;
7592  }
7593 
7594  const auto *OASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(AssocExpr);
7595 
7596  if (!OASE)
7597  continue;
7598 
7599  // Offset
7600  const Expr *OffsetExpr = OASE->getLowerBound();
7601  llvm::Value *Offset = nullptr;
7602  if (!OffsetExpr) {
7603  // If offset is absent, then we just set it to zero.
7604  Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, 0);
7605  } else {
7606  Offset = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(OffsetExpr),
7607  CGF.Int64Ty,
7608  /*isSigned=*/false);
7609  }
7610  CurOffsets.push_back(Offset);
7611 
7612  // Count
7613  const Expr *CountExpr = OASE->getLength();
7614  llvm::Value *Count = nullptr;
7615  if (!CountExpr) {
7616  // In Clang, once a high dimension is an array section, we construct all
7617  // the lower dimension as array section, however, for case like
7618  // arr[0:2][2], Clang construct the inner dimension as an array section
7619  // but it actually is not in an array section form according to spec.
7620  if (!OASE->getColonLocFirst().isValid() &&
7621  !OASE->getColonLocSecond().isValid()) {
7622  Count = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, 1);
7623  } else {
7624  // OpenMP 5.0, 2.1.5 Array Sections, Description.
7625  // When the length is absent it defaults to (size
7626  // lower-bound)/stride, where size is the size of the array
7627  // dimension.
7628  const Expr *StrideExpr = OASE->getStride();
7629  llvm::Value *Stride =
7630  StrideExpr
7631  ? CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(StrideExpr),
7632  CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/false)
7633  : nullptr;
7634  if (Stride)
7635  Count = CGF.Builder.CreateUDiv(
7636  CGF.Builder.CreateNUWSub(*DI, Offset), Stride);
7637  else
7638  Count = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWSub(*DI, Offset);
7639  }
7640  } else {
7641  Count = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(CountExpr);
7642  }
7643  Count = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(Count, CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/false);
7644  CurCounts.push_back(Count);
7645 
7646  // Stride_n' = Stride_n * (D_0 * D_1 ... * D_n-1) * Unit size
7647  // Take `int arr[5][5][5]` and `arr[0:2:2][1:2:1][0:2:2]` as an example:
7648  // Offset Count Stride
7649  // D0 0 1 4 (int) <- dummy dimension
7650  // D1 0 2 8 (2 * (1) * 4)
7651  // D2 1 2 20 (1 * (1 * 5) * 4)
7652  // D3 0 2 200 (2 * (1 * 5 * 4) * 4)
7653  const Expr *StrideExpr = OASE->getStride();
7654  llvm::Value *Stride =
7655  StrideExpr
7656  ? CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(StrideExpr),
7657  CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/false)
7658  : nullptr;
7659  DimProd = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(DimProd, *(DI - 1));
7660  if (Stride)
7661  CurStrides.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(DimProd, Stride));
7662  else
7663  CurStrides.push_back(DimProd);
7664  if (DI != DimSizes.end())
7665  ++DI;
7666  }
7667 
7668  CombinedInfo.NonContigInfo.Offsets.push_back(CurOffsets);
7669  CombinedInfo.NonContigInfo.Counts.push_back(CurCounts);
7670  CombinedInfo.NonContigInfo.Strides.push_back(CurStrides);
7671  }
7672 
7673  /// Return the adjusted map modifiers if the declaration a capture refers to
7674  /// appears in a first-private clause. This is expected to be used only with
7675  /// directives that start with 'target'.
7676  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags
7677  getMapModifiersForPrivateClauses(const CapturedStmt::Capture &Cap) const {
7678  assert(Cap.capturesVariable() && "Expected capture by reference only!");
7679 
7680  // A first private variable captured by reference will use only the
7681  // 'private ptr' and 'map to' flag. Return the right flags if the captured
7682  // declaration is known as first-private in this handler.
7683  if (FirstPrivateDecls.count(Cap.getCapturedVar())) {
7684  if (Cap.getCapturedVar()->getType()->isAnyPointerType())
7685  return OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO |
7686  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PTR_AND_OBJ;
7687  return OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PRIVATE |
7688  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO;
7689  }
7690  auto I = LambdasMap.find(Cap.getCapturedVar()->getCanonicalDecl());
7691  if (I != LambdasMap.end())
7692  // for map(to: lambda): using user specified map type.
7693  return getMapTypeBits(
7694  I->getSecond()->getMapType(), I->getSecond()->getMapTypeModifiers(),
7695  /*MotionModifiers=*/std::nullopt, I->getSecond()->isImplicit(),
7696  /*AddPtrFlag=*/false,
7697  /*AddIsTargetParamFlag=*/false,
7698  /*isNonContiguous=*/false);
7699  return OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO |
7700  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM;
7701  }
7702 
7703  void getPlainLayout(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
7704  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<const FieldDecl *> &Layout,
7705  bool AsBase) const {
7706  const CGRecordLayout &RL = CGF.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(RD);
7707 
7708  llvm::StructType *St =
7709  AsBase ? RL.getBaseSubobjectLLVMType() : RL.getLLVMType();
7710 
7711  unsigned NumElements = St->getNumElements();
7712  llvm::SmallVector<
7713  llvm::PointerUnion<const CXXRecordDecl *, const FieldDecl *>, 4>
7714  RecordLayout(NumElements);
7715 
7716  // Fill bases.
7717  for (const auto &I : RD->bases()) {
7718  if (I.isVirtual())
7719  continue;
7720  const auto *Base = I.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
7721  // Ignore empty bases.
7722  if (Base->isEmpty() || CGF.getContext()
7723  .getASTRecordLayout(Base)
7724  .getNonVirtualSize()
7725  .isZero())
7726  continue;
7727 
7728  unsigned FieldIndex = RL.getNonVirtualBaseLLVMFieldNo(Base);
7729  RecordLayout[FieldIndex] = Base;
7730  }
7731  // Fill in virtual bases.
7732  for (const auto &I : RD->vbases()) {
7733  const auto *Base = I.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
7734  // Ignore empty bases.
7735  if (Base->isEmpty())
7736  continue;
7737  unsigned FieldIndex = RL.getVirtualBaseIndex(Base);
7738  if (RecordLayout[FieldIndex])
7739  continue;
7740  RecordLayout[FieldIndex] = Base;
7741  }
7742  // Fill in all the fields.
7743  assert(!RD->isUnion() && "Unexpected union.");
7744  for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
7745  // Fill in non-bitfields. (Bitfields always use a zero pattern, which we
7746  // will fill in later.)
7747  if (!Field->isBitField() && !Field->isZeroSize(CGF.getContext())) {
7748  unsigned FieldIndex = RL.getLLVMFieldNo(Field);
7749  RecordLayout[FieldIndex] = Field;
7750  }
7751  }
7752  for (const llvm::PointerUnion<const CXXRecordDecl *, const FieldDecl *>
7753  &Data : RecordLayout) {
7754  if (Data.isNull())
7755  continue;
7756  if (const auto *Base = Data.dyn_cast<const CXXRecordDecl *>())
7757  getPlainLayout(Base, Layout, /*AsBase=*/true);
7758  else
7759  Layout.push_back(Data.get<const FieldDecl *>());
7760  }
7761  }
7762 
7763  /// Generate all the base pointers, section pointers, sizes, map types, and
7764  /// mappers for the extracted mappable expressions (all included in \a
7765  /// CombinedInfo). Also, for each item that relates with a device pointer, a
7766  /// pair of the relevant declaration and index where it occurs is appended to
7767  /// the device pointers info array.
7768  void generateAllInfoForClauses(
7769  ArrayRef<const OMPClause *> Clauses, MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo,
7770  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder,
7771  const llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const Decl>> &SkipVarSet =
7772  llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const Decl>>()) const {
7773  // We have to process the component lists that relate with the same
7774  // declaration in a single chunk so that we can generate the map flags
7775  // correctly. Therefore, we organize all lists in a map.
7776  enum MapKind { Present, Allocs, Other, Total };
7777  llvm::MapVector<CanonicalDeclPtr<const Decl>,
7778  SmallVector<SmallVector<MapInfo, 8>, 4>>
7779  Info;
7780 
7781  // Helper function to fill the information map for the different supported
7782  // clauses.
7783  auto &&InfoGen =
7784  [&Info, &SkipVarSet](
7785  const ValueDecl *D, MapKind Kind,
7786  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef L,
7787  OpenMPMapClauseKind MapType,
7788  ArrayRef<OpenMPMapModifierKind> MapModifiers,
7789  ArrayRef<OpenMPMotionModifierKind> MotionModifiers,
7790  bool ReturnDevicePointer, bool IsImplicit, const ValueDecl *Mapper,
7791  const Expr *VarRef = nullptr, bool ForDeviceAddr = false) {
7792  if (SkipVarSet.contains(D))
7793  return;
7794  auto It = Info.find(D);
7795  if (It == Info.end())
7796  It = Info
7797  .insert(std::make_pair(
7798  D, SmallVector<SmallVector<MapInfo, 8>, 4>(Total)))
7799  .first;
7800  It->second[Kind].emplace_back(
7801  L, MapType, MapModifiers, MotionModifiers, ReturnDevicePointer,
7802  IsImplicit, Mapper, VarRef, ForDeviceAddr);
7803  };
7804 
7805  for (const auto *Cl : Clauses) {
7806  const auto *C = dyn_cast<OMPMapClause>(Cl);
7807  if (!C)
7808  continue;
7809  MapKind Kind = Other;
7810  if (llvm::is_contained(C->getMapTypeModifiers(),
7811  OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_present))
7812  Kind = Present;
7813  else if (C->getMapType() == OMPC_MAP_alloc)
7814  Kind = Allocs;
7815  const auto *EI = C->getVarRefs().begin();
7816  for (const auto L : C->component_lists()) {
7817  const Expr *E = (C->getMapLoc().isValid()) ? *EI : nullptr;
7818  InfoGen(std::get<0>(L), Kind, std::get<1>(L), C->getMapType(),
7819  C->getMapTypeModifiers(), std::nullopt,
7820  /*ReturnDevicePointer=*/false, C->isImplicit(), std::get<2>(L),
7821  E);
7822  ++EI;
7823  }
7824  }
7825  for (const auto *Cl : Clauses) {
7826  const auto *C = dyn_cast<OMPToClause>(Cl);
7827  if (!C)
7828  continue;
7829  MapKind Kind = Other;
7830  if (llvm::is_contained(C->getMotionModifiers(),
7831  OMPC_MOTION_MODIFIER_present))
7832  Kind = Present;
7833  const auto *EI = C->getVarRefs().begin();
7834  for (const auto L : C->component_lists()) {
7835  InfoGen(std::get<0>(L), Kind, std::get<1>(L), OMPC_MAP_to, std::nullopt,
7836  C->getMotionModifiers(), /*ReturnDevicePointer=*/false,
7837  C->isImplicit(), std::get<2>(L), *EI);
7838  ++EI;
7839  }
7840  }
7841  for (const auto *Cl : Clauses) {
7842  const auto *C = dyn_cast<OMPFromClause>(Cl);
7843  if (!C)
7844  continue;
7845  MapKind Kind = Other;
7846  if (llvm::is_contained(C->getMotionModifiers(),
7847  OMPC_MOTION_MODIFIER_present))
7848  Kind = Present;
7849  const auto *EI = C->getVarRefs().begin();
7850  for (const auto L : C->component_lists()) {
7851  InfoGen(std::get<0>(L), Kind, std::get<1>(L), OMPC_MAP_from,
7852  std::nullopt, C->getMotionModifiers(),
7853  /*ReturnDevicePointer=*/false, C->isImplicit(), std::get<2>(L),
7854  *EI);
7855  ++EI;
7856  }
7857  }
7858 
7859  // Look at the use_device_ptr and use_device_addr clauses information and
7860  // mark the existing map entries as such. If there is no map information for
7861  // an entry in the use_device_ptr and use_device_addr list, we create one
7862  // with map type 'alloc' and zero size section. It is the user fault if that
7863  // was not mapped before. If there is no map information and the pointer is
7864  // a struct member, then we defer the emission of that entry until the whole
7865  // struct has been processed.
7866  llvm::MapVector<CanonicalDeclPtr<const Decl>,
7867  SmallVector<DeferredDevicePtrEntryTy, 4>>
7868  DeferredInfo;
7869  MapCombinedInfoTy UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo;
7870 
7871  auto &&UseDeviceDataCombinedInfoGen =
7872  [&UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo](const ValueDecl *VD, llvm::Value *Ptr,
7873  CodeGenFunction &CGF, bool IsDevAddr) {
7874  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(VD);
7875  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo.BasePointers.emplace_back(Ptr);
7876  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.emplace_back(VD);
7877  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo.DevicePointers.emplace_back(
7878  IsDevAddr ? DeviceInfoTy::Address : DeviceInfoTy::Pointer);
7879  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(Ptr);
7880  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(
7881  llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.Int64Ty));
7882  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo.Types.push_back(
7883  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_RETURN_PARAM);
7884  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
7885  };
7886 
7887  auto &&MapInfoGen =
7888  [&DeferredInfo, &UseDeviceDataCombinedInfoGen,
7889  &InfoGen](CodeGenFunction &CGF, const Expr *IE, const ValueDecl *VD,
7890  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef
7891  Components,
7892  bool IsImplicit, bool IsDevAddr) {
7893  // We didn't find any match in our map information - generate a zero
7894  // size array section - if the pointer is a struct member we defer
7895  // this action until the whole struct has been processed.
7896  if (isa<MemberExpr>(IE)) {
7897  // Insert the pointer into Info to be processed by
7898  // generateInfoForComponentList. Because it is a member pointer
7899  // without a pointee, no entry will be generated for it, therefore
7900  // we need to generate one after the whole struct has been
7901  // processed. Nonetheless, generateInfoForComponentList must be
7902  // called to take the pointer into account for the calculation of
7903  // the range of the partial struct.
7904  InfoGen(nullptr, Other, Components, OMPC_MAP_unknown, std::nullopt,
7905  std::nullopt, /*ReturnDevicePointer=*/false, IsImplicit,
7906  nullptr, nullptr, IsDevAddr);
7907  DeferredInfo[nullptr].emplace_back(IE, VD, IsDevAddr);
7908  } else {
7909  llvm::Value *Ptr;
7910  if (IsDevAddr) {
7911  if (IE->isGLValue())
7912  Ptr = CGF.EmitLValue(IE).getPointer(CGF);
7913  else
7914  Ptr = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(IE);
7915  } else {
7916  Ptr = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CGF.EmitLValue(IE), IE->getExprLoc());
7917  }
7918  UseDeviceDataCombinedInfoGen(VD, Ptr, CGF, IsDevAddr);
7919  }
7920  };
7921 
7922  auto &&IsMapInfoExist = [&Info](CodeGenFunction &CGF, const ValueDecl *VD,
7923  const Expr *IE, bool IsDevAddr) -> bool {
7924  // We potentially have map information for this declaration already.
7925  // Look for the first set of components that refer to it. If found,
7926  // return true.
7927  // If the first component is a member expression, we have to look into
7928  // 'this', which maps to null in the map of map information. Otherwise
7929  // look directly for the information.
7930  auto It = Info.find(isa<MemberExpr>(IE) ? nullptr : VD);
7931  if (It != Info.end()) {
7932  bool Found = false;
7933  for (auto &Data : It->second) {
7934  auto *CI = llvm::find_if(Data, [VD](const MapInfo &MI) {
7935  return MI.Components.back().getAssociatedDeclaration() == VD;
7936  });
7937  // If we found a map entry, signal that the pointer has to be
7938  // returned and move on to the next declaration. Exclude cases where
7939  // the base pointer is mapped as array subscript, array section or
7940  // array shaping. The base address is passed as a pointer to base in
7941  // this case and cannot be used as a base for use_device_ptr list
7942  // item.
7943  if (CI != Data.end()) {
7944  if (IsDevAddr) {
7945  CI->ForDeviceAddr = IsDevAddr;
7946  CI->ReturnDevicePointer = true;
7947  Found = true;
7948  break;
7949  } else {
7950  auto PrevCI = std::next(CI->Components.rbegin());
7951  const auto *VarD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(VD);
7952  if (CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory() ||
7953  isa<MemberExpr>(IE) ||
7954  !VD->getType().getNonReferenceType()->isPointerType() ||
7955  PrevCI == CI->Components.rend() ||
7956  isa<MemberExpr>(PrevCI->getAssociatedExpression()) || !VarD ||
7957  VarD->hasLocalStorage()) {
7958  CI->ForDeviceAddr = IsDevAddr;
7959  CI->ReturnDevicePointer = true;
7960  Found = true;
7961  break;
7962  }
7963  }
7964  }
7965  }
7966  return Found;
7967  }
7968  return false;
7969  };
7970 
7971  // Look at the use_device_ptr clause information and mark the existing map
7972  // entries as such. If there is no map information for an entry in the
7973  // use_device_ptr list, we create one with map type 'alloc' and zero size
7974  // section. It is the user fault if that was not mapped before. If there is
7975  // no map information and the pointer is a struct member, then we defer the
7976  // emission of that entry until the whole struct has been processed.
7977  for (const auto *Cl : Clauses) {
7978  const auto *C = dyn_cast<OMPUseDevicePtrClause>(Cl);
7979  if (!C)
7980  continue;
7981  for (const auto L : C->component_lists()) {
7982  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef Components =
7983  std::get<1>(L);
7984  assert(!Components.empty() &&
7985  "Not expecting empty list of components!");
7986  const ValueDecl *VD = Components.back().getAssociatedDeclaration();
7987  VD = cast<ValueDecl>(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
7988  const Expr *IE = Components.back().getAssociatedExpression();
7989  if (IsMapInfoExist(CGF, VD, IE, /*IsDevAddr=*/false))
7990  continue;
7991  MapInfoGen(CGF, IE, VD, Components, C->isImplicit(),
7992  /*IsDevAddr=*/false);
7993  }
7994  }
7995 
7996  llvm::SmallDenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const Decl>, 4> Processed;
7997  for (const auto *Cl : Clauses) {
7998  const auto *C = dyn_cast<OMPUseDeviceAddrClause>(Cl);
7999  if (!C)
8000  continue;
8001  for (const auto L : C->component_lists()) {
8002  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef Components =
8003  std::get<1>(L);
8004  assert(!std::get<1>(L).empty() &&
8005  "Not expecting empty list of components!");
8006  const ValueDecl *VD = std::get<1>(L).back().getAssociatedDeclaration();
8007  if (!Processed.insert(VD).second)
8008  continue;
8009  VD = cast<ValueDecl>(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
8010  const Expr *IE = std::get<1>(L).back().getAssociatedExpression();
8011  if (IsMapInfoExist(CGF, VD, IE, /*IsDevAddr=*/true))
8012  continue;
8013  MapInfoGen(CGF, IE, VD, Components, C->isImplicit(),
8014  /*IsDevAddr=*/true);
8015  }
8016  }
8017 
8018  for (const auto &Data : Info) {
8019  StructRangeInfoTy PartialStruct;
8020  // Current struct information:
8021  MapCombinedInfoTy CurInfo;
8022  // Current struct base information:
8023  MapCombinedInfoTy StructBaseCurInfo;
8024  const Decl *D = Data.first;
8025  const ValueDecl *VD = cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(D);
8026  for (const auto &M : Data.second) {
8027  for (const MapInfo &L : M) {
8028  assert(!L.Components.empty() &&
8029  "Not expecting declaration with no component lists.");
8030 
8031  // Remember the current base pointer index.
8032  unsigned CurrentBasePointersIdx = CurInfo.BasePointers.size();
8033  unsigned StructBasePointersIdx =
8034  StructBaseCurInfo.BasePointers.size();
8035  CurInfo.NonContigInfo.IsNonContiguous =
8036  L.Components.back().isNonContiguous();
8037  generateInfoForComponentList(
8038  L.MapType, L.MapModifiers, L.MotionModifiers, L.Components,
8039  CurInfo, StructBaseCurInfo, PartialStruct,
8040  /*IsFirstComponentList=*/false, L.IsImplicit,
8041  /*GenerateAllInfoForClauses*/ true, L.Mapper, L.ForDeviceAddr, VD,
8042  L.VarRef);
8043 
8044  // If this entry relates to a device pointer, set the relevant
8045  // declaration and add the 'return pointer' flag.
8046  if (L.ReturnDevicePointer) {
8047  // Check whether a value was added to either CurInfo or
8048  // StructBaseCurInfo and error if no value was added to either of
8049  // them:
8050  assert((CurrentBasePointersIdx < CurInfo.BasePointers.size() ||
8051  StructBasePointersIdx <
8052  StructBaseCurInfo.BasePointers.size()) &&
8053  "Unexpected number of mapped base pointers.");
8054 
8055  // Choose a base pointer index which is always valid:
8056  const ValueDecl *RelevantVD =
8057  L.Components.back().getAssociatedDeclaration();
8058  assert(RelevantVD &&
8059  "No relevant declaration related with device pointer??");
8060 
8061  // If StructBaseCurInfo has been updated this iteration then work on
8062  // the first new entry added to it i.e. make sure that when multiple
8063  // values are added to any of the lists, the first value added is
8064  // being modified by the assignments below (not the last value
8065  // added).
8066  if (StructBasePointersIdx < StructBaseCurInfo.BasePointers.size()) {
8067  StructBaseCurInfo.DevicePtrDecls[StructBasePointersIdx] =
8068  RelevantVD;
8069  StructBaseCurInfo.DevicePointers[StructBasePointersIdx] =
8070  L.ForDeviceAddr ? DeviceInfoTy::Address
8071  : DeviceInfoTy::Pointer;
8072  StructBaseCurInfo.Types[StructBasePointersIdx] |=
8073  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_RETURN_PARAM;
8074  } else {
8075  CurInfo.DevicePtrDecls[CurrentBasePointersIdx] = RelevantVD;
8076  CurInfo.DevicePointers[CurrentBasePointersIdx] =
8077  L.ForDeviceAddr ? DeviceInfoTy::Address
8078  : DeviceInfoTy::Pointer;
8079  CurInfo.Types[CurrentBasePointersIdx] |=
8080  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_RETURN_PARAM;
8081  }
8082  }
8083  }
8084  }
8085 
8086  // Append any pending zero-length pointers which are struct members and
8087  // used with use_device_ptr or use_device_addr.
8088  auto CI = DeferredInfo.find(Data.first);
8089  if (CI != DeferredInfo.end()) {
8090  for (const DeferredDevicePtrEntryTy &L : CI->second) {
8091  llvm::Value *BasePtr;
8092  llvm::Value *Ptr;
8093  if (L.ForDeviceAddr) {
8094  if (L.IE->isGLValue())
8095  Ptr = this->CGF.EmitLValue(L.IE).getPointer(CGF);
8096  else
8097  Ptr = this->CGF.EmitScalarExpr(L.IE);
8098  BasePtr = Ptr;
8099  // Entry is RETURN_PARAM. Also, set the placeholder value
8100  // MEMBER_OF=FFFF so that the entry is later updated with the
8101  // correct value of MEMBER_OF.
8102  CurInfo.Types.push_back(
8103  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_RETURN_PARAM |
8104  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF);
8105  } else {
8106  BasePtr = this->CGF.EmitLValue(L.IE).getPointer(CGF);
8107  Ptr = this->CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(this->CGF.EmitLValue(L.IE),
8108  L.IE->getExprLoc());
8109  // Entry is PTR_AND_OBJ and RETURN_PARAM. Also, set the
8110  // placeholder value MEMBER_OF=FFFF so that the entry is later
8111  // updated with the correct value of MEMBER_OF.
8112  CurInfo.Types.push_back(
8113  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PTR_AND_OBJ |
8114  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_RETURN_PARAM |
8115  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF);
8116  }
8117  CurInfo.Exprs.push_back(L.VD);
8118  CurInfo.BasePointers.emplace_back(BasePtr);
8119  CurInfo.DevicePtrDecls.emplace_back(L.VD);
8120  CurInfo.DevicePointers.emplace_back(
8121  L.ForDeviceAddr ? DeviceInfoTy::Address : DeviceInfoTy::Pointer);
8122  CurInfo.Pointers.push_back(Ptr);
8123  CurInfo.Sizes.push_back(
8124  llvm::Constant::getNullValue(this->CGF.Int64Ty));
8125  CurInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
8126  }
8127  }
8128 
8129  // Unify entries in one list making sure the struct mapping precedes the
8130  // individual fields:
8131  MapCombinedInfoTy UnionCurInfo;
8132  UnionCurInfo.append(StructBaseCurInfo);
8133  UnionCurInfo.append(CurInfo);
8134 
8135  // If there is an entry in PartialStruct it means we have a struct with
8136  // individual members mapped. Emit an extra combined entry.
8137  if (PartialStruct.Base.isValid()) {
8138  UnionCurInfo.NonContigInfo.Dims.push_back(0);
8139  // Emit a combined entry:
8140  emitCombinedEntry(CombinedInfo, UnionCurInfo.Types, PartialStruct,
8141  /*IsMapThis*/ !VD, OMPBuilder, VD);
8142  }
8143 
8144  // We need to append the results of this capture to what we already have.
8145  CombinedInfo.append(UnionCurInfo);
8146  }
8147  // Append data for use_device_ptr clauses.
8148  CombinedInfo.append(UseDeviceDataCombinedInfo);
8149  }
8150 
8151 public:
8152  MappableExprsHandler(const OMPExecutableDirective &Dir, CodeGenFunction &CGF)
8153  : CurDir(&Dir), CGF(CGF) {
8154  // Extract firstprivate clause information.
8155  for (const auto *C : Dir.getClausesOfKind<OMPFirstprivateClause>())
8156  for (const auto *D : C->varlists())
8157  FirstPrivateDecls.try_emplace(
8158  cast<VarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(D)->getDecl()), C->isImplicit());
8159  // Extract implicit firstprivates from uses_allocators clauses.
8160  for (const auto *C : Dir.getClausesOfKind<OMPUsesAllocatorsClause>()) {
8161  for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumberOfAllocators(); I < E; ++I) {
8162  OMPUsesAllocatorsClause::Data D = C->getAllocatorData(I);
8163  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast_or_null<DeclRefExpr>(D.AllocatorTraits))
8164  FirstPrivateDecls.try_emplace(cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl()),
8165  /*Implicit=*/true);
8166  else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(
8167  cast<DeclRefExpr>(D.Allocator->IgnoreParenImpCasts())
8168  ->getDecl()))
8169  FirstPrivateDecls.try_emplace(VD, /*Implicit=*/true);
8170  }
8171  }
8172  // Extract device pointer clause information.
8173  for (const auto *C : Dir.getClausesOfKind<OMPIsDevicePtrClause>())
8174  for (auto L : C->component_lists())
8175  DevPointersMap[std::get<0>(L)].push_back(std::get<1>(L));
8176  // Extract device addr clause information.
8177  for (const auto *C : Dir.getClausesOfKind<OMPHasDeviceAddrClause>())
8178  for (auto L : C->component_lists())
8179  HasDevAddrsMap[std::get<0>(L)].push_back(std::get<1>(L));
8180  // Extract map information.
8181  for (const auto *C : Dir.getClausesOfKind<OMPMapClause>()) {
8182  if (C->getMapType() != OMPC_MAP_to)
8183  continue;
8184  for (auto L : C->component_lists()) {
8185  const ValueDecl *VD = std::get<0>(L);
8186  const auto *RD = VD ? VD->getType()
8187  .getCanonicalType()
8188  .getNonReferenceType()
8189  ->getAsCXXRecordDecl()
8190  : nullptr;
8191  if (RD && RD->isLambda())
8192  LambdasMap.try_emplace(std::get<0>(L), C);
8193  }
8194  }
8195  }
8196 
8197  /// Constructor for the declare mapper directive.
8198  MappableExprsHandler(const OMPDeclareMapperDecl &Dir, CodeGenFunction &CGF)
8199  : CurDir(&Dir), CGF(CGF) {}
8200 
8201  /// Generate code for the combined entry if we have a partially mapped struct
8202  /// and take care of the mapping flags of the arguments corresponding to
8203  /// individual struct members.
8204  void emitCombinedEntry(MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo,
8205  MapFlagsArrayTy &CurTypes,
8206  const StructRangeInfoTy &PartialStruct, bool IsMapThis,
8207  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder,
8208  const ValueDecl *VD = nullptr,
8209  bool NotTargetParams = true) const {
8210  if (CurTypes.size() == 1 &&
8211  ((CurTypes.back() & OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF) !=
8212  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF) &&
8213  !PartialStruct.IsArraySection)
8214  return;
8215  Address LBAddr = PartialStruct.LowestElem.second;
8216  Address HBAddr = PartialStruct.HighestElem.second;
8217  if (PartialStruct.HasCompleteRecord) {
8218  LBAddr = PartialStruct.LB;
8219  HBAddr = PartialStruct.LB;
8220  }
8221  CombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(VD);
8222  // Base is the base of the struct
8223  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(PartialStruct.Base.emitRawPointer(CGF));
8224  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
8225  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
8226  // Pointer is the address of the lowest element
8227  llvm::Value *LB = LBAddr.emitRawPointer(CGF);
8228  const CXXMethodDecl *MD =
8229  CGF.CurFuncDecl ? dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CGF.CurFuncDecl) : nullptr;
8230  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MD ? MD->getParent() : nullptr;
8231  bool HasBaseClass = RD && IsMapThis ? RD->getNumBases() > 0 : false;
8232  // There should not be a mapper for a combined entry.
8233  if (HasBaseClass) {
8234  // OpenMP 5.2 148:21:
8235  // If the target construct is within a class non-static member function,
8236  // and a variable is an accessible data member of the object for which the
8237  // non-static data member function is invoked, the variable is treated as
8238  // if the this[:1] expression had appeared in a map clause with a map-type
8239  // of tofrom.
8240  // Emit this[:1]
8241  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(PartialStruct.Base.emitRawPointer(CGF));
8242  QualType Ty = MD->getFunctionObjectParameterType();
8243  llvm::Value *Size =
8244  CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.getTypeSize(Ty), CGF.Int64Ty,
8245  /*isSigned=*/true);
8246  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(Size);
8247  } else {
8248  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(LB);
8249  // Size is (addr of {highest+1} element) - (addr of lowest element)
8250  llvm::Value *HB = HBAddr.emitRawPointer(CGF);
8251  llvm::Value *HAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(
8252  HBAddr.getElementType(), HB, /*Idx0=*/1);
8253  llvm::Value *CLAddr = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerCast(LB, CGF.VoidPtrTy);
8254  llvm::Value *CHAddr = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerCast(HAddr, CGF.VoidPtrTy);
8255  llvm::Value *Diff = CGF.Builder.CreatePtrDiff(CGF.Int8Ty, CHAddr, CLAddr);
8256  llvm::Value *Size = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(Diff, CGF.Int64Ty,
8257  /*isSigned=*/false);
8258  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(Size);
8259  }
8260  CombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
8261  // Map type is always TARGET_PARAM, if generate info for captures.
8262  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(
8263  NotTargetParams ? OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_NONE
8264  : OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TARGET_PARAM);
8265  // If any element has the present modifier, then make sure the runtime
8266  // doesn't attempt to allocate the struct.
8267  if (CurTypes.end() !=
8268  llvm::find_if(CurTypes, [](OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags Type) {
8269  return static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
8270  Type & OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PRESENT);
8271  }))
8272  CombinedInfo.Types.back() |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PRESENT;
8273  // Remove TARGET_PARAM flag from the first element
8274  (*CurTypes.begin()) &= ~OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TARGET_PARAM;
8275  // If any element has the ompx_hold modifier, then make sure the runtime
8276  // uses the hold reference count for the struct as a whole so that it won't
8277  // be unmapped by an extra dynamic reference count decrement. Add it to all
8278  // elements as well so the runtime knows which reference count to check
8279  // when determining whether it's time for device-to-host transfers of
8280  // individual elements.
8281  if (CurTypes.end() !=
8282  llvm::find_if(CurTypes, [](OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags Type) {
8283  return static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
8284  Type & OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_OMPX_HOLD);
8285  })) {
8286  CombinedInfo.Types.back() |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_OMPX_HOLD;
8287  for (auto &M : CurTypes)
8288  M |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_OMPX_HOLD;
8289  }
8290 
8291  // All other current entries will be MEMBER_OF the combined entry
8292  // (except for PTR_AND_OBJ entries which do not have a placeholder value
8293  // 0xFFFF in the MEMBER_OF field).
8294  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags MemberOfFlag =
8295  OMPBuilder.getMemberOfFlag(CombinedInfo.BasePointers.size() - 1);
8296  for (auto &M : CurTypes)
8297  OMPBuilder.setCorrectMemberOfFlag(M, MemberOfFlag);
8298  }
8299 
8300  /// Generate all the base pointers, section pointers, sizes, map types, and
8301  /// mappers for the extracted mappable expressions (all included in \a
8302  /// CombinedInfo). Also, for each item that relates with a device pointer, a
8303  /// pair of the relevant declaration and index where it occurs is appended to
8304  /// the device pointers info array.
8305  void generateAllInfo(
8306  MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo, llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder,
8307  const llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const Decl>> &SkipVarSet =
8308  llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const Decl>>()) const {
8309  assert(CurDir.is<const OMPExecutableDirective *>() &&
8310  "Expect a executable directive");
8311  const auto *CurExecDir = CurDir.get<const OMPExecutableDirective *>();
8312  generateAllInfoForClauses(CurExecDir->clauses(), CombinedInfo, OMPBuilder,
8313  SkipVarSet);
8314  }
8315 
8316  /// Generate all the base pointers, section pointers, sizes, map types, and
8317  /// mappers for the extracted map clauses of user-defined mapper (all included
8318  /// in \a CombinedInfo).
8319  void generateAllInfoForMapper(MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo,
8320  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder) const {
8321  assert(CurDir.is<const OMPDeclareMapperDecl *>() &&
8322  "Expect a declare mapper directive");
8323  const auto *CurMapperDir = CurDir.get<const OMPDeclareMapperDecl *>();
8324  generateAllInfoForClauses(CurMapperDir->clauses(), CombinedInfo,
8325  OMPBuilder);
8326  }
8327 
8328  /// Emit capture info for lambdas for variables captured by reference.
8329  void generateInfoForLambdaCaptures(
8330  const ValueDecl *VD, llvm::Value *Arg, MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo,
8331  llvm::DenseMap<llvm::Value *, llvm::Value *> &LambdaPointers) const {
8332  QualType VDType = VD->getType().getCanonicalType().getNonReferenceType();
8333  const auto *RD = VDType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
8334  if (!RD || !RD->isLambda())
8335  return;
8336  Address VDAddr(Arg, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(VDType),
8337  CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
8338  LValue VDLVal = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(VDAddr, VDType);
8339  llvm::DenseMap<const ValueDecl *, FieldDecl *> Captures;
8340  FieldDecl *ThisCapture = nullptr;
8341  RD->getCaptureFields(Captures, ThisCapture);
8342  if (ThisCapture) {
8343  LValue ThisLVal =
8344  CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(VDLVal, ThisCapture);
8345  LValue ThisLValVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(VDLVal, ThisCapture);
8346  LambdaPointers.try_emplace(ThisLVal.getPointer(CGF),
8347  VDLVal.getPointer(CGF));
8348  CombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(VD);
8349  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(ThisLVal.getPointer(CGF));
8350  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
8351  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
8352  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(ThisLValVal.getPointer(CGF));
8353  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(
8354  CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.getTypeSize(CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy),
8355  CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
8356  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(
8357  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PTR_AND_OBJ |
8358  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_LITERAL |
8359  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF |
8360  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_IMPLICIT);
8361  CombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
8362  }
8363  for (const LambdaCapture &LC : RD->captures()) {
8364  if (!LC.capturesVariable())
8365  continue;
8366  const VarDecl *VD = cast<VarDecl>(LC.getCapturedVar());
8367  if (LC.getCaptureKind() != LCK_ByRef && !VD->getType()->isPointerType())
8368  continue;
8369  auto It = Captures.find(VD);
8370  assert(It != Captures.end() && "Found lambda capture without field.");
8371  LValue VarLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(VDLVal, It->second);
8372  if (LC.getCaptureKind() == LCK_ByRef) {
8373  LValue VarLValVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(VDLVal, It->second);
8374  LambdaPointers.try_emplace(VarLVal.getPointer(CGF),
8375  VDLVal.getPointer(CGF));
8376  CombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(VD);
8377  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(VarLVal.getPointer(CGF));
8378  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
8379  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
8380  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(VarLValVal.getPointer(CGF));
8381  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
8382  CGF.getTypeSize(
8383  VD->getType().getCanonicalType().getNonReferenceType()),
8384  CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
8385  } else {
8386  RValue VarRVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(VarLVal, RD->getLocation());
8387  LambdaPointers.try_emplace(VarLVal.getPointer(CGF),
8388  VDLVal.getPointer(CGF));
8389  CombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(VD);
8390  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(VarLVal.getPointer(CGF));
8391  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
8392  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
8393  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(VarRVal.getScalarVal());
8394  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, 0));
8395  }
8396  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(
8397  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PTR_AND_OBJ |
8398  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_LITERAL |
8399  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF |
8400  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_IMPLICIT);
8401  CombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
8402  }
8403  }
8404 
8405  /// Set correct indices for lambdas captures.
8406  void adjustMemberOfForLambdaCaptures(
8407  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder,
8408  const llvm::DenseMap<llvm::Value *, llvm::Value *> &LambdaPointers,
8409  MapBaseValuesArrayTy &BasePointers, MapValuesArrayTy &Pointers,
8410  MapFlagsArrayTy &Types) const {
8411  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Types.size(); I < E; ++I) {
8412  // Set correct member_of idx for all implicit lambda captures.
8413  if (Types[I] != (OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PTR_AND_OBJ |
8414  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_LITERAL |
8415  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_MEMBER_OF |
8416  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_IMPLICIT))
8417  continue;
8418  llvm::Value *BasePtr = LambdaPointers.lookup(BasePointers[I]);
8419  assert(BasePtr && "Unable to find base lambda address.");
8420  int TgtIdx = -1;
8421  for (unsigned J = I; J > 0; --J) {
8422  unsigned Idx = J - 1;
8423  if (Pointers[Idx] != BasePtr)
8424  continue;
8425  TgtIdx = Idx;
8426  break;
8427  }
8428  assert(TgtIdx != -1 && "Unable to find parent lambda.");
8429  // All other current entries will be MEMBER_OF the combined entry
8430  // (except for PTR_AND_OBJ entries which do not have a placeholder value
8431  // 0xFFFF in the MEMBER_OF field).
8432  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags MemberOfFlag =
8433  OMPBuilder.getMemberOfFlag(TgtIdx);
8434  OMPBuilder.setCorrectMemberOfFlag(Types[I], MemberOfFlag);
8435  }
8436  }
8437 
8438  /// Generate the base pointers, section pointers, sizes, map types, and
8439  /// mappers associated to a given capture (all included in \a CombinedInfo).
8440  void generateInfoForCapture(const CapturedStmt::Capture *Cap,
8441  llvm::Value *Arg, MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo,
8442  StructRangeInfoTy &PartialStruct) const {
8443  assert(!Cap->capturesVariableArrayType() &&
8444  "Not expecting to generate map info for a variable array type!");
8445 
8446  // We need to know when we generating information for the first component
8447  const ValueDecl *VD = Cap->capturesThis()
8448  ? nullptr
8449  : Cap->getCapturedVar()->getCanonicalDecl();
8450 
8451  // for map(to: lambda): skip here, processing it in
8452  // generateDefaultMapInfo
8453  if (LambdasMap.count(VD))
8454  return;
8455 
8456  // If this declaration appears in a is_device_ptr clause we just have to
8457  // pass the pointer by value. If it is a reference to a declaration, we just
8458  // pass its value.
8459  if (VD && (DevPointersMap.count(VD) || HasDevAddrsMap.count(VD))) {
8460  CombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(VD);
8461  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.emplace_back(Arg);
8462  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.emplace_back(VD);
8463  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.emplace_back(DeviceInfoTy::Pointer);
8464  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(Arg);
8465  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
8466  CGF.getTypeSize(CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy), CGF.Int64Ty,
8467  /*isSigned=*/true));
8468  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(
8469  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_LITERAL |
8470  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TARGET_PARAM);
8471  CombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
8472  return;
8473  }
8474 
8475  using MapData =
8476  std::tuple<OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef,
8477  OpenMPMapClauseKind, ArrayRef<OpenMPMapModifierKind>, bool,
8478  const ValueDecl *, const Expr *>;
8479  SmallVector<MapData, 4> DeclComponentLists;
8480  // For member fields list in is_device_ptr, store it in
8481  // DeclComponentLists for generating components info.
8482  static const OpenMPMapModifierKind Unknown = OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_unknown;
8483  auto It = DevPointersMap.find(VD);
8484  if (It != DevPointersMap.end())
8485  for (const auto &MCL : It->second)
8486  DeclComponentLists.emplace_back(MCL, OMPC_MAP_to, Unknown,
8487  /*IsImpicit = */ true, nullptr,
8488  nullptr);
8489  auto I = HasDevAddrsMap.find(VD);
8490  if (I != HasDevAddrsMap.end())
8491  for (const auto &MCL : I->second)
8492  DeclComponentLists.emplace_back(MCL, OMPC_MAP_tofrom, Unknown,
8493  /*IsImpicit = */ true, nullptr,
8494  nullptr);
8495  assert(CurDir.is<const OMPExecutableDirective *>() &&
8496  "Expect a executable directive");
8497  const auto *CurExecDir = CurDir.get<const OMPExecutableDirective *>();
8498  for (const auto *C : CurExecDir->getClausesOfKind<OMPMapClause>()) {
8499  const auto *EI = C->getVarRefs().begin();
8500  for (const auto L : C->decl_component_lists(VD)) {
8501  const ValueDecl *VDecl, *Mapper;
8502  // The Expression is not correct if the mapping is implicit
8503  const Expr *E = (C->getMapLoc().isValid()) ? *EI : nullptr;
8504  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef Components;
8505  std::tie(VDecl, Components, Mapper) = L;
8506  assert(VDecl == VD && "We got information for the wrong declaration??");
8507  assert(!Components.empty() &&
8508  "Not expecting declaration with no component lists.");
8509  DeclComponentLists.emplace_back(Components, C->getMapType(),
8510  C->getMapTypeModifiers(),
8511  C->isImplicit(), Mapper, E);
8512  ++EI;
8513  }
8514  }
8515  llvm::stable_sort(DeclComponentLists, [](const MapData &LHS,
8516  const MapData &RHS) {
8517  ArrayRef<OpenMPMapModifierKind> MapModifiers = std::get<2>(LHS);
8518  OpenMPMapClauseKind MapType = std::get<1>(RHS);
8519  bool HasPresent =
8520  llvm::is_contained(MapModifiers, clang::OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_present);
8521  bool HasAllocs = MapType == OMPC_MAP_alloc;
8522  MapModifiers = std::get<2>(RHS);
8523  MapType = std::get<1>(LHS);
8524  bool HasPresentR =
8525  llvm::is_contained(MapModifiers, clang::OMPC_MAP_MODIFIER_present);
8526  bool HasAllocsR = MapType == OMPC_MAP_alloc;
8527  return (HasPresent && !HasPresentR) || (HasAllocs && !HasAllocsR);
8528  });
8529 
8530  // Find overlapping elements (including the offset from the base element).
8531  llvm::SmallDenseMap<
8532  const MapData *,
8533  llvm::SmallVector<
8534  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef, 4>,
8535  4>
8536  OverlappedData;
8537  size_t Count = 0;
8538  for (const MapData &L : DeclComponentLists) {
8539  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef Components;
8540  OpenMPMapClauseKind MapType;
8541  ArrayRef<OpenMPMapModifierKind> MapModifiers;
8542  bool IsImplicit;
8543  const ValueDecl *Mapper;
8544  const Expr *VarRef;
8545  std::tie(Components, MapType, MapModifiers, IsImplicit, Mapper, VarRef) =
8546  L;
8547  ++Count;
8548  for (const MapData &L1 : ArrayRef(DeclComponentLists).slice(Count)) {
8549  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef Components1;
8550  std::tie(Components1, MapType, MapModifiers, IsImplicit, Mapper,
8551  VarRef) = L1;
8552  auto CI = Components.rbegin();
8553  auto CE = Components.rend();
8554  auto SI = Components1.rbegin();
8555  auto SE = Components1.rend();
8556  for (; CI != CE && SI != SE; ++CI, ++SI) {
8557  if (CI->getAssociatedExpression()->getStmtClass() !=
8558  SI->getAssociatedExpression()->getStmtClass())
8559  break;
8560  // Are we dealing with different variables/fields?
8561  if (CI->getAssociatedDeclaration() != SI->getAssociatedDeclaration())
8562  break;
8563  }
8564  // Found overlapping if, at least for one component, reached the head
8565  // of the components list.
8566  if (CI == CE || SI == SE) {
8567  // Ignore it if it is the same component.
8568  if (CI == CE && SI == SE)
8569  continue;
8570  const auto It = (SI == SE) ? CI : SI;
8571  // If one component is a pointer and another one is a kind of
8572  // dereference of this pointer (array subscript, section, dereference,
8573  // etc.), it is not an overlapping.
8574  // Same, if one component is a base and another component is a
8575  // dereferenced pointer memberexpr with the same base.
8576  if (!isa<MemberExpr>(It->getAssociatedExpression()) ||
8577  (std::prev(It)->getAssociatedDeclaration() &&
8578  std::prev(It)
8579  ->getAssociatedDeclaration()
8580  ->getType()
8581  ->isPointerType()) ||
8582  (It->getAssociatedDeclaration() &&
8583  It->getAssociatedDeclaration()->getType()->isPointerType() &&
8584  std::next(It) != CE && std::next(It) != SE))
8585  continue;
8586  const MapData &BaseData = CI == CE ? L : L1;
8587  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef SubData =
8588  SI == SE ? Components : Components1;
8589  auto &OverlappedElements = OverlappedData.FindAndConstruct(&BaseData);
8590  OverlappedElements.getSecond().push_back(SubData);
8591  }
8592  }
8593  }
8594  // Sort the overlapped elements for each item.
8595  llvm::SmallVector<const FieldDecl *, 4> Layout;
8596  if (!OverlappedData.empty()) {
8597  const Type *BaseType = VD->getType().getCanonicalType().getTypePtr();
8598  const Type *OrigType = BaseType->getPointeeOrArrayElementType();
8599  while (BaseType != OrigType) {
8600  BaseType = OrigType->getCanonicalTypeInternal().getTypePtr();
8601  OrigType = BaseType->getPointeeOrArrayElementType();
8602  }
8603 
8604  if (const auto *CRD = BaseType->getAsCXXRecordDecl())
8605  getPlainLayout(CRD, Layout, /*AsBase=*/false);
8606  else {
8607  const auto *RD = BaseType->getAsRecordDecl();
8608  Layout.append(RD->field_begin(), RD->field_end());
8609  }
8610  }
8611  for (auto &Pair : OverlappedData) {
8612  llvm::stable_sort(
8613  Pair.getSecond(),
8614  [&Layout](
8615  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef First,
8616  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef
8617  Second) {
8618  auto CI = First.rbegin();
8619  auto CE = First.rend();
8620  auto SI = Second.rbegin();
8621  auto SE = Second.rend();
8622  for (; CI != CE && SI != SE; ++CI, ++SI) {
8623  if (CI->getAssociatedExpression()->getStmtClass() !=
8624  SI->getAssociatedExpression()->getStmtClass())
8625  break;
8626  // Are we dealing with different variables/fields?
8627  if (CI->getAssociatedDeclaration() !=
8628  SI->getAssociatedDeclaration())
8629  break;
8630  }
8631 
8632  // Lists contain the same elements.
8633  if (CI == CE && SI == SE)
8634  return false;
8635 
8636  // List with less elements is less than list with more elements.
8637  if (CI == CE || SI == SE)
8638  return CI == CE;
8639 
8640  const auto *FD1 = cast<FieldDecl>(CI->getAssociatedDeclaration());
8641  const auto *FD2 = cast<FieldDecl>(SI->getAssociatedDeclaration());
8642  if (FD1->getParent() == FD2->getParent())
8643  return FD1->getFieldIndex() < FD2->getFieldIndex();
8644  const auto *It =
8645  llvm::find_if(Layout, [FD1, FD2](const FieldDecl *FD) {
8646  return FD == FD1 || FD == FD2;
8647  });
8648  return *It == FD1;
8649  });
8650  }
8651 
8652  // Associated with a capture, because the mapping flags depend on it.
8653  // Go through all of the elements with the overlapped elements.
8654  bool IsFirstComponentList = true;
8655  MapCombinedInfoTy StructBaseCombinedInfo;
8656  for (const auto &Pair : OverlappedData) {
8657  const MapData &L = *Pair.getFirst();
8658  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef Components;
8659  OpenMPMapClauseKind MapType;
8660  ArrayRef<OpenMPMapModifierKind> MapModifiers;
8661  bool IsImplicit;
8662  const ValueDecl *Mapper;
8663  const Expr *VarRef;
8664  std::tie(Components, MapType, MapModifiers, IsImplicit, Mapper, VarRef) =
8665  L;
8666  ArrayRef<OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef>
8667  OverlappedComponents = Pair.getSecond();
8668  generateInfoForComponentList(
8669  MapType, MapModifiers, std::nullopt, Components, CombinedInfo,
8670  StructBaseCombinedInfo, PartialStruct, IsFirstComponentList,
8671  IsImplicit, /*GenerateAllInfoForClauses*/ false, Mapper,
8672  /*ForDeviceAddr=*/false, VD, VarRef, OverlappedComponents);
8673  IsFirstComponentList = false;
8674  }
8675  // Go through other elements without overlapped elements.
8676  for (const MapData &L : DeclComponentLists) {
8677  OMPClauseMappableExprCommon::MappableExprComponentListRef Components;
8678  OpenMPMapClauseKind MapType;
8679  ArrayRef<OpenMPMapModifierKind> MapModifiers;
8680  bool IsImplicit;
8681  const ValueDecl *Mapper;
8682  const Expr *VarRef;
8683  std::tie(Components, MapType, MapModifiers, IsImplicit, Mapper, VarRef) =
8684  L;
8685  auto It = OverlappedData.find(&L);
8686  if (It == OverlappedData.end())
8687  generateInfoForComponentList(
8688  MapType, MapModifiers, std::nullopt, Components, CombinedInfo,
8689  StructBaseCombinedInfo, PartialStruct, IsFirstComponentList,
8690  IsImplicit, /*GenerateAllInfoForClauses*/ false, Mapper,
8691  /*ForDeviceAddr=*/false, VD, VarRef);
8692  IsFirstComponentList = false;
8693  }
8694  }
8695 
8696  /// Generate the default map information for a given capture \a CI,
8697  /// record field declaration \a RI and captured value \a CV.
8698  void generateDefaultMapInfo(const CapturedStmt::Capture &CI,
8699  const FieldDecl &RI, llvm::Value *CV,
8700  MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo) const {
8701  bool IsImplicit = true;
8702  // Do the default mapping.
8703  if (CI.capturesThis()) {
8704  CombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(nullptr);
8705  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(CV);
8706  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
8707  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
8708  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(CV);
8709  const auto *PtrTy = cast<PointerType>(RI.getType().getTypePtr());
8710  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(
8711  CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.getTypeSize(PtrTy->getPointeeType()),
8712  CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
8713  // Default map type.
8714  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO |
8715  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM);
8716  } else if (CI.capturesVariableByCopy()) {
8717  const VarDecl *VD = CI.getCapturedVar();
8718  CombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
8719  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(CV);
8720  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
8721  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
8722  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(CV);
8723  if (!RI.getType()->isAnyPointerType()) {
8724  // We have to signal to the runtime captures passed by value that are
8725  // not pointers.
8726  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(
8727  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_LITERAL);
8728  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
8729  CGF.getTypeSize(RI.getType()), CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
8730  } else {
8731  // Pointers are implicitly mapped with a zero size and no flags
8732  // (other than first map that is added for all implicit maps).
8733  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_NONE);
8734  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.Int64Ty));
8735  }
8736  auto I = FirstPrivateDecls.find(VD);
8737  if (I != FirstPrivateDecls.end())
8738  IsImplicit = I->getSecond();
8739  } else {
8740  assert(CI.capturesVariable() && "Expected captured reference.");
8741  const auto *PtrTy = cast<ReferenceType>(RI.getType().getTypePtr());
8742  QualType ElementType = PtrTy->getPointeeType();
8743  CombinedInfo.Sizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
8744  CGF.getTypeSize(ElementType), CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
8745  // The default map type for a scalar/complex type is 'to' because by
8746  // default the value doesn't have to be retrieved. For an aggregate
8747  // type, the default is 'tofrom'.
8748  CombinedInfo.Types.push_back(getMapModifiersForPrivateClauses(CI));
8749  const VarDecl *VD = CI.getCapturedVar();
8750  auto I = FirstPrivateDecls.find(VD);
8751  CombinedInfo.Exprs.push_back(VD->getCanonicalDecl());
8752  CombinedInfo.BasePointers.push_back(CV);
8753  CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
8754  CombinedInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(DeviceInfoTy::None);
8755  if (I != FirstPrivateDecls.end() && ElementType->isAnyPointerType()) {
8756  Address PtrAddr = CGF.EmitLoadOfReference(CGF.MakeAddrLValue(
8757  CV, ElementType, CGF.getContext().getDeclAlign(VD),
8758  AlignmentSource::Decl));
8759  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(PtrAddr.emitRawPointer(CGF));
8760  } else {
8761  CombinedInfo.Pointers.push_back(CV);
8762  }
8763  if (I != FirstPrivateDecls.end())
8764  IsImplicit = I->getSecond();
8765  }
8766  // Every default map produces a single argument which is a target parameter.
8767  CombinedInfo.Types.back() |=
8768  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TARGET_PARAM;
8769 
8770  // Add flag stating this is an implicit map.
8771  if (IsImplicit)
8772  CombinedInfo.Types.back() |= OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_IMPLICIT;
8773 
8774  // No user-defined mapper for default mapping.
8775  CombinedInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
8776  }
8777 };
8778 } // anonymous namespace
8779 
8780 // Try to extract the base declaration from a `this->x` expression if possible.
8781 static ValueDecl *getDeclFromThisExpr(const Expr *E) {
8782  if (!E)
8783  return nullptr;
8784 
8785  if (const auto *OASE = dyn_cast<OMPArraySectionExpr>(E->IgnoreParenCasts()))
8786  if (const MemberExpr *ME =
8787  dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(OASE->getBase()->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
8788  return ME->getMemberDecl();
8789  return nullptr;
8790 }
8791 
8792 /// Emit a string constant containing the names of the values mapped to the
8793 /// offloading runtime library.
8794 llvm::Constant *
8795 emitMappingInformation(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder,
8796  MappableExprsHandler::MappingExprInfo &MapExprs) {
8797 
8798  uint32_t SrcLocStrSize;
8799  if (!MapExprs.getMapDecl() && !MapExprs.getMapExpr())
8800  return OMPBuilder.getOrCreateDefaultSrcLocStr(SrcLocStrSize);
8801 
8802  SourceLocation Loc;
8803  if (!MapExprs.getMapDecl() && MapExprs.getMapExpr()) {
8804  if (const ValueDecl *VD = getDeclFromThisExpr(MapExprs.getMapExpr()))
8805  Loc = VD->getLocation();
8806  else
8807  Loc = MapExprs.getMapExpr()->getExprLoc();
8808  } else {
8809  Loc = MapExprs.getMapDecl()->getLocation();
8810  }
8811 
8812  std::string ExprName;
8813  if (MapExprs.getMapExpr()) {
8814  PrintingPolicy P(CGF.getContext().getLangOpts());
8815  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(ExprName);
8816  MapExprs.getMapExpr()->printPretty(OS, nullptr, P);
8817  OS.flush();
8818  } else {
8819  ExprName = MapExprs.getMapDecl()->getNameAsString();
8820  }
8821 
8822  PresumedLoc PLoc = CGF.getContext().getSourceManager().getPresumedLoc(Loc);
8823  return OMPBuilder.getOrCreateSrcLocStr(PLoc.getFilename(), ExprName,
8824  PLoc.getLine(), PLoc.getColumn(),
8825  SrcLocStrSize);
8826 }
8827 
8828 /// Emit the arrays used to pass the captures and map information to the
8829 /// offloading runtime library. If there is no map or capture information,
8830 /// return nullptr by reference.
8831 static void emitOffloadingArrays(
8832  CodeGenFunction &CGF, MappableExprsHandler::MapCombinedInfoTy &CombinedInfo,
8833  CGOpenMPRuntime::TargetDataInfo &Info, llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder,
8834  bool IsNonContiguous = false) {
8835  CodeGenModule &CGM = CGF.CGM;
8836 
8837  // Reset the array information.
8838  Info.clearArrayInfo();
8839  Info.NumberOfPtrs = CombinedInfo.BasePointers.size();
8840 
8841  using InsertPointTy = llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy;
8842  InsertPointTy AllocaIP(CGF.AllocaInsertPt->getParent(),
8843  CGF.AllocaInsertPt->getIterator());
8844  InsertPointTy CodeGenIP(CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock(),
8845  CGF.Builder.GetInsertPoint());
8846 
8847  auto FillInfoMap = [&](MappableExprsHandler::MappingExprInfo &MapExpr) {
8848  return emitMappingInformation(CGF, OMPBuilder, MapExpr);
8849  };
8850  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() !=
8851  llvm::codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo) {
8852  CombinedInfo.Names.resize(CombinedInfo.Exprs.size());
8853  llvm::transform(CombinedInfo.Exprs, CombinedInfo.Names.begin(),
8854  FillInfoMap);
8855  }
8856 
8857  auto DeviceAddrCB = [&](unsigned int I, llvm::Value *NewDecl) {
8858  if (const ValueDecl *DevVD = CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls[I]) {
8859  Info.CaptureDeviceAddrMap.try_emplace(DevVD, NewDecl);
8860  }
8861  };
8862 
8863  auto CustomMapperCB = [&](unsigned int I) {
8864  llvm::Value *MFunc = nullptr;
8865  if (CombinedInfo.Mappers[I]) {
8866  Info.HasMapper = true;
8867  MFunc = CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getOrCreateUserDefinedMapperFunc(
8868  cast<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(CombinedInfo.Mappers[I]));
8869  }
8870  return MFunc;
8871  };
8872  OMPBuilder.emitOffloadingArrays(AllocaIP, CodeGenIP, CombinedInfo, Info,
8873  /*IsNonContiguous=*/true, DeviceAddrCB,
8874  CustomMapperCB);
8875 }
8876 
8877 /// Check for inner distribute directive.
8878 static const OMPExecutableDirective *
8879 getNestedDistributeDirective(ASTContext &Ctx, const OMPExecutableDirective &D) {
8880  const auto *CS = D.getInnermostCapturedStmt();
8881  const auto *Body =
8882  CS->getCapturedStmt()->IgnoreContainers(/*IgnoreCaptured=*/true);
8883  const Stmt *ChildStmt =
8884  CGOpenMPSIMDRuntime::getSingleCompoundChild(Ctx, Body);
8885 
8886  if (const auto *NestedDir =
8887  dyn_cast_or_null<OMPExecutableDirective>(ChildStmt)) {
8888  OpenMPDirectiveKind DKind = NestedDir->getDirectiveKind();
8889  switch (D.getDirectiveKind()) {
8890  case OMPD_target:
8891  // For now, treat 'target' with nested 'teams loop' as if it's
8892  // distributed (target teams distribute).
8893  if (isOpenMPDistributeDirective(DKind) || DKind == OMPD_teams_loop)
8894  return NestedDir;
8895  if (DKind == OMPD_teams) {
8896  Body = NestedDir->getInnermostCapturedStmt()->IgnoreContainers(
8897  /*IgnoreCaptured=*/true);
8898  if (!Body)
8899  return nullptr;
8900  ChildStmt = CGOpenMPSIMDRuntime::getSingleCompoundChild(Ctx, Body);
8901  if (const auto *NND =
8902  dyn_cast_or_null<OMPExecutableDirective>(ChildStmt)) {
8903  DKind = NND->getDirectiveKind();
8904  if (isOpenMPDistributeDirective(DKind))
8905  return NND;
8906  }
8907  }
8908  return nullptr;
8909  case OMPD_target_teams:
8910  if (isOpenMPDistributeDirective(DKind))
8911  return NestedDir;
8912  return nullptr;
8913  case OMPD_target_parallel:
8914  case OMPD_target_simd:
8915  case OMPD_target_parallel_for:
8916  case OMPD_target_parallel_for_simd:
8917  return nullptr;
8918  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute:
8919  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_simd:
8920  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
8921  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
8922  case OMPD_parallel:
8923  case OMPD_for:
8924  case OMPD_parallel_for:
8925  case OMPD_parallel_master:
8926  case OMPD_parallel_sections:
8927  case OMPD_for_simd:
8928  case OMPD_parallel_for_simd:
8929  case OMPD_cancel:
8930  case OMPD_cancellation_point:
8931  case OMPD_ordered:
8932  case OMPD_threadprivate:
8933  case OMPD_allocate:
8934  case OMPD_task:
8935  case OMPD_simd:
8936  case OMPD_tile:
8937  case OMPD_unroll:
8938  case OMPD_sections:
8939  case OMPD_section:
8940  case OMPD_single:
8941  case OMPD_master:
8942  case OMPD_critical:
8943  case OMPD_taskyield:
8944  case OMPD_barrier:
8945  case OMPD_taskwait:
8946  case OMPD_taskgroup:
8947  case OMPD_atomic:
8948  case OMPD_flush:
8949  case OMPD_depobj:
8950  case OMPD_scan:
8951  case OMPD_teams:
8952  case OMPD_target_data:
8953  case OMPD_target_exit_data:
8954  case OMPD_target_enter_data:
8955  case OMPD_distribute:
8956  case OMPD_distribute_simd:
8957  case OMPD_distribute_parallel_for:
8958  case OMPD_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
8959  case OMPD_teams_distribute:
8960  case OMPD_teams_distribute_simd:
8961  case OMPD_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
8962  case OMPD_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
8963  case OMPD_target_update:
8964  case OMPD_declare_simd:
8965  case OMPD_declare_variant:
8966  case OMPD_begin_declare_variant:
8967  case OMPD_end_declare_variant:
8968  case OMPD_declare_target:
8969  case OMPD_end_declare_target:
8970  case OMPD_declare_reduction:
8971  case OMPD_declare_mapper:
8972  case OMPD_taskloop:
8973  case OMPD_taskloop_simd:
8974  case OMPD_master_taskloop:
8975  case OMPD_master_taskloop_simd:
8976  case OMPD_parallel_master_taskloop:
8977  case OMPD_parallel_master_taskloop_simd:
8978  case OMPD_requires:
8979  case OMPD_metadirective:
8980  case OMPD_unknown:
8981  default:
8982  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected directive.");
8983  }
8984  }
8985 
8986  return nullptr;
8987 }
8988 
8989 /// Emit the user-defined mapper function. The code generation follows the
8990 /// pattern in the example below.
8991 /// \code
8992 /// void .omp_mapper.<type_name>.<mapper_id>.(void *rt_mapper_handle,
8993 /// void *base, void *begin,
8994 /// int64_t size, int64_t type,
8995 /// void *name = nullptr) {
8996 /// // Allocate space for an array section first or add a base/begin for
8997 /// // pointer dereference.
8998 /// if ((size > 1 || (base != begin && maptype.IsPtrAndObj)) &&
8999 /// !maptype.IsDelete)
9000 /// __tgt_push_mapper_component(rt_mapper_handle, base, begin,
9001 /// size*sizeof(Ty), clearToFromMember(type));
9002 /// // Map members.
9003 /// for (unsigned i = 0; i < size; i++) {
9004 /// // For each component specified by this mapper:
9005 /// for (auto c : begin[i]->all_components) {
9006 /// if (c.hasMapper())
9007 /// (*c.Mapper())(rt_mapper_handle, c.arg_base, c.arg_begin, c.arg_size,
9008 /// c.arg_type, c.arg_name);
9009 /// else
9010 /// __tgt_push_mapper_component(rt_mapper_handle, c.arg_base,
9011 /// c.arg_begin, c.arg_size, c.arg_type,
9012 /// c.arg_name);
9013 /// }
9014 /// }
9015 /// // Delete the array section.
9016 /// if (size > 1 && maptype.IsDelete)
9017 /// __tgt_push_mapper_component(rt_mapper_handle, base, begin,
9018 /// size*sizeof(Ty), clearToFromMember(type));
9019 /// }
9020 /// \endcode
9021 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitUserDefinedMapper(const OMPDeclareMapperDecl *D,
9022  CodeGenFunction *CGF) {
9023  if (UDMMap.count(D) > 0)
9024  return;
9025  ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
9026  QualType Ty = D->getType();
9027  QualType PtrTy = C.getPointerType(Ty).withRestrict();
9028  QualType Int64Ty = C.getIntTypeForBitwidth(/*DestWidth=*/64, /*Signed=*/true);
9029  auto *MapperVarDecl =
9030  cast<VarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(D->getMapperVarRef())->getDecl());
9031  SourceLocation Loc = D->getLocation();
9032  CharUnits ElementSize = C.getTypeSizeInChars(Ty);
9033  llvm::Type *ElemTy = CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);
9034 
9035  // Prepare mapper function arguments and attributes.
9036  ImplicitParamDecl HandleArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
9037  C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamKind::Other);
9038  ImplicitParamDecl BaseArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr, C.VoidPtrTy,
9039  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
9040  ImplicitParamDecl BeginArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr,
9041  C.VoidPtrTy, ImplicitParamKind::Other);
9042  ImplicitParamDecl SizeArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr, Int64Ty,
9043  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
9044  ImplicitParamDecl TypeArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr, Int64Ty,
9045  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
9046  ImplicitParamDecl NameArg(C, /*DC=*/nullptr, Loc, /*Id=*/nullptr, C.VoidPtrTy,
9047  ImplicitParamKind::Other);
9048  FunctionArgList Args;
9049  Args.push_back(&HandleArg);
9050  Args.push_back(&BaseArg);
9051  Args.push_back(&BeginArg);
9052  Args.push_back(&SizeArg);
9053  Args.push_back(&TypeArg);
9054  Args.push_back(&NameArg);
9055  const CGFunctionInfo &FnInfo =
9056  CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(C.VoidTy, Args);
9057  llvm::FunctionType *FnTy = CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
9058  SmallString<64> TyStr;
9059  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(TyStr);
9060  CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCanonicalTypeName(Ty, Out);
9061  std::string Name = getName({"omp_mapper", TyStr, D->getName()});
9062  auto *Fn = llvm::Function::Create(FnTy, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
9063  Name, &CGM.getModule());
9064  CGM.SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl(), Fn, FnInfo);
9065  Fn->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeNone);
9066  // Start the mapper function code generation.
9067  CodeGenFunction MapperCGF(CGM);
9068  MapperCGF.StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), C.VoidTy, Fn, FnInfo, Args, Loc, Loc);
9069  // Compute the starting and end addresses of array elements.
9070  llvm::Value *Size = MapperCGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
9071  MapperCGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&SizeArg), /*Volatile=*/false,
9072  C.getPointerType(Int64Ty), Loc);
9073  // Prepare common arguments for array initiation and deletion.
9074  llvm::Value *Handle = MapperCGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
9075  MapperCGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&HandleArg),
9076  /*Volatile=*/false, C.getPointerType(C.VoidPtrTy), Loc);
9077  llvm::Value *BaseIn = MapperCGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
9078  MapperCGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&BaseArg),
9079  /*Volatile=*/false, C.getPointerType(C.VoidPtrTy), Loc);
9080  llvm::Value *BeginIn = MapperCGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
9081  MapperCGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&BeginArg),
9082  /*Volatile=*/false, C.getPointerType(C.VoidPtrTy), Loc);
9083  // Convert the size in bytes into the number of array elements.
9084  Size = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateExactUDiv(
9085  Size, MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(ElementSize.getQuantity()));
9086  llvm::Value *PtrBegin = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(
9087  BeginIn, CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(PtrTy));
9088  llvm::Value *PtrEnd = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateGEP(ElemTy, PtrBegin, Size);
9089  llvm::Value *MapType = MapperCGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
9090  MapperCGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&TypeArg), /*Volatile=*/false,
9091  C.getPointerType(Int64Ty), Loc);
9092  llvm::Value *MapName = MapperCGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(
9093  MapperCGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&NameArg),
9094  /*Volatile=*/false, C.getPointerType(C.VoidPtrTy), Loc);
9095 
9096  // Emit array initiation if this is an array section and \p MapType indicates
9097  // that memory allocation is required.
9098  llvm::BasicBlock *HeadBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.arraymap.head");
9099  emitUDMapperArrayInitOrDel(MapperCGF, Handle, BaseIn, BeginIn, Size, MapType,
9100  MapName, ElementSize, HeadBB, /*IsInit=*/true);
9101 
9102  // Emit a for loop to iterate through SizeArg of elements and map all of them.
9103 
9104  // Emit the loop header block.
9105  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(HeadBB);
9106  llvm::BasicBlock *BodyBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.arraymap.body");
9107  llvm::BasicBlock *DoneBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.done");
9108  // Evaluate whether the initial condition is satisfied.
9109  llvm::Value *IsEmpty =
9110  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateICmpEQ(PtrBegin, PtrEnd, "omp.arraymap.isempty");
9111  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(IsEmpty, DoneBB, BodyBB);
9112  llvm::BasicBlock *EntryBB = MapperCGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
9113 
9114  // Emit the loop body block.
9115  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(BodyBB);
9116  llvm::BasicBlock *LastBB = BodyBB;
9117  llvm::PHINode *PtrPHI = MapperCGF.Builder.CreatePHI(
9118  PtrBegin->getType(), 2, "omp.arraymap.ptrcurrent");
9119  PtrPHI->addIncoming(PtrBegin, EntryBB);
9120  Address PtrCurrent(PtrPHI, ElemTy,
9121  MapperCGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(&BeginArg)
9122  .getAlignment()
9123  .alignmentOfArrayElement(ElementSize));
9124  // Privatize the declared variable of mapper to be the current array element.
9125  CodeGenFunction::OMPPrivateScope Scope(MapperCGF);
9126  Scope.addPrivate(MapperVarDecl, PtrCurrent);
9127  (void)Scope.Privatize();
9128 
9129  // Get map clause information. Fill up the arrays with all mapped variables.
9130  MappableExprsHandler::MapCombinedInfoTy Info;
9131  MappableExprsHandler MEHandler(*D, MapperCGF);
9132  MEHandler.generateAllInfoForMapper(Info, OMPBuilder);
9133 
9134  // Call the runtime API __tgt_mapper_num_components to get the number of
9135  // pre-existing components.
9136  llvm::Value *OffloadingArgs[] = {Handle};
9137  llvm::Value *PreviousSize = MapperCGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
9138  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(CGM.getModule(),
9139  OMPRTL___tgt_mapper_num_components),
9140  OffloadingArgs);
9141  llvm::Value *ShiftedPreviousSize = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateShl(
9142  PreviousSize,
9143  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(MappableExprsHandler::getFlagMemberOffset()));
9144 
9145  // Fill up the runtime mapper handle for all components.
9146  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Info.BasePointers.size(); ++I) {
9147  llvm::Value *CurBaseArg = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(
9148  Info.BasePointers[I], CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(C.VoidPtrTy));
9149  llvm::Value *CurBeginArg = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(
9150  Info.Pointers[I], CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(C.VoidPtrTy));
9151  llvm::Value *CurSizeArg = Info.Sizes[I];
9152  llvm::Value *CurNameArg =
9153  (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() ==
9154  llvm::codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo)
9155  ? llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGM.VoidPtrTy)
9156  : emitMappingInformation(MapperCGF, OMPBuilder, Info.Exprs[I]);
9157 
9158  // Extract the MEMBER_OF field from the map type.
9159  llvm::Value *OriMapType = MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9160  static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9161  Info.Types[I]));
9162  llvm::Value *MemberMapType =
9163  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateNUWAdd(OriMapType, ShiftedPreviousSize);
9164 
9165  // Combine the map type inherited from user-defined mapper with that
9166  // specified in the program. According to the OMP_MAP_TO and OMP_MAP_FROM
9167  // bits of the \a MapType, which is the input argument of the mapper
9168  // function, the following code will set the OMP_MAP_TO and OMP_MAP_FROM
9169  // bits of MemberMapType.
9170  // [OpenMP 5.0], 1.2.6. map-type decay.
9171  // | alloc | to | from | tofrom | release | delete
9172  // ----------------------------------------------------------
9173  // alloc | alloc | alloc | alloc | alloc | release | delete
9174  // to | alloc | to | alloc | to | release | delete
9175  // from | alloc | alloc | from | from | release | delete
9176  // tofrom | alloc | to | from | tofrom | release | delete
9177  llvm::Value *LeftToFrom = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
9178  MapType,
9179  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9180  static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9181  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO |
9182  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM)));
9183  llvm::BasicBlock *AllocBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.type.alloc");
9184  llvm::BasicBlock *AllocElseBB =
9185  MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.type.alloc.else");
9186  llvm::BasicBlock *ToBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.type.to");
9187  llvm::BasicBlock *ToElseBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.type.to.else");
9188  llvm::BasicBlock *FromBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.type.from");
9189  llvm::BasicBlock *EndBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.type.end");
9190  llvm::Value *IsAlloc = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(LeftToFrom);
9191  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(IsAlloc, AllocBB, AllocElseBB);
9192  // In case of alloc, clear OMP_MAP_TO and OMP_MAP_FROM.
9193  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(AllocBB);
9194  llvm::Value *AllocMapType = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
9195  MemberMapType,
9196  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9197  ~static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9198  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO |
9199  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM)));
9200  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateBr(EndBB);
9201  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(AllocElseBB);
9202  llvm::Value *IsTo = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateICmpEQ(
9203  LeftToFrom,
9204  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9205  static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9206  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO)));
9207  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(IsTo, ToBB, ToElseBB);
9208  // In case of to, clear OMP_MAP_FROM.
9209  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(ToBB);
9210  llvm::Value *ToMapType = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
9211  MemberMapType,
9212  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9213  ~static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9214  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM)));
9215  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateBr(EndBB);
9216  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(ToElseBB);
9217  llvm::Value *IsFrom = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateICmpEQ(
9218  LeftToFrom,
