9219  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9220  static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9221  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM)));
9222  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(IsFrom, FromBB, EndBB);
9223  // In case of from, clear OMP_MAP_TO.
9224  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(FromBB);
9225  llvm::Value *FromMapType = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
9226  MemberMapType,
9227  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9228  ~static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9229  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO)));
9230  // In case of tofrom, do nothing.
9231  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(EndBB);
9232  LastBB = EndBB;
9233  llvm::PHINode *CurMapType =
9234  MapperCGF.Builder.CreatePHI(CGM.Int64Ty, 4, "omp.maptype");
9235  CurMapType->addIncoming(AllocMapType, AllocBB);
9236  CurMapType->addIncoming(ToMapType, ToBB);
9237  CurMapType->addIncoming(FromMapType, FromBB);
9238  CurMapType->addIncoming(MemberMapType, ToElseBB);
9239 
9240  llvm::Value *OffloadingArgs[] = {Handle, CurBaseArg, CurBeginArg,
9241  CurSizeArg, CurMapType, CurNameArg};
9242  if (Info.Mappers[I]) {
9243  // Call the corresponding mapper function.
9244  llvm::Function *MapperFunc = getOrCreateUserDefinedMapperFunc(
9245  cast<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(Info.Mappers[I]));
9246  assert(MapperFunc && "Expect a valid mapper function is available.");
9247  MapperCGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(MapperFunc, OffloadingArgs);
9248  } else {
9249  // Call the runtime API __tgt_push_mapper_component to fill up the runtime
9250  // data structure.
9251  MapperCGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
9252  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
9253  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___tgt_push_mapper_component),
9254  OffloadingArgs);
9255  }
9256  }
9257 
9258  // Update the pointer to point to the next element that needs to be mapped,
9259  // and check whether we have mapped all elements.
9260  llvm::Value *PtrNext = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP1_32(
9261  ElemTy, PtrPHI, /*Idx0=*/1, "omp.arraymap.next");
9262  PtrPHI->addIncoming(PtrNext, LastBB);
9263  llvm::Value *IsDone =
9264  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateICmpEQ(PtrNext, PtrEnd, "omp.arraymap.isdone");
9265  llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB = MapperCGF.createBasicBlock("omp.arraymap.exit");
9266  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(IsDone, ExitBB, BodyBB);
9267 
9268  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB);
9269  // Emit array deletion if this is an array section and \p MapType indicates
9270  // that deletion is required.
9271  emitUDMapperArrayInitOrDel(MapperCGF, Handle, BaseIn, BeginIn, Size, MapType,
9272  MapName, ElementSize, DoneBB, /*IsInit=*/false);
9273 
9274  // Emit the function exit block.
9275  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(DoneBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
9276  MapperCGF.FinishFunction();
9277  UDMMap.try_emplace(D, Fn);
9278  if (CGF) {
9279  auto &Decls = FunctionUDMMap.FindAndConstruct(CGF->CurFn);
9280  Decls.second.push_back(D);
9281  }
9282 }
9283 
9284 /// Emit the array initialization or deletion portion for user-defined mapper
9285 /// code generation. First, it evaluates whether an array section is mapped and
9286 /// whether the \a MapType instructs to delete this section. If \a IsInit is
9287 /// true, and \a MapType indicates to not delete this array, array
9288 /// initialization code is generated. If \a IsInit is false, and \a MapType
9289 /// indicates to not this array, array deletion code is generated.
9290 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitUDMapperArrayInitOrDel(
9291  CodeGenFunction &MapperCGF, llvm::Value *Handle, llvm::Value *Base,
9292  llvm::Value *Begin, llvm::Value *Size, llvm::Value *MapType,
9293  llvm::Value *MapName, CharUnits ElementSize, llvm::BasicBlock *ExitBB,
9294  bool IsInit) {
9295  StringRef Prefix = IsInit ? ".init" : ".del";
9296 
9297  // Evaluate if this is an array section.
9298  llvm::BasicBlock *BodyBB =
9299  MapperCGF.createBasicBlock(getName({"omp.array", Prefix}));
9300  llvm::Value *IsArray = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateICmpSGT(
9301  Size, MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(1), "omp.arrayinit.isarray");
9302  llvm::Value *DeleteBit = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
9303  MapType,
9304  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9305  static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9306  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_DELETE)));
9307  llvm::Value *DeleteCond;
9308  llvm::Value *Cond;
9309  if (IsInit) {
9310  // base != begin?
9311  llvm::Value *BaseIsBegin = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateICmpNE(Base, Begin);
9312  // IsPtrAndObj?
9313  llvm::Value *PtrAndObjBit = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
9314  MapType,
9315  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9316  static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9317  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_PTR_AND_OBJ)));
9318  PtrAndObjBit = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateIsNotNull(PtrAndObjBit);
9319  BaseIsBegin = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(BaseIsBegin, PtrAndObjBit);
9320  Cond = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateOr(IsArray, BaseIsBegin);
9321  DeleteCond = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(
9322  DeleteBit, getName({"omp.array", Prefix, ".delete"}));
9323  } else {
9324  Cond = IsArray;
9325  DeleteCond = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateIsNotNull(
9326  DeleteBit, getName({"omp.array", Prefix, ".delete"}));
9327  }
9328  Cond = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(Cond, DeleteCond);
9329  MapperCGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Cond, BodyBB, ExitBB);
9330 
9331  MapperCGF.EmitBlock(BodyBB);
9332  // Get the array size by multiplying element size and element number (i.e., \p
9333  // Size).
9334  llvm::Value *ArraySize = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(
9335  Size, MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(ElementSize.getQuantity()));
9336  // Remove OMP_MAP_TO and OMP_MAP_FROM from the map type, so that it achieves
9337  // memory allocation/deletion purpose only.
9338  llvm::Value *MapTypeArg = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateAnd(
9339  MapType,
9340  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9341  ~static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9342  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TO |
9343  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_FROM)));
9344  MapTypeArg = MapperCGF.Builder.CreateOr(
9345  MapTypeArg,
9346  MapperCGF.Builder.getInt64(
9347  static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags>>(
9348  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_IMPLICIT)));
9349 
9350  // Call the runtime API __tgt_push_mapper_component to fill up the runtime
9351  // data structure.
9352  llvm::Value *OffloadingArgs[] = {Handle, Base, Begin,
9353  ArraySize, MapTypeArg, MapName};
9354  MapperCGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
9355  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(CGM.getModule(),
9356  OMPRTL___tgt_push_mapper_component),
9357  OffloadingArgs);
9358 }
9359 
9360 llvm::Function *CGOpenMPRuntime::getOrCreateUserDefinedMapperFunc(
9361  const OMPDeclareMapperDecl *D) {
9362  auto I = UDMMap.find(D);
9363  if (I != UDMMap.end())
9364  return I->second;
9365  emitUserDefinedMapper(D);
9366  return UDMMap.lookup(D);
9367 }
9368 
9369 llvm::Value *CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetNumIterationsCall(
9370  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D,
9371  llvm::function_ref<llvm::Value *(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9372  const OMPLoopDirective &D)>
9373  SizeEmitter) {
9374  OpenMPDirectiveKind Kind = D.getDirectiveKind();
9375  const OMPExecutableDirective *TD = &D;
9376  // Get nested teams distribute kind directive, if any. For now, treat
9377  // 'target_teams_loop' as if it's really a target_teams_distribute.
9378  if ((!isOpenMPDistributeDirective(Kind) || !isOpenMPTeamsDirective(Kind)) &&
9379  Kind != OMPD_target_teams_loop)
9380  TD = getNestedDistributeDirective(CGM.getContext(), D);
9381  if (!TD)
9382  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, 0);
9383 
9384  const auto *LD = cast<OMPLoopDirective>(TD);
9385  if (llvm::Value *NumIterations = SizeEmitter(CGF, *LD))
9386  return NumIterations;
9387  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, 0);
9388 }
9389 
9390 static void
9391 emitTargetCallFallback(CGOpenMPRuntime *OMPRuntime, llvm::Function *OutlinedFn,
9392  const OMPExecutableDirective &D,
9393  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Value *> &CapturedVars,
9394  bool RequiresOuterTask, const CapturedStmt &CS,
9395  bool OffloadingMandatory, CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
9396  if (OffloadingMandatory) {
9397  CGF.Builder.CreateUnreachable();
9398  } else {
9399  if (RequiresOuterTask) {
9400  CapturedVars.clear();
9401  CGF.GenerateOpenMPCapturedVars(CS, CapturedVars);
9402  }
9403  OMPRuntime->emitOutlinedFunctionCall(CGF, D.getBeginLoc(), OutlinedFn,
9404  CapturedVars);
9405  }
9406 }
9407 
9408 static llvm::Value *emitDeviceID(
9409  llvm::PointerIntPair<const Expr *, 2, OpenMPDeviceClauseModifier> Device,
9410  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
9411  // Emit device ID if any.
9412  llvm::Value *DeviceID;
9413  if (Device.getPointer()) {
9414  assert((Device.getInt() == OMPC_DEVICE_unknown ||
9415  Device.getInt() == OMPC_DEVICE_device_num) &&
9416  "Expected device_num modifier.");
9417  llvm::Value *DevVal = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(Device.getPointer());
9418  DeviceID =
9419  CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(DevVal, CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true);
9420  } else {
9421  DeviceID = CGF.Builder.getInt64(OMP_DEVICEID_UNDEF);
9422  }
9423  return DeviceID;
9424 }
9425 
9426 llvm::Value *emitDynCGGroupMem(const OMPExecutableDirective &D,
9427  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
9428  llvm::Value *DynCGroupMem = CGF.Builder.getInt32(0);
9429 
9430  if (auto *DynMemClause = D.getSingleClause<OMPXDynCGroupMemClause>()) {
9431  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope DynCGroupMemScope(CGF);
9432  llvm::Value *DynCGroupMemVal = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(
9433  DynMemClause->getSize(), /*IgnoreResultAssign=*/true);
9434  DynCGroupMem = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(DynCGroupMemVal, CGF.Int32Ty,
9435  /*isSigned=*/false);
9436  }
9437  return DynCGroupMem;
9438 }
9439 
9440 static void emitTargetCallKernelLaunch(
9441  CGOpenMPRuntime *OMPRuntime, llvm::Function *OutlinedFn,
9442  const OMPExecutableDirective &D,
9443  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Value *> &CapturedVars, bool RequiresOuterTask,
9444  const CapturedStmt &CS, bool OffloadingMandatory,
9445  llvm::PointerIntPair<const Expr *, 2, OpenMPDeviceClauseModifier> Device,
9446  llvm::Value *OutlinedFnID, CodeGenFunction::OMPTargetDataInfo &InputInfo,
9447  llvm::Value *&MapTypesArray, llvm::Value *&MapNamesArray,
9448  llvm::function_ref<llvm::Value *(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9449  const OMPLoopDirective &D)>
9450  SizeEmitter,
9451  CodeGenFunction &CGF, CodeGenModule &CGM) {
9452  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder = OMPRuntime->getOMPBuilder();
9453 
9454  // Fill up the arrays with all the captured variables.
9455  MappableExprsHandler::MapCombinedInfoTy CombinedInfo;
9456 
9457  // Get mappable expression information.
9458  MappableExprsHandler MEHandler(D, CGF);
9459  llvm::DenseMap<llvm::Value *, llvm::Value *> LambdaPointers;
9460  llvm::DenseSet<CanonicalDeclPtr<const Decl>> MappedVarSet;
9461 
9462  auto RI = CS.getCapturedRecordDecl()->field_begin();
9463  auto *CV = CapturedVars.begin();
9464  for (CapturedStmt::const_capture_iterator CI = CS.capture_begin(),
9465  CE = CS.capture_end();
9466  CI != CE; ++CI, ++RI, ++CV) {
9467  MappableExprsHandler::MapCombinedInfoTy CurInfo;
9468  MappableExprsHandler::StructRangeInfoTy PartialStruct;
9469 
9470  // VLA sizes are passed to the outlined region by copy and do not have map
9471  // information associated.
9472  if (CI->capturesVariableArrayType()) {
9473  CurInfo.Exprs.push_back(nullptr);
9474  CurInfo.BasePointers.push_back(*CV);
9475  CurInfo.DevicePtrDecls.push_back(nullptr);
9476  CurInfo.DevicePointers.push_back(
9477  MappableExprsHandler::DeviceInfoTy::None);
9478  CurInfo.Pointers.push_back(*CV);
9479  CurInfo.Sizes.push_back(CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(
9480  CGF.getTypeSize(RI->getType()), CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true));
9481  // Copy to the device as an argument. No need to retrieve it.
9482  CurInfo.Types.push_back(OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_LITERAL |
9483  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_TARGET_PARAM |
9484  OpenMPOffloadMappingFlags::OMP_MAP_IMPLICIT);
9485  CurInfo.Mappers.push_back(nullptr);
9486  } else {
9487  // If we have any information in the map clause, we use it, otherwise we
9488  // just do a default mapping.
9489  MEHandler.generateInfoForCapture(CI, *CV, CurInfo, PartialStruct);
9490  if (!CI->capturesThis())
9491  MappedVarSet.insert(CI->getCapturedVar());
9492  else
9493  MappedVarSet.insert(nullptr);
9494  if (CurInfo.BasePointers.empty() && !PartialStruct.Base.isValid())
9495  MEHandler.generateDefaultMapInfo(*CI, **RI, *CV, CurInfo);
9496  // Generate correct mapping for variables captured by reference in
9497  // lambdas.
9498  if (CI->capturesVariable())
9499  MEHandler.generateInfoForLambdaCaptures(CI->getCapturedVar(), *CV,
9500  CurInfo, LambdaPointers);
9501  }
9502  // We expect to have at least an element of information for this capture.
9503  assert((!CurInfo.BasePointers.empty() || PartialStruct.Base.isValid()) &&
9504  "Non-existing map pointer for capture!");
9505  assert(CurInfo.BasePointers.size() == CurInfo.Pointers.size() &&
9506  CurInfo.BasePointers.size() == CurInfo.Sizes.size() &&
9507  CurInfo.BasePointers.size() == CurInfo.Types.size() &&
9508  CurInfo.BasePointers.size() == CurInfo.Mappers.size() &&
9509  "Inconsistent map information sizes!");
9510 
9511  // If there is an entry in PartialStruct it means we have a struct with
9512  // individual members mapped. Emit an extra combined entry.
9513  if (PartialStruct.Base.isValid()) {
9514  CombinedInfo.append(PartialStruct.PreliminaryMapData);
9515  MEHandler.emitCombinedEntry(
9516  CombinedInfo, CurInfo.Types, PartialStruct, CI->capturesThis(),
9517  OMPBuilder, nullptr,
9518  !PartialStruct.PreliminaryMapData.BasePointers.empty());
9519  }
9520 
9521  // We need to append the results of this capture to what we already have.
9522  CombinedInfo.append(CurInfo);
9523  }
9524  // Adjust MEMBER_OF flags for the lambdas captures.
9525  MEHandler.adjustMemberOfForLambdaCaptures(
9526  OMPBuilder, LambdaPointers, CombinedInfo.BasePointers,
9527  CombinedInfo.Pointers, CombinedInfo.Types);
9528  // Map any list items in a map clause that were not captures because they
9529  // weren't referenced within the construct.
9530  MEHandler.generateAllInfo(CombinedInfo, OMPBuilder, MappedVarSet);
9531 
9532  CGOpenMPRuntime::TargetDataInfo Info;
9533  // Fill up the arrays and create the arguments.
9534  emitOffloadingArrays(CGF, CombinedInfo, Info, OMPBuilder);
9535  bool EmitDebug = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() !=
9536  llvm::codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo;
9537  OMPBuilder.emitOffloadingArraysArgument(CGF.Builder, Info.RTArgs, Info,
9538  EmitDebug,
9539  /*ForEndCall=*/false);
9540 
9541  InputInfo.NumberOfTargetItems = Info.NumberOfPtrs;
9542  InputInfo.BasePointersArray = Address(Info.RTArgs.BasePointersArray,
9543  CGF.VoidPtrTy, CGM.getPointerAlign());
9544  InputInfo.PointersArray =
9545  Address(Info.RTArgs.PointersArray, CGF.VoidPtrTy, CGM.getPointerAlign());
9546  InputInfo.SizesArray =
9547  Address(Info.RTArgs.SizesArray, CGF.Int64Ty, CGM.getPointerAlign());
9548  InputInfo.MappersArray =
9549  Address(Info.RTArgs.MappersArray, CGF.VoidPtrTy, CGM.getPointerAlign());
9550  MapTypesArray = Info.RTArgs.MapTypesArray;
9551  MapNamesArray = Info.RTArgs.MapNamesArray;
9552 
9553  auto &&ThenGen = [&OMPRuntime, OutlinedFn, &D, &CapturedVars,
9554  RequiresOuterTask, &CS, OffloadingMandatory, Device,
9555  OutlinedFnID, &InputInfo, &MapTypesArray, &MapNamesArray,
9556  SizeEmitter](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &) {
9557  bool IsReverseOffloading = Device.getInt() == OMPC_DEVICE_ancestor;
9558 
9559  if (IsReverseOffloading) {
9560  // Reverse offloading is not supported, so just execute on the host.
9561  // FIXME: This fallback solution is incorrect since it ignores the
9562  // OMP_TARGET_OFFLOAD environment variable. Instead it would be better to
9563  // assert here and ensure SEMA emits an error.
9564  emitTargetCallFallback(OMPRuntime, OutlinedFn, D, CapturedVars,
9565  RequiresOuterTask, CS, OffloadingMandatory, CGF);
9566  return;
9567  }
9568 
9569  bool HasNoWait = D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPNowaitClause>();
9570  unsigned NumTargetItems = InputInfo.NumberOfTargetItems;
9571 
9572  llvm::Value *BasePointersArray =
9573  InputInfo.BasePointersArray.emitRawPointer(CGF);
9574  llvm::Value *PointersArray = InputInfo.PointersArray.emitRawPointer(CGF);
9575  llvm::Value *SizesArray = InputInfo.SizesArray.emitRawPointer(CGF);
9576  llvm::Value *MappersArray = InputInfo.MappersArray.emitRawPointer(CGF);
9577 
9578  auto &&EmitTargetCallFallbackCB =
9579  [&OMPRuntime, OutlinedFn, &D, &CapturedVars, RequiresOuterTask, &CS,
9580  OffloadingMandatory, &CGF](llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy IP)
9581  -> llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy {
9582  CGF.Builder.restoreIP(IP);
9583  emitTargetCallFallback(OMPRuntime, OutlinedFn, D, CapturedVars,
9584  RequiresOuterTask, CS, OffloadingMandatory, CGF);
9585  return CGF.Builder.saveIP();
9586  };
9587 
9588  llvm::Value *DeviceID = emitDeviceID(Device, CGF);
9589  llvm::Value *NumTeams = OMPRuntime->emitNumTeamsForTargetDirective(CGF, D);
9590  llvm::Value *NumThreads =
9591  OMPRuntime->emitNumThreadsForTargetDirective(CGF, D);
9592  llvm::Value *RTLoc = OMPRuntime->emitUpdateLocation(CGF, D.getBeginLoc());
9593  llvm::Value *NumIterations =
9594  OMPRuntime->emitTargetNumIterationsCall(CGF, D, SizeEmitter);
9595  llvm::Value *DynCGGroupMem = emitDynCGGroupMem(D, CGF);
9596  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy AllocaIP(
9597  CGF.AllocaInsertPt->getParent(), CGF.AllocaInsertPt->getIterator());
9598 
9599  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::TargetDataRTArgs RTArgs(
9600  BasePointersArray, PointersArray, SizesArray, MapTypesArray,
9601  nullptr /* MapTypesArrayEnd */, MappersArray, MapNamesArray);
9602 
9603  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::TargetKernelArgs Args(
9604  NumTargetItems, RTArgs, NumIterations, NumTeams, NumThreads,
9605  DynCGGroupMem, HasNoWait);
9606 
9607  CGF.Builder.restoreIP(OMPRuntime->getOMPBuilder().emitKernelLaunch(
9608  CGF.Builder, OutlinedFn, OutlinedFnID, EmitTargetCallFallbackCB, Args,
9609  DeviceID, RTLoc, AllocaIP));
9610  };
9611 
9612  if (RequiresOuterTask)
9613  CGF.EmitOMPTargetTaskBasedDirective(D, ThenGen, InputInfo);
9614  else
9615  OMPRuntime->emitInlinedDirective(CGF, D.getDirectiveKind(), ThenGen);
9616 }
9617 
9618 static void
9619 emitTargetCallElse(CGOpenMPRuntime *OMPRuntime, llvm::Function *OutlinedFn,
9620  const OMPExecutableDirective &D,
9621  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<llvm::Value *> &CapturedVars,
9622  bool RequiresOuterTask, const CapturedStmt &CS,
9623  bool OffloadingMandatory, CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
9624 
9625  // Notify that the host version must be executed.
9626  auto &&ElseGen =
9627  [&OMPRuntime, OutlinedFn, &D, &CapturedVars, RequiresOuterTask, &CS,
9628  OffloadingMandatory](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &) {
9629  emitTargetCallFallback(OMPRuntime, OutlinedFn, D, CapturedVars,
9630  RequiresOuterTask, CS, OffloadingMandatory, CGF);
9631  };
9632 
9633  if (RequiresOuterTask) {
9634  CodeGenFunction::OMPTargetDataInfo InputInfo;
9635  CGF.EmitOMPTargetTaskBasedDirective(D, ElseGen, InputInfo);
9636  } else {
9637  OMPRuntime->emitInlinedDirective(CGF, D.getDirectiveKind(), ElseGen);
9638  }
9639 }
9640 
9641 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetCall(
9642  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D,
9643  llvm::Function *OutlinedFn, llvm::Value *OutlinedFnID, const Expr *IfCond,
9644  llvm::PointerIntPair<const Expr *, 2, OpenMPDeviceClauseModifier> Device,
9645  llvm::function_ref<llvm::Value *(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9646  const OMPLoopDirective &D)>
9647  SizeEmitter) {
9648  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
9649  return;
9650 
9651  const bool OffloadingMandatory = !CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice &&
9652  CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPOffloadMandatory;
9653 
9654  assert((OffloadingMandatory || OutlinedFn) && "Invalid outlined function!");
9655 
9656  const bool RequiresOuterTask =
9657  D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPDependClause>() ||
9658  D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPNowaitClause>() ||
9659  D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPInReductionClause>() ||
9660  (CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMP >= 51 &&
9661  needsTaskBasedThreadLimit(D.getDirectiveKind()) &&
9662  D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPThreadLimitClause>());
9663  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 16> CapturedVars;
9664  const CapturedStmt &CS = *D.getCapturedStmt(OMPD_target);
9665  auto &&ArgsCodegen = [&CS, &CapturedVars](CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9666  PrePostActionTy &) {
9667  CGF.GenerateOpenMPCapturedVars(CS, CapturedVars);
9668  };
9669  emitInlinedDirective(CGF, OMPD_unknown, ArgsCodegen);
9670 
9671  CodeGenFunction::OMPTargetDataInfo InputInfo;
9672  llvm::Value *MapTypesArray = nullptr;
9673  llvm::Value *MapNamesArray = nullptr;
9674 
9675  auto &&TargetThenGen = [this, OutlinedFn, &D, &CapturedVars,
9676  RequiresOuterTask, &CS, OffloadingMandatory, Device,
9677  OutlinedFnID, &InputInfo, &MapTypesArray,
9678  &MapNamesArray, SizeEmitter](CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9679  PrePostActionTy &) {
9680  emitTargetCallKernelLaunch(this, OutlinedFn, D, CapturedVars,
9681  RequiresOuterTask, CS, OffloadingMandatory,
9682  Device, OutlinedFnID, InputInfo, MapTypesArray,
9683  MapNamesArray, SizeEmitter, CGF, CGM);
9684  };
9685 
9686  auto &&TargetElseGen =
9687  [this, OutlinedFn, &D, &CapturedVars, RequiresOuterTask, &CS,
9688  OffloadingMandatory](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &) {
9689  emitTargetCallElse(this, OutlinedFn, D, CapturedVars, RequiresOuterTask,
9690  CS, OffloadingMandatory, CGF);
9691  };
9692 
9693  // If we have a target function ID it means that we need to support
9694  // offloading, otherwise, just execute on the host. We need to execute on host
9695  // regardless of the conditional in the if clause if, e.g., the user do not
9696  // specify target triples.
9697  if (OutlinedFnID) {
9698  if (IfCond) {
9699  emitIfClause(CGF, IfCond, TargetThenGen, TargetElseGen);
9700  } else {
9701  RegionCodeGenTy ThenRCG(TargetThenGen);
9702  ThenRCG(CGF);
9703  }
9704  } else {
9705  RegionCodeGenTy ElseRCG(TargetElseGen);
9706  ElseRCG(CGF);
9707  }
9708 }
9709 
9710 void CGOpenMPRuntime::scanForTargetRegionsFunctions(const Stmt *S,
9711  StringRef ParentName) {
9712  if (!S)
9713  return;
9714 
9715  // Codegen OMP target directives that offload compute to the device.
9716  bool RequiresDeviceCodegen =
9717  isa<OMPExecutableDirective>(S) &&
9718  isOpenMPTargetExecutionDirective(
9719  cast<OMPExecutableDirective>(S)->getDirectiveKind());
9720 
9721  if (RequiresDeviceCodegen) {
9722  const auto &E = *cast<OMPExecutableDirective>(S);
9723 
9724  llvm::TargetRegionEntryInfo EntryInfo = getEntryInfoFromPresumedLoc(
9725  CGM, OMPBuilder, E.getBeginLoc(), ParentName);
9726 
9727  // Is this a target region that should not be emitted as an entry point? If
9728  // so just signal we are done with this target region.
9729  if (!OMPBuilder.OffloadInfoManager.hasTargetRegionEntryInfo(EntryInfo))
9730  return;
9731 
9732  switch (E.getDirectiveKind()) {
9733  case OMPD_target:
9734  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetDeviceFunction(CGM, ParentName,
9735  cast<OMPTargetDirective>(E));
9736  break;
9737  case OMPD_target_parallel:
9738  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetParallelDeviceFunction(
9739  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetParallelDirective>(E));
9740  break;
9741  case OMPD_target_teams:
9742  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetTeamsDeviceFunction(
9743  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetTeamsDirective>(E));
9744  break;
9745  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute:
9746  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetTeamsDistributeDeviceFunction(
9747  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetTeamsDistributeDirective>(E));
9748  break;
9749  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_simd:
9750  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetTeamsDistributeSimdDeviceFunction(
9751  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetTeamsDistributeSimdDirective>(E));
9752  break;
9753  case OMPD_target_parallel_for:
9754  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetParallelForDeviceFunction(
9755  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetParallelForDirective>(E));
9756  break;
9757  case OMPD_target_parallel_for_simd:
9758  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetParallelForSimdDeviceFunction(
9759  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetParallelForSimdDirective>(E));
9760  break;
9761  case OMPD_target_simd:
9762  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetSimdDeviceFunction(
9763  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetSimdDirective>(E));
9764  break;
9765  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
9766  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetTeamsDistributeParallelForDeviceFunction(
9767  CGM, ParentName,
9768  cast<OMPTargetTeamsDistributeParallelForDirective>(E));
9769  break;
9770  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
9771  CodeGenFunction::
9772  EmitOMPTargetTeamsDistributeParallelForSimdDeviceFunction(
9773  CGM, ParentName,
9774  cast<OMPTargetTeamsDistributeParallelForSimdDirective>(E));
9775  break;
9776  case OMPD_target_teams_loop:
9777  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetTeamsGenericLoopDeviceFunction(
9778  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetTeamsGenericLoopDirective>(E));
9779  break;
9780  case OMPD_target_parallel_loop:
9781  CodeGenFunction::EmitOMPTargetParallelGenericLoopDeviceFunction(
9782  CGM, ParentName, cast<OMPTargetParallelGenericLoopDirective>(E));
9783  break;
9784  case OMPD_parallel:
9785  case OMPD_for:
9786  case OMPD_parallel_for:
9787  case OMPD_parallel_master:
9788  case OMPD_parallel_sections:
9789  case OMPD_for_simd:
9790  case OMPD_parallel_for_simd:
9791  case OMPD_cancel:
9792  case OMPD_cancellation_point:
9793  case OMPD_ordered:
9794  case OMPD_threadprivate:
9795  case OMPD_allocate:
9796  case OMPD_task:
9797  case OMPD_simd:
9798  case OMPD_tile:
9799  case OMPD_unroll:
9800  case OMPD_sections:
9801  case OMPD_section:
9802  case OMPD_single:
9803  case OMPD_master:
9804  case OMPD_critical:
9805  case OMPD_taskyield:
9806  case OMPD_barrier:
9807  case OMPD_taskwait:
9808  case OMPD_taskgroup:
9809  case OMPD_atomic:
9810  case OMPD_flush:
9811  case OMPD_depobj:
9812  case OMPD_scan:
9813  case OMPD_teams:
9814  case OMPD_target_data:
9815  case OMPD_target_exit_data:
9816  case OMPD_target_enter_data:
9817  case OMPD_distribute:
9818  case OMPD_distribute_simd:
9819  case OMPD_distribute_parallel_for:
9820  case OMPD_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
9821  case OMPD_teams_distribute:
9822  case OMPD_teams_distribute_simd:
9823  case OMPD_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
9824  case OMPD_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
9825  case OMPD_target_update:
9826  case OMPD_declare_simd:
9827  case OMPD_declare_variant:
9828  case OMPD_begin_declare_variant:
9829  case OMPD_end_declare_variant:
9830  case OMPD_declare_target:
9831  case OMPD_end_declare_target:
9832  case OMPD_declare_reduction:
9833  case OMPD_declare_mapper:
9834  case OMPD_taskloop:
9835  case OMPD_taskloop_simd:
9836  case OMPD_master_taskloop:
9837  case OMPD_master_taskloop_simd:
9838  case OMPD_parallel_master_taskloop:
9839  case OMPD_parallel_master_taskloop_simd:
9840  case OMPD_requires:
9841  case OMPD_metadirective:
9842  case OMPD_unknown:
9843  default:
9844  llvm_unreachable("Unknown target directive for OpenMP device codegen.");
9845  }
9846  return;
9847  }
9848 
9849  if (const auto *E = dyn_cast<OMPExecutableDirective>(S)) {
9850  if (!E->hasAssociatedStmt() || !E->getAssociatedStmt())
9851  return;
9852 
9853  scanForTargetRegionsFunctions(E->getRawStmt(), ParentName);
9854  return;
9855  }
9856 
9857  // If this is a lambda function, look into its body.
9858  if (const auto *L = dyn_cast<LambdaExpr>(S))
9859  S = L->getBody();
9860 
9861  // Keep looking for target regions recursively.
9862  for (const Stmt *II : S->children())
9863  scanForTargetRegionsFunctions(II, ParentName);
9864 }
9865 
9866 static bool isAssumedToBeNotEmitted(const ValueDecl *VD, bool IsDevice) {
9867  std::optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::DevTypeTy> DevTy =
9868  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::getDeviceType(VD);
9869  if (!DevTy)
9870  return false;
9871  // Do not emit device_type(nohost) functions for the host.
9872  if (!IsDevice && DevTy == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::DT_NoHost)
9873  return true;
9874  // Do not emit device_type(host) functions for the device.
9875  if (IsDevice && DevTy == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::DT_Host)
9876  return true;
9877  return false;
9878 }
9879 
9880 bool CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetFunctions(GlobalDecl GD) {
9881  // If emitting code for the host, we do not process FD here. Instead we do
9882  // the normal code generation.
9883  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice) {
9884  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl()))
9885  if (isAssumedToBeNotEmitted(cast<ValueDecl>(FD),
9886  CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice))
9887  return true;
9888  return false;
9889  }
9890 
9891  const ValueDecl *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
9892  // Try to detect target regions in the function.
9893  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(VD)) {
9894  StringRef Name = CGM.getMangledName(GD);
9895  scanForTargetRegionsFunctions(FD->getBody(), Name);
9896  if (isAssumedToBeNotEmitted(cast<ValueDecl>(FD),
9897  CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice))
9898  return true;
9899  }
9900 
9901  // Do not to emit function if it is not marked as declare target.
9902  return !OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD) &&
9903  AlreadyEmittedTargetDecls.count(VD) == 0;
9904 }
9905 
9906 bool CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetGlobalVariable(GlobalDecl GD) {
9907  if (isAssumedToBeNotEmitted(cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl()),
9908  CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice))
9909  return true;
9910 
9911  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice)
9912  return false;
9913 
9914  // Check if there are Ctors/Dtors in this declaration and look for target
9915  // regions in it. We use the complete variant to produce the kernel name
9916  // mangling.
9917  QualType RDTy = cast<VarDecl>(GD.getDecl())->getType();
9918  if (const auto *RD = RDTy->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
9919  for (const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor : RD->ctors()) {
9920  StringRef ParentName =
9921  CGM.getMangledName(GlobalDecl(Ctor, Ctor_Complete));
9922  scanForTargetRegionsFunctions(Ctor->getBody(), ParentName);
9923  }
9924  if (const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = RD->getDestructor()) {
9925  StringRef ParentName =
9926  CGM.getMangledName(GlobalDecl(Dtor, Dtor_Complete));
9927  scanForTargetRegionsFunctions(Dtor->getBody(), ParentName);
9928  }
9929  }
9930 
9931  // Do not to emit variable if it is not marked as declare target.
9932  std::optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MapTypeTy> Res =
9933  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(
9934  cast<VarDecl>(GD.getDecl()));
9935  if (!Res || *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link ||
9936  ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To ||
9937  *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Enter) &&
9938  HasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory)) {
9939  DeferredGlobalVariables.insert(cast<VarDecl>(GD.getDecl()));
9940  return true;
9941  }
9942  return false;
9943 }
9944 
9945 void CGOpenMPRuntime::registerTargetGlobalVariable(const VarDecl *VD,
9946  llvm::Constant *Addr) {
9947  if (CGM.getLangOpts().OMPTargetTriples.empty() &&
9948  !CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice)
9949  return;
9950 
9951  std::optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MapTypeTy> Res =
9952  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD);
9953 
9954  // If this is an 'extern' declaration we defer to the canonical definition and
9955  // do not emit an offloading entry.
9956  if (Res && *Res != OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link &&
9957  VD->hasExternalStorage())
9958  return;
9959 
9960  if (!Res) {
9961  if (CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice) {
9962  // Register non-target variables being emitted in device code (debug info
9963  // may cause this).
9964  StringRef VarName = CGM.getMangledName(VD);
9965  EmittedNonTargetVariables.try_emplace(VarName, Addr);
9966  }
9967  return;
9968  }
9969 
9970  auto AddrOfGlobal = [&VD, this]() { return CGM.GetAddrOfGlobal(VD); };
9971  auto LinkageForVariable = [&VD, this]() {
9972  return CGM.getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD);
9973  };
9974 
9975  std::vector<llvm::GlobalVariable *> GeneratedRefs;
9976  OMPBuilder.registerTargetGlobalVariable(
9977  convertCaptureClause(VD), convertDeviceClause(VD),
9978  VD->hasDefinition(CGM.getContext()) == VarDecl::DeclarationOnly,
9979  VD->isExternallyVisible(),
9980  getEntryInfoFromPresumedLoc(CGM, OMPBuilder,
9981  VD->getCanonicalDecl()->getBeginLoc()),
9982  CGM.getMangledName(VD), GeneratedRefs, CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd,
9983  CGM.getLangOpts().OMPTargetTriples, AddrOfGlobal, LinkageForVariable,
9984  CGM.getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(
9985  CGM.getContext().getPointerType(VD->getType())),
9986  Addr);
9987 
9988  for (auto *ref : GeneratedRefs)
9989  CGM.addCompilerUsedGlobal(ref);
9990 }
9991 
9992 bool CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetGlobal(GlobalDecl GD) {
9993  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl()) ||
9994  isa<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(GD.getDecl()))
9995  return emitTargetFunctions(GD);
9996 
9997  return emitTargetGlobalVariable(GD);
9998 }
9999 
10000 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitDeferredTargetDecls() const {
10001  for (const VarDecl *VD : DeferredGlobalVariables) {
10002  std::optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MapTypeTy> Res =
10003  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD);
10004  if (!Res)
10005  continue;
10006  if ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To ||
10007  *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Enter) &&
10008  !HasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory) {
10009  CGM.EmitGlobal(VD);
10010  } else {
10011  assert((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link ||
10012  ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To ||
10013  *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Enter) &&
10014  HasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory)) &&
10015  "Expected link clause or to clause with unified memory.");
10016  (void)CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfDeclareTargetVar(VD);
10017  }
10018  }
10019 }
10020 
10021 void CGOpenMPRuntime::adjustTargetSpecificDataForLambdas(
10022  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D) const {
10023  assert(isOpenMPTargetExecutionDirective(D.getDirectiveKind()) &&
10024  " Expected target-based directive.");
10025 }
10026 
10027 void CGOpenMPRuntime::processRequiresDirective(const OMPRequiresDecl *D) {
10028  for (const OMPClause *Clause : D->clauselists()) {
10029  if (Clause->getClauseKind() == OMPC_unified_shared_memory) {
10030  HasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory = true;
10031  OMPBuilder.Config.setHasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory(true);
10032  } else if (const auto *AC =
10033  dyn_cast<OMPAtomicDefaultMemOrderClause>(Clause)) {
10034  switch (AC->getAtomicDefaultMemOrderKind()) {
10035  case OMPC_ATOMIC_DEFAULT_MEM_ORDER_acq_rel:
10036  RequiresAtomicOrdering = llvm::AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease;
10037  break;
10038  case OMPC_ATOMIC_DEFAULT_MEM_ORDER_seq_cst:
10039  RequiresAtomicOrdering = llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent;
10040  break;
10041  case OMPC_ATOMIC_DEFAULT_MEM_ORDER_relaxed:
10042  RequiresAtomicOrdering = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic;
10043  break;
10044  case OMPC_ATOMIC_DEFAULT_MEM_ORDER_unknown:
10045  break;
10046  }
10047  }
10048  }
10049 }
10050 
10051 llvm::AtomicOrdering CGOpenMPRuntime::getDefaultMemoryOrdering() const {
10052  return RequiresAtomicOrdering;
10053 }
10054 
10055 bool CGOpenMPRuntime::hasAllocateAttributeForGlobalVar(const VarDecl *VD,
10056  LangAS &AS) {
10057  if (!VD || !VD->hasAttr<OMPAllocateDeclAttr>())
10058  return false;
10059  const auto *A = VD->getAttr<OMPAllocateDeclAttr>();
10060  switch(A->getAllocatorType()) {
10061  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPNullMemAlloc:
10062  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPDefaultMemAlloc:
10063  // Not supported, fallback to the default mem space.
10064  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPLargeCapMemAlloc:
10065  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPCGroupMemAlloc:
10066  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPHighBWMemAlloc:
10067  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPLowLatMemAlloc:
10068  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPThreadMemAlloc:
10069  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPConstMemAlloc:
10070  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPPTeamMemAlloc:
10071  AS = LangAS::Default;
10072  return true;
10073  case OMPAllocateDeclAttr::OMPUserDefinedMemAlloc:
10074  llvm_unreachable("Expected predefined allocator for the variables with the "
10075  "static storage.");
10076  }
10077  return false;
10078 }

10080 bool CGOpenMPRuntime::hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory() const {
10081  return HasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory;
10082 }

10085  CodeGenModule &CGM)

10089  CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().ShouldMarkAsGlobal = false;
10090  }

10096 }

10098 bool CGOpenMPRuntime::markAsGlobalTarget(GlobalDecl GD) {
10099  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice || !ShouldMarkAsGlobal)
10100  return true;
10101 
10102  const auto *D = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
10103  // Do not to emit function if it is marked as declare target as it was already
10104  // emitted.
10105  if (OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(D)) {
10106  if (D->hasBody() && AlreadyEmittedTargetDecls.count(D) == 0) {
10107  if (auto *F = dyn_cast_or_null<llvm::Function>(
10108  CGM.GetGlobalValue(CGM.getMangledName(GD))))
10109  return !F->isDeclaration();
10110  return false;
10111  }
10112  return true;
10113  }
10114 
10115  return !AlreadyEmittedTargetDecls.insert(D).second;
10116 }
10117 
10118 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTeamsCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
10119  const OMPExecutableDirective &D,
10120  SourceLocation Loc,
10121  llvm::Function *OutlinedFn,
10122  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> CapturedVars) {
10123  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
10124  return;
10125 
10126  llvm::Value *RTLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc);
10127  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope Scope(CGF);
10128 
10129  // Build call __kmpc_fork_teams(loc, n, microtask, var1, .., varn);
10130  llvm::Value *Args[] = {
10131  RTLoc,
10132  CGF.Builder.getInt32(CapturedVars.size()), // Number of captured vars
10133  CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(OutlinedFn, getKmpc_MicroPointerTy())};
10134  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 16> RealArgs;
10135  RealArgs.append(std::begin(Args), std::end(Args));
10136  RealArgs.append(CapturedVars.begin(), CapturedVars.end());
10137 
10138  llvm::FunctionCallee RTLFn = OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
10139  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_fork_teams);
10140  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(RTLFn, RealArgs);
10141 }
10142 
10143 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitNumTeamsClause(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
10144  const Expr *NumTeams,
10145  const Expr *ThreadLimit,
10146  SourceLocation Loc) {
10147  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
10148  return;
10149 
10150  llvm::Value *RTLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc);
10151 
10152  llvm::Value *NumTeamsVal =
10153  NumTeams
10154  ? CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(NumTeams),
10155  CGF.CGM.Int32Ty, /* isSigned = */ true)
10156  : CGF.Builder.getInt32(0);
10157 
10158  llvm::Value *ThreadLimitVal =
10159  ThreadLimit
10160  ? CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(ThreadLimit),
10161  CGF.CGM.Int32Ty, /* isSigned = */ true)
10162  : CGF.Builder.getInt32(0);
10163 
10164  // Build call __kmpc_push_num_teamss(&loc, global_tid, num_teams, thread_limit)
10165  llvm::Value *PushNumTeamsArgs[] = {RTLoc, getThreadID(CGF, Loc), NumTeamsVal,
10166  ThreadLimitVal};
10167  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
10168  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_push_num_teams),
10169  PushNumTeamsArgs);
10170 }
10171 
10172 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitThreadLimitClause(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
10173  const Expr *ThreadLimit,
10174  SourceLocation Loc) {
10175  llvm::Value *RTLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, Loc);
10176  llvm::Value *ThreadLimitVal =
10177  ThreadLimit
10178  ? CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(ThreadLimit),
10179  CGF.CGM.Int32Ty, /* isSigned = */ true)
10180  : CGF.Builder.getInt32(0);
10181 
10182  // Build call __kmpc_set_thread_limit(&loc, global_tid, thread_limit)
10183  llvm::Value *ThreadLimitArgs[] = {RTLoc, getThreadID(CGF, Loc),
10184  ThreadLimitVal};
10185  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
10186  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_set_thread_limit),
10187  ThreadLimitArgs);
10188 }
10189 
10190 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetDataCalls(
10191  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D, const Expr *IfCond,
10192  const Expr *Device, const RegionCodeGenTy &CodeGen,
10193  CGOpenMPRuntime::TargetDataInfo &Info) {
10194  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
10195  return;
10196 
10197  // Action used to replace the default codegen action and turn privatization
10198  // off.
10199  PrePostActionTy NoPrivAction;
10200 
10201  using InsertPointTy = llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::InsertPointTy;
10202 
10203  llvm::Value *IfCondVal = nullptr;
10204  if (IfCond)
10205  IfCondVal = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(IfCond);
10206 
10207  // Emit device ID if any.
10208  llvm::Value *DeviceID = nullptr;
10209  if (Device) {
10210  DeviceID = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(Device),
10211  CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true);
10212  } else {
10213  DeviceID = CGF.Builder.getInt64(OMP_DEVICEID_UNDEF);
10214  }
10215 
10216  // Fill up the arrays with all the mapped variables.
10217  MappableExprsHandler::MapCombinedInfoTy CombinedInfo;
10218  auto GenMapInfoCB =
10219  [&](InsertPointTy CodeGenIP) -> llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::MapInfosTy & {
10220  CGF.Builder.restoreIP(CodeGenIP);
10221  // Get map clause information.
10222  MappableExprsHandler MEHandler(D, CGF);
10223  MEHandler.generateAllInfo(CombinedInfo, OMPBuilder);
10224 
10225  auto FillInfoMap = [&](MappableExprsHandler::MappingExprInfo &MapExpr) {
10226  return emitMappingInformation(CGF, OMPBuilder, MapExpr);
10227  };
10228  if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() !=
10229  llvm::codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo) {
10230  CombinedInfo.Names.resize(CombinedInfo.Exprs.size());
10231  llvm::transform(CombinedInfo.Exprs, CombinedInfo.Names.begin(),
10232  FillInfoMap);
10233  }
10234 
10235  return CombinedInfo;
10236  };
10237  using BodyGenTy = llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::BodyGenTy;
10238  auto BodyCB = [&](InsertPointTy CodeGenIP, BodyGenTy BodyGenType) {
10239  CGF.Builder.restoreIP(CodeGenIP);
10240  switch (BodyGenType) {
10241  case BodyGenTy::Priv:
10242  if (!Info.CaptureDeviceAddrMap.empty())
10243  CodeGen(CGF);
10244  break;
10245  case BodyGenTy::DupNoPriv:
10246  if (!Info.CaptureDeviceAddrMap.empty()) {
10247  CodeGen.setAction(NoPrivAction);
10248  CodeGen(CGF);
10249  }
10250  break;
10251  case BodyGenTy::NoPriv:
10252  if (Info.CaptureDeviceAddrMap.empty()) {
10253  CodeGen.setAction(NoPrivAction);
10254  CodeGen(CGF);
10255  }
10256  break;
10257  }
10258  return InsertPointTy(CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock(),
10259  CGF.Builder.GetInsertPoint());
10260  };
10261 
10262  auto DeviceAddrCB = [&](unsigned int I, llvm::Value *NewDecl) {
10263  if (const ValueDecl *DevVD = CombinedInfo.DevicePtrDecls[I]) {
10264  Info.CaptureDeviceAddrMap.try_emplace(DevVD, NewDecl);
10265  }
10266  };
10267 
10268  auto CustomMapperCB = [&](unsigned int I) {
10269  llvm::Value *MFunc = nullptr;
10270  if (CombinedInfo.Mappers[I]) {
10271  Info.HasMapper = true;
10272  MFunc = CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getOrCreateUserDefinedMapperFunc(
10273  cast<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(CombinedInfo.Mappers[I]));
10274  }
10275  return MFunc;
10276  };
10277 
10278  // Source location for the ident struct
10279  llvm::Value *RTLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, D.getBeginLoc());
10280 
10281  InsertPointTy AllocaIP(CGF.AllocaInsertPt->getParent(),
10282  CGF.AllocaInsertPt->getIterator());
10283  InsertPointTy CodeGenIP(CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock(),
10284  CGF.Builder.GetInsertPoint());
10285  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder::LocationDescription OmpLoc(CodeGenIP);
10286  CGF.Builder.restoreIP(OMPBuilder.createTargetData(
10287  OmpLoc, AllocaIP, CodeGenIP, DeviceID, IfCondVal, Info, GenMapInfoCB,
10288  /*MapperFunc=*/nullptr, BodyCB, DeviceAddrCB, CustomMapperCB, RTLoc));
10289 }
10290 
10291 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitTargetDataStandAloneCall(
10292  CodeGenFunction &CGF, const OMPExecutableDirective &D, const Expr *IfCond,
10293  const Expr *Device) {
10294  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
10295  return;
10296 
10297  assert((isa<OMPTargetEnterDataDirective>(D) ||
10298  isa<OMPTargetExitDataDirective>(D) ||
10299  isa<OMPTargetUpdateDirective>(D)) &&
10300  "Expecting either target enter, exit data, or update directives.");
10301 
10302  CodeGenFunction::OMPTargetDataInfo InputInfo;
10303  llvm::Value *MapTypesArray = nullptr;
10304  llvm::Value *MapNamesArray = nullptr;
10305  // Generate the code for the opening of the data environment.
10306  auto &&ThenGen = [this, &D, Device, &InputInfo, &MapTypesArray,
10307  &MapNamesArray](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &) {
10308  // Emit device ID if any.
10309  llvm::Value *DeviceID = nullptr;
10310  if (Device) {
10311  DeviceID = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(CGF.EmitScalarExpr(Device),
10312  CGF.Int64Ty, /*isSigned=*/true);
10313  } else {
10314  DeviceID = CGF.Builder.getInt64(OMP_DEVICEID_UNDEF);
10315  }
10316 
10317  // Emit the number of elements in the offloading arrays.
10318  llvm::Constant *PointerNum =
10319  CGF.Builder.getInt32(InputInfo.NumberOfTargetItems);
10320 
10321  // Source location for the ident struct
10322  llvm::Value *RTLoc = emitUpdateLocation(CGF, D.getBeginLoc());
10323 
10324  llvm::Value *OffloadingArgs[] = {
10325  RTLoc,
10326  DeviceID,
10327  PointerNum,
10328  InputInfo.BasePointersArray.emitRawPointer(CGF),
10329  InputInfo.PointersArray.emitRawPointer(CGF),
10330  InputInfo.SizesArray.emitRawPointer(CGF),
10331  MapTypesArray,
10332  MapNamesArray,
10333  InputInfo.MappersArray.emitRawPointer(CGF)};
10334 
10335  // Select the right runtime function call for each standalone
10336  // directive.
10337  const bool HasNowait = D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPNowaitClause>();
10338  RuntimeFunction RTLFn;
10339  switch (D.getDirectiveKind()) {
10340  case OMPD_target_enter_data:
10341  RTLFn = HasNowait ? OMPRTL___tgt_target_data_begin_nowait_mapper
10342  : OMPRTL___tgt_target_data_begin_mapper;
10343  break;
10344  case OMPD_target_exit_data:
10345  RTLFn = HasNowait ? OMPRTL___tgt_target_data_end_nowait_mapper
10346  : OMPRTL___tgt_target_data_end_mapper;
10347  break;
10348  case OMPD_target_update:
10349  RTLFn = HasNowait ? OMPRTL___tgt_target_data_update_nowait_mapper
10350  : OMPRTL___tgt_target_data_update_mapper;
10351  break;
10352  case OMPD_parallel:
10353  case OMPD_for:
10354  case OMPD_parallel_for:
10355  case OMPD_parallel_master:
10356  case OMPD_parallel_sections:
10357  case OMPD_for_simd:
10358  case OMPD_parallel_for_simd:
10359  case OMPD_cancel:
10360  case OMPD_cancellation_point:
10361  case OMPD_ordered:
10362  case OMPD_threadprivate:
10363  case OMPD_allocate:
10364  case OMPD_task:
10365  case OMPD_simd:
10366  case OMPD_tile:
10367  case OMPD_unroll:
10368  case OMPD_sections:
10369  case OMPD_section:
10370  case OMPD_single:
10371  case OMPD_master:
10372  case OMPD_critical:
10373  case OMPD_taskyield:
10374  case OMPD_barrier:
10375  case OMPD_taskwait:
10376  case OMPD_taskgroup:
10377  case OMPD_atomic:
10378  case OMPD_flush:
10379  case OMPD_depobj:
10380  case OMPD_scan:
10381  case OMPD_teams:
10382  case OMPD_target_data:
10383  case OMPD_distribute:
10384  case OMPD_distribute_simd:
10385  case OMPD_distribute_parallel_for:
10386  case OMPD_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
10387  case OMPD_teams_distribute:
10388  case OMPD_teams_distribute_simd:
10389  case OMPD_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
10390  case OMPD_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd:

10397  case OMPD_declare_reduction:
10398  case OMPD_declare_mapper:
10399  case OMPD_taskloop:
10400  case OMPD_taskloop_simd:
10401  case OMPD_master_taskloop:
10402  case OMPD_master_taskloop_simd:
10403  case OMPD_parallel_master_taskloop:
10404  case OMPD_parallel_master_taskloop_simd:
10405  case OMPD_target:
10406  case OMPD_target_simd:

10408  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_simd:
10409  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for:
10410  case OMPD_target_teams_distribute_parallel_for_simd:
10411  case OMPD_target_teams:
10412  case OMPD_target_parallel:
10413  case OMPD_target_parallel_for:
10414  case OMPD_target_parallel_for_simd:
10415  case OMPD_requires:
10416  case OMPD_metadirective:
10417  case OMPD_unknown:
10418  default:
10419  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected standalone target data directive.");
10420  break;
10421  }
10422  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(
10423  OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(CGM.getModule(), RTLFn),
10424  OffloadingArgs);
10425  };
10426 
10427  auto &&TargetThenGen = [this, &ThenGen, &D, &InputInfo, &MapTypesArray,
10428  &MapNamesArray](CodeGenFunction &CGF,
10429  PrePostActionTy &) {
10430  // Fill up the arrays with all the mapped variables.
10431  MappableExprsHandler::MapCombinedInfoTy CombinedInfo;
10432 
10433  // Get map clause information.
10434  MappableExprsHandler MEHandler(D, CGF);
10435  MEHandler.generateAllInfo(CombinedInfo, OMPBuilder);
10436 
10437  CGOpenMPRuntime::TargetDataInfo Info;
10438  // Fill up the arrays and create the arguments.
10439  emitOffloadingArrays(CGF, CombinedInfo, Info, OMPBuilder,
10440  /*IsNonContiguous=*/true);
10441  bool RequiresOuterTask = D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPDependClause>() ||
10442  D.hasClausesOfKind<OMPNowaitClause>();
10443  bool EmitDebug = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().getDebugInfo() !=
10444  llvm::codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo;
10445  OMPBuilder.emitOffloadingArraysArgument(CGF.Builder, Info.RTArgs, Info,
10446  EmitDebug,
10447  /*ForEndCall=*/false);
10448  InputInfo.NumberOfTargetItems = Info.NumberOfPtrs;
10449  InputInfo.BasePointersArray = Address(Info.RTArgs.BasePointersArray,
10450  CGF.VoidPtrTy, CGM.getPointerAlign());
10451  InputInfo.PointersArray = Address(Info.RTArgs.PointersArray, CGF.VoidPtrTy,
10452  CGM.getPointerAlign());
10453  InputInfo.SizesArray =
10454  Address(Info.RTArgs.SizesArray, CGF.Int64Ty, CGM.getPointerAlign());
10455  InputInfo.MappersArray =
10456  Address(Info.RTArgs.MappersArray, CGF.VoidPtrTy, CGM.getPointerAlign());
10457  MapTypesArray = Info.RTArgs.MapTypesArray;
10458  MapNamesArray = Info.RTArgs.MapNamesArray;
10459  if (RequiresOuterTask)
10460  CGF.EmitOMPTargetTaskBasedDirective(D, ThenGen, InputInfo);
10461  else
10462  emitInlinedDirective(CGF, D.getDirectiveKind(), ThenGen);
10463  };
10464 
10465  if (IfCond) {
10466  emitIfClause(CGF, IfCond, TargetThenGen,
10467  [](CodeGenFunction &CGF, PrePostActionTy &) {});
10468  } else {
10469  RegionCodeGenTy ThenRCG(TargetThenGen);
10470  ThenRCG(CGF);
10471  }
10472 }

10474 namespace {
10475  /// Kind of parameter in a function with 'declare simd' directive.
10476 enum ParamKindTy {
10477  Linear,
10478  LinearRef,
10479  LinearUVal,
10480  LinearVal,
10481  Uniform,
10482  Vector,
10483 };
10484 /// Attribute set of the parameter.
10485 struct ParamAttrTy {
10486  ParamKindTy Kind = Vector;
10487  llvm::APSInt StrideOrArg;
10488  llvm::APSInt Alignment;
10489  bool HasVarStride = false;
10490 };
10491 } // namespace
10492 
10493 static unsigned evaluateCDTSize(const FunctionDecl *FD,
10494  ArrayRef<ParamAttrTy> ParamAttrs) {
10495  // Every vector variant of a SIMD-enabled function has a vector length (VLEN).
10496  // If OpenMP clause "simdlen" is used, the VLEN is the value of the argument
10497  // of that clause. The VLEN value must be power of 2.
10498  // In other case the notion of the function`s "characteristic data type" (CDT)
10499  // is used to compute the vector length.
10500  // CDT is defined in the following order:
10501  // a) For non-void function, the CDT is the return type.
10502  // b) If the function has any non-uniform, non-linear parameters, then the
10503  // CDT is the type of the first such parameter.
10504  // c) If the CDT determined by a) or b) above is struct, union, or class
10505  // type which is pass-by-value (except for the type that maps to the
10506  // built-in complex data type), the characteristic data type is int.
10507  // d) If none of the above three cases is applicable, the CDT is int.
10508  // The VLEN is then determined based on the CDT and the size of vector
10509  // register of that ISA for which current vector version is generated. The
10510  // VLEN is computed using the formula below:
10511  // VLEN = sizeof(vector_register) / sizeof(CDT),
10512  // where vector register size specified in section 3.2.1 Registers and the
10513  // Stack Frame of original AMD64 ABI document.
10514  QualType RetType = FD->getReturnType();
10515  if (RetType.isNull())
10516  return 0;
10517  ASTContext &C = FD->getASTContext();
10518  QualType CDT;
10519  if (!RetType.isNull() && !RetType->isVoidType()) {
10520  CDT = RetType;
10521  } else {
10522  unsigned Offset = 0;
10523  if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
10524  if (ParamAttrs[Offset].Kind == Vector)
10525  CDT = C.getPointerType(C.getRecordType(MD->getParent()));
10526  ++Offset;
10527  }
10528  if (CDT.isNull()) {
10529  for (unsigned I = 0, E = FD->getNumParams(); I < E; ++I) {
10530  if (ParamAttrs[I + Offset].Kind == Vector) {
10531  CDT = FD->getParamDecl(I)->getType();
10532  break;
10533  }
10534  }
10535  }
10536  }
10537  if (CDT.isNull())
10538  CDT = C.IntTy;
10539  CDT = CDT->getCanonicalTypeUnqualified();
10540  if (CDT->isRecordType() || CDT->isUnionType())
10541  CDT = C.IntTy;
10542  return C.getTypeSize(CDT);
10543 }
10544 
10545 /// Mangle the parameter part of the vector function name according to
10546 /// their OpenMP classification. The mangling function is defined in
10547 /// section 4.5 of the AAVFABI(2021Q1).
10548 static std::string mangleVectorParameters(ArrayRef<ParamAttrTy> ParamAttrs) {
10549  SmallString<256> Buffer;
10550  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
10551  for (const auto &ParamAttr : ParamAttrs) {
10552  switch (ParamAttr.Kind) {
10553  case Linear:
10554  Out << 'l';
10555  break;
10556  case LinearRef:
10557  Out << 'R';
10558  break;
10559  case LinearUVal:
10560  Out << 'U';
10561  break;
10562  case LinearVal:
10563  Out << 'L';
10564  break;
10565  case Uniform:
10566  Out << 'u';
10567  break;
10568  case Vector:
10569  Out << 'v';
10570  break;
10571  }
10572  if (ParamAttr.HasVarStride)
10573  Out << "s" << ParamAttr.StrideOrArg;
10574  else if (ParamAttr.Kind == Linear || ParamAttr.Kind == LinearRef ||
10575  ParamAttr.Kind == LinearUVal || ParamAttr.Kind == LinearVal) {
10576  // Don't print the step value if it is not present or if it is
10577  // equal to 1.
10578  if (ParamAttr.StrideOrArg < 0)
10579  Out << 'n' << -ParamAttr.StrideOrArg;
10580  else if (ParamAttr.StrideOrArg != 1)
10581  Out << ParamAttr.StrideOrArg;
10582  }
10583 
10584  if (!!ParamAttr.Alignment)
10585  Out << 'a' << ParamAttr.Alignment;
10586  }
10587 
10588  return std::string(Out.str());
10589 }
10590 
10591 static void
10592 emitX86DeclareSimdFunction(const FunctionDecl *FD, llvm::Function *Fn,
10593  const llvm::APSInt &VLENVal,
10594  ArrayRef<ParamAttrTy> ParamAttrs,
10595  OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BranchStateTy State) {
10596  struct ISADataTy {
10597  char ISA;
10598  unsigned VecRegSize;
10599  };
10600  ISADataTy ISAData[] = {
10601  {
10602  'b', 128
10603  }, // SSE
10604  {
10605  'c', 256
10606  }, // AVX
10607  {
10608  'd', 256
10609  }, // AVX2
10610  {
10611  'e', 512
10612  }, // AVX512
10613  };
10614  llvm::SmallVector<char, 2> Masked;
10615  switch (State) {
10616  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Undefined:
10617  Masked.push_back('N');
10618  Masked.push_back('M');
10619  break;
10620  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Notinbranch:
10621  Masked.push_back('N');
10622  break;
10623  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Inbranch:
10624  Masked.push_back('M');
10625  break;
10626  }
10627  for (char Mask : Masked) {
10628  for (const ISADataTy &Data : ISAData) {
10629  SmallString<256> Buffer;
10630  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
10631  Out << "_ZGV" << Data.ISA << Mask;
10632  if (!VLENVal) {
10633  unsigned NumElts = evaluateCDTSize(FD, ParamAttrs);
10634  assert(NumElts && "Non-zero simdlen/cdtsize expected");
10635  Out << llvm::APSInt::getUnsigned(Data.VecRegSize / NumElts);
10636  } else {
10637  Out << VLENVal;
10638  }
10639  Out << mangleVectorParameters(ParamAttrs);
10640  Out << '_' << Fn->getName();
10641  Fn->addFnAttr(Out.str());
10642  }
10643  }
10644 }
10645 
10646 // This are the Functions that are needed to mangle the name of the
10647 // vector functions generated by the compiler, according to the rules
10648 // defined in the "Vector Function ABI specifications for AArch64",
10649 // available at
10650 // https://developer.arm.com/products/software-development-tools/hpc/arm-compiler-for-hpc/vector-function-abi.
10651 
10652 /// Maps To Vector (MTV), as defined in 4.1.1 of the AAVFABI (2021Q1).
10653 static bool getAArch64MTV(QualType QT, ParamKindTy Kind) {
10654  QT = QT.getCanonicalType();
10655 
10656  if (QT->isVoidType())
10657  return false;
10658 
10659  if (Kind == ParamKindTy::Uniform)
10660  return false;
10661 
10662  if (Kind == ParamKindTy::LinearUVal || Kind == ParamKindTy::LinearRef)
10663  return false;
10664 
10665  if ((Kind == ParamKindTy::Linear || Kind == ParamKindTy::LinearVal) &&
10666  !QT->isReferenceType())
10667  return false;
10668 
10669  return true;
10670 }
10671 
10672 /// Pass By Value (PBV), as defined in 3.1.2 of the AAVFABI.
10673 static bool getAArch64PBV(QualType QT, ASTContext &C) {
10674  QT = QT.getCanonicalType();
10675  unsigned Size = C.getTypeSize(QT);
10676 
10677  // Only scalars and complex within 16 bytes wide set PVB to true.
10678  if (Size != 8 && Size != 16 && Size != 32 && Size != 64 && Size != 128)
10679  return false;
10680 
10681  if (QT->isFloatingType())
10682  return true;
10683 
10684  if (QT->isIntegerType())
10685  return true;
10686 
10687  if (QT->isPointerType())
10688  return true;
10689 
10690  // TODO: Add support for complex types (section 3.1.2, item 2).
10691 
10692  return false;
10693 }
10694 
10695 /// Computes the lane size (LS) of a return type or of an input parameter,
10696 /// as defined by `LS(P)` in 3.2.1 of the AAVFABI.
10697 /// TODO: Add support for references, section 3.2.1, item 1.
10698 static unsigned getAArch64LS(QualType QT, ParamKindTy Kind, ASTContext &C) {
10699  if (!getAArch64MTV(QT, Kind) && QT.getCanonicalType()->isPointerType()) {
10700  QualType PTy = QT.getCanonicalType()->getPointeeType();
10701  if (getAArch64PBV(PTy, C))
10702  return C.getTypeSize(PTy);
10703  }
10704  if (getAArch64PBV(QT, C))
10705  return C.getTypeSize(QT);
10706 
10707  return C.getTypeSize(C.getUIntPtrType());
10708 }
10709 
10710 // Get Narrowest Data Size (NDS) and Widest Data Size (WDS) from the
10711 // signature of the scalar function, as defined in 3.2.2 of the
10712 // AAVFABI.
10713 static std::tuple<unsigned, unsigned, bool>
10714 getNDSWDS(const FunctionDecl *FD, ArrayRef<ParamAttrTy> ParamAttrs) {
10715  QualType RetType = FD->getReturnType().getCanonicalType();
10716 
10717  ASTContext &C = FD->getASTContext();
10718 
10719  bool OutputBecomesInput = false;
10720 
10721  llvm::SmallVector<unsigned, 8> Sizes;
10722  if (!RetType->isVoidType()) {
10723  Sizes.push_back(getAArch64LS(RetType, ParamKindTy::Vector, C));
10724  if (!getAArch64PBV(RetType, C) && getAArch64MTV(RetType, {}))
10725  OutputBecomesInput = true;
10726  }
10727  for (unsigned I = 0, E = FD->getNumParams(); I < E; ++I) {
10728  QualType QT = FD->getParamDecl(I)->getType().getCanonicalType();
10729  Sizes.push_back(getAArch64LS(QT, ParamAttrs[I].Kind, C));
10730  }
10731 
10732  assert(!Sizes.empty() && "Unable to determine NDS and WDS.");
10733  // The LS of a function parameter / return value can only be a power
10734  // of 2, starting from 8 bits, up to 128.
10735  assert(llvm::all_of(Sizes,
10736  [](unsigned Size) {
10737  return Size == 8 || Size == 16 || Size == 32 ||
10738  Size == 64 || Size == 128;
10739  }) &&
10740  "Invalid size");
10741 
10742  return std::make_tuple(*std::min_element(std::begin(Sizes), std::end(Sizes)),
10743  *std::max_element(std::begin(Sizes), std::end(Sizes)),
10744  OutputBecomesInput);
10745 }
10746 
10747 // Function used to add the attribute. The parameter `VLEN` is
10748 // templated to allow the use of "x" when targeting scalable functions
10749 // for SVE.
10750 template <typename T>
10751 static void addAArch64VectorName(T VLEN, StringRef LMask, StringRef Prefix,
10752  char ISA, StringRef ParSeq,
10753  StringRef MangledName, bool OutputBecomesInput,
10754  llvm::Function *Fn) {
10755  SmallString<256> Buffer;
10756  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
10757  Out << Prefix << ISA << LMask << VLEN;
10758  if (OutputBecomesInput)
10759  Out << "v";
10760  Out << ParSeq << "_" << MangledName;
10761  Fn->addFnAttr(Out.str());
10762 }
10763 
10764 // Helper function to generate the Advanced SIMD names depending on
10765 // the value of the NDS when simdlen is not present.
10766 static void addAArch64AdvSIMDNDSNames(unsigned NDS, StringRef Mask,
10767  StringRef Prefix, char ISA,
10768  StringRef ParSeq, StringRef MangledName,
10769  bool OutputBecomesInput,
10770  llvm::Function *Fn) {
10771  switch (NDS) {
10772  case 8:
10773  addAArch64VectorName(8, Mask, Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10774  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10775  addAArch64VectorName(16, Mask, Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10776  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10777  break;
10778  case 16:
10779  addAArch64VectorName(4, Mask, Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10780  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10781  addAArch64VectorName(8, Mask, Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10782  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10783  break;
10784  case 32:
10785  addAArch64VectorName(2, Mask, Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10786  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10787  addAArch64VectorName(4, Mask, Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10788  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10789  break;
10790  case 64:
10791  case 128:
10792  addAArch64VectorName(2, Mask, Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10793  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10794  break;
10795  default:
10796  llvm_unreachable("Scalar type is too wide.");
10797  }
10798 }
10799 
10800 /// Emit vector function attributes for AArch64, as defined in the AAVFABI.
10801 static void emitAArch64DeclareSimdFunction(
10802  CodeGenModule &CGM, const FunctionDecl *FD, unsigned UserVLEN,
10803  ArrayRef<ParamAttrTy> ParamAttrs,
10804  OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BranchStateTy State, StringRef MangledName,
10805  char ISA, unsigned VecRegSize, llvm::Function *Fn, SourceLocation SLoc) {
10806 
10807  // Get basic data for building the vector signature.
10808  const auto Data = getNDSWDS(FD, ParamAttrs);
10809  const unsigned NDS = std::get<0>(Data);
10810  const unsigned WDS = std::get<1>(Data);
10811  const bool OutputBecomesInput = std::get<2>(Data);
10812 
10813  // Check the values provided via `simdlen` by the user.
10814  // 1. A `simdlen(1)` doesn't produce vector signatures,
10815  if (UserVLEN == 1) {
10816  unsigned DiagID = CGM.getDiags().getCustomDiagID(
10817  DiagnosticsEngine::Warning,
10818  "The clause simdlen(1) has no effect when targeting aarch64.");
10819  CGM.getDiags().Report(SLoc, DiagID);
10820  return;
10821  }
10822 
10823  // 2. Section 3.3.1, item 1: user input must be a power of 2 for
10824  // Advanced SIMD output.
10825  if (ISA == 'n' && UserVLEN && !llvm::isPowerOf2_32(UserVLEN)) {
10826  unsigned DiagID = CGM.getDiags().getCustomDiagID(
10827  DiagnosticsEngine::Warning, "The value specified in simdlen must be a "
10828  "power of 2 when targeting Advanced SIMD.");
10829  CGM.getDiags().Report(SLoc, DiagID);
10830  return;
10831  }
10832 
10833  // 3. Section 3.4.1. SVE fixed lengh must obey the architectural
10834  // limits.
10835  if (ISA == 's' && UserVLEN != 0) {
10836  if ((UserVLEN * WDS > 2048) || (UserVLEN * WDS % 128 != 0)) {
10837  unsigned DiagID = CGM.getDiags().getCustomDiagID(
10838  DiagnosticsEngine::Warning, "The clause simdlen must fit the %0-bit "
10839  "lanes in the architectural constraints "
10840  "for SVE (min is 128-bit, max is "
10841  "2048-bit, by steps of 128-bit)");
10842  CGM.getDiags().Report(SLoc, DiagID) << WDS;
10843  return;
10844  }
10845  }
10846 
10847  // Sort out parameter sequence.
10848  const std::string ParSeq = mangleVectorParameters(ParamAttrs);
10849  StringRef Prefix = "_ZGV";
10850  // Generate simdlen from user input (if any).
10851  if (UserVLEN) {
10852  if (ISA == 's') {
10853  // SVE generates only a masked function.
10854  addAArch64VectorName(UserVLEN, "M", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10855  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10856  } else {
10857  assert(ISA == 'n' && "Expected ISA either 's' or 'n'.");
10858  // Advanced SIMD generates one or two functions, depending on
10859  // the `[not]inbranch` clause.
10860  switch (State) {
10861  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Undefined:
10862  addAArch64VectorName(UserVLEN, "N", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10863  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10864  addAArch64VectorName(UserVLEN, "M", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10865  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10866  break;
10867  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Notinbranch:
10868  addAArch64VectorName(UserVLEN, "N", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10869  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10870  break;
10871  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Inbranch:
10872  addAArch64VectorName(UserVLEN, "M", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10873  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10874  break;
10875  }
10876  }
10877  } else {
10878  // If no user simdlen is provided, follow the AAVFABI rules for
10879  // generating the vector length.
10880  if (ISA == 's') {
10881  // SVE, section 3.4.1, item 1.
10882  addAArch64VectorName("x", "M", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10883  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10884  } else {
10885  assert(ISA == 'n' && "Expected ISA either 's' or 'n'.");
10886  // Advanced SIMD, Section 3.3.1 of the AAVFABI, generates one or
10887  // two vector names depending on the use of the clause
10888  // `[not]inbranch`.
10889  switch (State) {
10890  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Undefined:
10891  addAArch64AdvSIMDNDSNames(NDS, "N", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10892  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10893  addAArch64AdvSIMDNDSNames(NDS, "M", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10894  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10895  break;
10896  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Notinbranch:
10897  addAArch64AdvSIMDNDSNames(NDS, "N", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10898  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10899  break;
10900  case OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BS_Inbranch:
10901  addAArch64AdvSIMDNDSNames(NDS, "M", Prefix, ISA, ParSeq, MangledName,
10902  OutputBecomesInput, Fn);
10903  break;
10904  }
10905  }
10906  }
10907 }
10908 
10909 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitDeclareSimdFunction(const FunctionDecl *FD,
10910  llvm::Function *Fn) {
10911  ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
10912  FD = FD->getMostRecentDecl();
10913  while (FD) {
10914  // Map params to their positions in function decl.
10915  llvm::DenseMap<const Decl *, unsigned> ParamPositions;
10916  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FD))
10917  ParamPositions.try_emplace(FD, 0);
10918  unsigned ParamPos = ParamPositions.size();
10919  for (const ParmVarDecl *P : FD->parameters()) {
10920  ParamPositions.try_emplace(P->getCanonicalDecl(), ParamPos);
10921  ++ParamPos;
10922  }
10923  for (const auto *Attr : FD->specific_attrs<OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr>()) {
10924  llvm::SmallVector<ParamAttrTy, 8> ParamAttrs(ParamPositions.size());
10925  // Mark uniform parameters.
10926  for (const Expr *E : Attr->uniforms()) {
10927  E = E->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
10928  unsigned Pos;
10929  if (isa<CXXThisExpr>(E)) {
10930  Pos = ParamPositions[FD];
10931  } else {
10932  const auto *PVD = cast<ParmVarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)->getDecl())
10933  ->getCanonicalDecl();
10934  auto It = ParamPositions.find(PVD);
10935  assert(It != ParamPositions.end() && "Function parameter not found");
10936  Pos = It->second;
10937  }
10938  ParamAttrs[Pos].Kind = Uniform;
10939  }
10940  // Get alignment info.
10941  auto *NI = Attr->alignments_begin();
10942  for (const Expr *E : Attr->aligneds()) {
10943  E = E->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
10944  unsigned Pos;
10945  QualType ParmTy;
10946  if (isa<CXXThisExpr>(E)) {
10947  Pos = ParamPositions[FD];
10948  ParmTy = E->getType();
10949  } else {
10950  const auto *PVD = cast<ParmVarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)->getDecl())
10951  ->getCanonicalDecl();
10952  auto It = ParamPositions.find(PVD);
10953  assert(It != ParamPositions.end() && "Function parameter not found");
10954  Pos = It->second;
10955  ParmTy = PVD->getType();
10956  }
10957  ParamAttrs[Pos].Alignment =
10958  (*NI)
10959  ? (*NI)->EvaluateKnownConstInt(C)
10960  : llvm::APSInt::getUnsigned(
10961  C.toCharUnitsFromBits(C.getOpenMPDefaultSimdAlign(ParmTy))
10962  .getQuantity());
10963  ++NI;
10964  }
10965  // Mark linear parameters.
10966  auto *SI = Attr->steps_begin();
10967  auto *MI = Attr->modifiers_begin();
10968  for (const Expr *E : Attr->linears()) {
10969  E = E->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
10970  unsigned Pos;
10971  bool IsReferenceType = false;
10972  // Rescaling factor needed to compute the linear parameter
10973  // value in the mangled name.
10974  unsigned PtrRescalingFactor = 1;
10975  if (isa<CXXThisExpr>(E)) {
10976  Pos = ParamPositions[FD];
10977  auto *P = cast<PointerType>(E->getType());
10978  PtrRescalingFactor = CGM.getContext()
10979  .getTypeSizeInChars(P->getPointeeType())
10980  .getQuantity();
10981  } else {
10982  const auto *PVD = cast<ParmVarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)->getDecl())
10983  ->getCanonicalDecl();
10984  auto It = ParamPositions.find(PVD);
10985  assert(It != ParamPositions.end() && "Function parameter not found");
10986  Pos = It->second;
10987  if (auto *P = dyn_cast<PointerType>(PVD->getType()))
10988  PtrRescalingFactor = CGM.getContext()
10989  .getTypeSizeInChars(P->getPointeeType())
10990  .getQuantity();
10991  else if (PVD->getType()->isReferenceType()) {
10992  IsReferenceType = true;
10993  PtrRescalingFactor =
10994  CGM.getContext()
10995  .getTypeSizeInChars(PVD->getType().getNonReferenceType())
10996  .getQuantity();
10997  }
10998  }
10999  ParamAttrTy &ParamAttr = ParamAttrs[Pos];
11000  if (*MI == OMPC_LINEAR_ref)
11001  ParamAttr.Kind = LinearRef;
11002  else if (*MI == OMPC_LINEAR_uval)
11003  ParamAttr.Kind = LinearUVal;
11004  else if (IsReferenceType)
11005  ParamAttr.Kind = LinearVal;
11006  else
11007  ParamAttr.Kind = Linear;
11008  // Assuming a stride of 1, for `linear` without modifiers.
11009  ParamAttr.StrideOrArg = llvm::APSInt::getUnsigned(1);
11010  if (*SI) {
11011  Expr::EvalResult Result;
11012  if (!(*SI)->EvaluateAsInt(Result, C, Expr::SE_AllowSideEffects)) {
11013  if (const auto *DRE =
11014  cast<DeclRefExpr>((*SI)->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) {
11015  if (const auto *StridePVD =
11016  dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
11017  ParamAttr.HasVarStride = true;
11018  auto It = ParamPositions.find(StridePVD->getCanonicalDecl());
11019  assert(It != ParamPositions.end() &&
11020  "Function parameter not found");
11021  ParamAttr.StrideOrArg = llvm::APSInt::getUnsigned(It->second);
11022  }
11023  }
11024  } else {
11025  ParamAttr.StrideOrArg = Result.Val.getInt();
11026  }
11027  }
11028  // If we are using a linear clause on a pointer, we need to
11029  // rescale the value of linear_step with the byte size of the
11030  // pointee type.
11031  if (!ParamAttr.HasVarStride &&
11032  (ParamAttr.Kind == Linear || ParamAttr.Kind == LinearRef))
11033  ParamAttr.StrideOrArg = ParamAttr.StrideOrArg * PtrRescalingFactor;
11034  ++SI;
11035  ++MI;
11036  }
11037  llvm::APSInt VLENVal;
11038  SourceLocation ExprLoc;
11039  const Expr *VLENExpr = Attr->getSimdlen();
11040  if (VLENExpr) {
11041  VLENVal = VLENExpr->EvaluateKnownConstInt(C);
11042  ExprLoc = VLENExpr->getExprLoc();
11043  }
11044  OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr::BranchStateTy State = Attr->getBranchState();
11045  if (CGM.getTriple().isX86()) {
11046  emitX86DeclareSimdFunction(FD, Fn, VLENVal, ParamAttrs, State);
11047  } else if (CGM.getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64) {
11048  unsigned VLEN = VLENVal.getExtValue();
11049  StringRef MangledName = Fn->getName();
11050  if (CGM.getTarget().hasFeature("sve"))
11051  emitAArch64DeclareSimdFunction(CGM, FD, VLEN, ParamAttrs, State,
11052  MangledName, 's', 128, Fn, ExprLoc);
11053  else if (CGM.getTarget().hasFeature("neon"))
11054  emitAArch64DeclareSimdFunction(CGM, FD, VLEN, ParamAttrs, State,
11055  MangledName, 'n', 128, Fn, ExprLoc);
11056  }
11057  }
11058  FD = FD->getPreviousDecl();
11059  }
11060 }
11061 
11062 namespace {
11063 /// Cleanup action for doacross support.
11064 class DoacrossCleanupTy final : public EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
11065 public:
11066  static const int DoacrossFinArgs = 2;
11067 
11068 private:
11069  llvm::FunctionCallee RTLFn;
11070  llvm::Value *Args[DoacrossFinArgs];
11071 
11072 public:
11073  DoacrossCleanupTy(llvm::FunctionCallee RTLFn,
11074  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> CallArgs)
11075  : RTLFn(RTLFn) {
11076  assert(CallArgs.size() == DoacrossFinArgs);
11077  std::copy(CallArgs.begin(), CallArgs.end(), std::begin(Args));
11078  }
11079  void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags /*flags*/) override {
11080  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
11081  return;
11082  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(RTLFn, Args);
11083  }
11084 };
11085 } // namespace
11086 
11087 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitDoacrossInit(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
11088  const OMPLoopDirective &D,
11089  ArrayRef<Expr *> NumIterations) {
11090  if (!CGF.HaveInsertPoint())
11091  return;
11092 
11093  ASTContext &C = CGM.getContext();
11094  QualType Int64Ty = C.getIntTypeForBitwidth(/*DestWidth=*/64, /*Signed=*/true);
11095  RecordDecl *RD;
11096  if (KmpDimTy.isNull()) {
11097  // Build struct kmp_dim { // loop bounds info casted to kmp_int64
11098  // kmp_int64 lo; // lower
11099  // kmp_int64 up; // upper
11100  // kmp_int64 st; // stride
11101  // };
11102  RD = C.buildImplicitRecord("kmp_dim");
11103  RD->startDefinition();
11104  addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, Int64Ty);
11105  addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, Int64Ty);
11106  addFieldToRecordDecl(C, RD, Int64Ty);
11107  RD->completeDefinition();
11108  KmpDimTy = C.getRecordType(RD);
11109  } else {
11110  RD = cast<RecordDecl>(KmpDimTy->getAsTagDecl());
11111  }
11112  llvm::APInt Size(/*numBits=*/32, NumIterations.size());
11113  QualType ArrayTy = C.getConstantArrayType(KmpDimTy, Size, nullptr,
11114  ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
11115 
11116  Address DimsAddr = CGF.CreateMemTemp(ArrayTy, "dims");
11117  CGF.EmitNullInitialization(DimsAddr, ArrayTy);
11118  enum { LowerFD = 0, UpperFD, StrideFD };
11119  // Fill dims with data.
11120  for (unsigned I = 0, E = NumIterations.size(); I < E; ++I) {
11121  LValue DimsLVal = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(
11122  CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(DimsAddr, I), KmpDimTy);
11123  // dims.upper = num_iterations;
11124  LValue UpperLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(
11125  DimsLVal, *std::next(RD->field_begin(), UpperFD));
11126  llvm::Value *NumIterVal = CGF.EmitScalarConversion(
11127  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(NumIterations[I]), NumIterations[I]->getType(),
11128  Int64Ty, NumIterations[I]->getExprLoc());
11129  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(NumIterVal, UpperLVal);
11130  // dims.stride = 1;
11131  LValue StrideLVal = CGF.EmitLValueForField(
11132  DimsLVal, *std::next(RD->field_begin(), StrideFD));
11133  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(CGM.Int64Ty, /*V=*/1),
11134  StrideLVal);
11135  }
11136 
11137  // Build call void __kmpc_doacross_init(ident_t *loc, kmp_int32 gtid,
11138  // kmp_int32 num_dims, struct kmp_dim * dims);
11139  llvm::Value *Args[] = {
11140  emitUpdateLocation(CGF, D.getBeginLoc()),
11141  getThreadID(CGF, D.getBeginLoc()),
11142  llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(CGM.Int32Ty, NumIterations.size()),
11143  CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
11144  CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(DimsAddr, 0).emitRawPointer(CGF),
11145  CGM.VoidPtrTy)};
11146 
11147  llvm::FunctionCallee RTLFn = OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
11148  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_doacross_init);
11149  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(RTLFn, Args);
11150  llvm::Value *FiniArgs[DoacrossCleanupTy::DoacrossFinArgs] = {
11151  emitUpdateLocation(CGF, D.getEndLoc()), getThreadID(CGF, D.getEndLoc())};
11152  llvm::FunctionCallee FiniRTLFn = OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(
11153  CGM.getModule(), OMPRTL___kmpc_doacross_fini);
11154  CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<DoacrossCleanupTy>(NormalAndEHCleanup, FiniRTLFn,
11155  llvm::ArrayRef(FiniArgs));
11156 }
11157 
11158 template <typename T>
11159 static void EmitDoacrossOrdered(CodeGenFunction &CGF, CodeGenModule &CGM,
11160  const T *C, llvm::Value *ULoc,
11161  llvm::Value *ThreadID) {
11162  QualType Int64Ty =
11163  CGM.getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(/*DestWidth=*/64, /*Signed=*/1);
11164  llvm::APInt Size(/*numBits=*/32, C->getNumLoops());
11165  QualType ArrayTy = CGM.getContext().getConstantArrayType(
11166  Int64Ty, Size, nullptr, ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0);
11167  Address CntAddr = CGF.CreateMemTemp(ArrayTy, ".cnt.addr");
11168  for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumLoops(); I < E; ++I) {
11169  const Expr *CounterVal = C->getLoopData(I);
11170  assert(CounterVal);
11171  llvm::Value *CntVal = CGF.EmitScalarConversion(
11172  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(CounterVal), CounterVal->getType(), Int64Ty,
11173  CounterVal->getExprLoc());
11174  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(CntVal, CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(CntAddr, I),
11175  /*Volatile=*/false, Int64Ty);
11176  }
11177  llvm::Value *Args[] = {
11178  ULoc, ThreadID,
11179  CGF.Builder.CreateConstArrayGEP(CntAddr, 0).emitRawPointer(CGF)};
11180  llvm::FunctionCallee RTLFn;
11181  llvm::OpenMPIRBuilder &OMPBuilder = CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().getOMPBuilder();
11182  OMPDoacrossKind<T> ODK;
11183  if (ODK.isSource(C)) {
11184  RTLFn = OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(CGM.getModule(),
11185  OMPRTL___kmpc_doacross_post);
11186  } else {
11187  assert(ODK.isSink(C) && "Expect sink modifier.");
11188  RTLFn = OMPBuilder.getOrCreateRuntimeFunction(CGM.getModule(),
11189  OMPRTL___kmpc_doacross_wait);
11190  }
11191  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(RTLFn, Args);
11192 }
11193 
11194 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitDoacrossOrdered(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
11195  const OMPDependClause *C) {
11196  return EmitDoacrossOrdered<OMPDependClause>(
11197  CGF, CGM, C, emitUpdateLocation(CGF, C->getBeginLoc()),
11198  getThreadID(CGF, C->getBeginLoc()));
11199 }

11201 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitDoacrossOrdered(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
11202  const OMPDoacrossClause *C) {
11203  return EmitDoacrossOrdered<OMPDoacrossClause>(
11204  CGF, CGM, C, emitUpdateLocation(CGF, C->getBeginLoc()),
11205  getThreadID(CGF, C->getBeginLoc()));
11206 }

11208 void CGOpenMPRuntime::emitCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF, SourceLocation Loc,
11209  llvm::FunctionCallee Callee,
11210  ArrayRef<llvm::Value *> Args) const {
11211  assert(Loc.isValid() && "Outlined function call location must be valid.");
11212  auto DL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateDefaultArtificial(CGF, Loc);
11213 
11214  if (auto *Fn = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Callee.getCallee())) {
11215  if (Fn->doesNotThrow()) {
11216  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(Fn, Args);
11217  return;
11218  }
11219  }
11220  CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(Callee, Args);
11221 }
